55 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCastToVoidPtr(llvm::Value *value) {
56  unsigned addressSpace =
57  cast<llvm::PointerType>(value->getType())->getAddressSpace();
58 
59  llvm::PointerType *destType = Int8PtrTy;
60  if (addressSpace)
61  destType = llvm::Type::getInt8PtrTy(getLLVMContext(), addressSpace);
62 
63  if (value->getType() == destType) return value;
64  return Builder.CreateBitCast(value, destType);
65 }

67 /// CreateTempAlloca - This creates a alloca and inserts it into the entry
68 /// block.
69 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(llvm::Type *Ty,
70  CharUnits Align,
71  const Twine &Name,
72  llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
73  auto Alloca = CreateTempAlloca(Ty, Name, ArraySize);
74  Alloca->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
75  return Address(Alloca, Ty, Align);
76 }
77 
78 /// CreateTempAlloca - This creates a alloca and inserts it into the entry
79 /// block. The alloca is casted to default address space if necessary.
80 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty, CharUnits Align,
81  const Twine &Name,
82  llvm::Value *ArraySize,
83  Address *AllocaAddr) {
84  auto Alloca = CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(Ty, Align, Name, ArraySize);
85  if (AllocaAddr)
86  *AllocaAddr = Alloca;
87  llvm::Value *V = Alloca.getPointer();
88  // Alloca always returns a pointer in alloca address space, which may
89  // be different from the type defined by the language. For example,
90  // in C++ the auto variables are in the default address space. Therefore
91  // cast alloca to the default address space when necessary.
92  if (getASTAllocaAddressSpace() != LangAS::Default) {
93  auto DestAddrSpace = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default);
94  llvm::IRBuilderBase::InsertPointGuard IPG(Builder);
95  // When ArraySize is nullptr, alloca is inserted at AllocaInsertPt,
96  // otherwise alloca is inserted at the current insertion point of the
97  // builder.
98  if (!ArraySize)
99  Builder.SetInsertPoint(getPostAllocaInsertPoint());
100  V = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
101  *this, V, getASTAllocaAddressSpace(), LangAS::Default,
102  Ty->getPointerTo(DestAddrSpace), /*non-null*/ true);
103  }
104 
105  return Address(V, Ty, Align);
106 }
107 
108 /// CreateTempAlloca - This creates an alloca and inserts it into the entry
109 /// block if \p ArraySize is nullptr, otherwise inserts it at the current
110 /// insertion point of the builder.
111 llvm::AllocaInst *CodeGenFunction::CreateTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty,
112  const Twine &Name,
113  llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
114  if (ArraySize)
115  return Builder.CreateAlloca(Ty, ArraySize, Name);
116  return new llvm::AllocaInst(Ty, CGM.getDataLayout().getAllocaAddrSpace(),
117  ArraySize, Name, AllocaInsertPt);
118 }

120 /// CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca - This creates an alloca with the
121 /// default alignment of the corresponding LLVM type, which is *not*
122 /// guaranteed to be related in any way to the expected alignment of
123 /// an AST type that might have been lowered to Ty.
124 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(llvm::Type *Ty,
125  const Twine &Name) {
126  CharUnits Align =
127  CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(Ty));
128  return CreateTempAlloca(Ty, Align, Name);
129 }

131 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateIRTemp(QualType Ty, const Twine &Name) {
132  CharUnits Align = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
133  return CreateTempAlloca(ConvertType(Ty), Align, Name);
134 }

136 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTemp(QualType Ty, const Twine &Name,
137  Address *Alloca) {
138  // FIXME: Should we prefer the preferred type alignment here?
139  return CreateMemTemp(Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty), Name, Alloca);
140 }
141 
142 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTemp(QualType Ty, CharUnits Align,
143  const Twine &Name, Address *Alloca) {
144  Address Result = CreateTempAlloca(ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), Align, Name,
145  /*ArraySize=*/nullptr, Alloca);
146 
147  if (Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
148  auto *ArrayTy = cast<llvm::ArrayType>(Result.getElementType());
149  auto *VectorTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(ArrayTy->getElementType(),
150  ArrayTy->getNumElements());
151 
152  Result = Address(
153  Builder.CreateBitCast(Result.getPointer(), VectorTy->getPointerTo()),
154  VectorTy, Result.getAlignment());
155  }
156  return Result;
157 }
158 
159 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTempWithoutCast(QualType Ty, CharUnits Align,
160  const Twine &Name) {
161  return CreateTempAllocaWithoutCast(ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), Align, Name);
162 }
163 
164 Address CodeGenFunction::CreateMemTempWithoutCast(QualType Ty,
165  const Twine &Name) {
166  return CreateMemTempWithoutCast(Ty, getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty),
167  Name);
168 }

170 /// EvaluateExprAsBool - Perform the usual unary conversions on the specified
171 /// expression and compare the result against zero, returning an Int1Ty value.
172 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EvaluateExprAsBool(const Expr *E) {
173  PGO.setCurrentStmt(E);
174  if (const MemberPointerType *MPT = E->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
175  llvm::Value *MemPtr = EmitScalarExpr(E);
176  return CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(*this, MemPtr, MPT);
177  }
178 
179  QualType BoolTy = getContext().BoolTy;
180  SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
181  CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(*this, E);
182  if (!E->getType()->isAnyComplexType())
183  return EmitScalarConversion(EmitScalarExpr(E), E->getType(), BoolTy, Loc);
184 
185  return EmitComplexToScalarConversion(EmitComplexExpr(E), E->getType(), BoolTy,
186  Loc);
187 }
188 
189 /// EmitIgnoredExpr - Emit code to compute the specified expression,
190 /// ignoring the result.
191 void CodeGenFunction::EmitIgnoredExpr(const Expr *E) {
192  if (E->isPRValue())
193  return (void) EmitAnyExpr(E, AggValueSlot::ignored(), true);
194 
195  // Just emit it as an l-value and drop the result.
196  EmitLValue(E);
197 }
198 
199 /// EmitAnyExpr - Emit code to compute the specified expression which
200 /// can have any type. The result is returned as an RValue struct.
201 /// If this is an aggregate expression, AggSlot indicates where the
202 /// result should be returned.
203 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExpr(const Expr *E,
204  AggValueSlot aggSlot,
205  bool ignoreResult) {
206  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
207  case TEK_Scalar:
208  return RValue::get(EmitScalarExpr(E, ignoreResult));
209  case TEK_Complex:
210  return RValue::getComplex(EmitComplexExpr(E, ignoreResult, ignoreResult));
211  case TEK_Aggregate:
212  if (!ignoreResult && aggSlot.isIgnored())
213  aggSlot = CreateAggTemp(E->getType(), "agg-temp");
214  EmitAggExpr(E, aggSlot);
215  return aggSlot.asRValue();
216  }
217  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
218 }
219 
220 /// EmitAnyExprToTemp - Similar to EmitAnyExpr(), however, the result will
221 /// always be accessible even if no aggregate location is provided.
222 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExprToTemp(const Expr *E) {
223  AggValueSlot AggSlot = AggValueSlot::ignored();
224 
225  if (hasAggregateEvaluationKind(E->getType()))
226  AggSlot = CreateAggTemp(E->getType(), "agg.tmp");
227  return EmitAnyExpr(E, AggSlot);
228 }
229 
230 /// EmitAnyExprToMem - Evaluate an expression into a given memory
231 /// location.
232 void CodeGenFunction::EmitAnyExprToMem(const Expr *E,
233  Address Location,
234  Qualifiers Quals,
235  bool IsInit) {
236  // FIXME: This function should take an LValue as an argument.
237  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
238  case TEK_Complex:
239  EmitComplexExprIntoLValue(E, MakeAddrLValue(Location, E->getType()),
240  /*isInit*/ false);
241  return;
242 
243  case TEK_Aggregate: {
244  EmitAggExpr(E, AggValueSlot::forAddr(Location, Quals,
245  AggValueSlot::IsDestructed_t(IsInit),
246  AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
247  AggValueSlot::IsAliased_t(!IsInit),
248  AggValueSlot::MayOverlap));
249  return;
250  }
251 
252  case TEK_Scalar: {
253  RValue RV = RValue::get(EmitScalarExpr(E, /*Ignore*/ false));
254  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Location, E->getType());
255  EmitStoreThroughLValue(RV, LV);
256  return;
257  }
258  }
259  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
260 }
261 
262 static void
263 pushTemporaryCleanup(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M,
264  const Expr *E, Address ReferenceTemporary) {
265  // Objective-C++ ARC:
266  // If we are binding a reference to a temporary that has ownership, we
267  // need to perform retain/release operations on the temporary.
268  //
269  // FIXME: This should be looking at E, not M.
270  if (auto Lifetime = M->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
271  switch (Lifetime) {
272  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
273  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
274  // Carry on to normal cleanup handling.
275  break;
276 
277  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
278  // Nothing to do; cleaned up by an autorelease pool.
279  return;
280 
281  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
282  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
283  switch (StorageDuration Duration = M->getStorageDuration()) {
284  case SD_Static:
285  // Note: we intentionally do not register a cleanup to release
286  // the object on program termination.
287  return;
288 
289  case SD_Thread:
290  // FIXME: We should probably register a cleanup in this case.
291  return;
292 
293  case SD_Automatic:
294  case SD_FullExpression:
295  CodeGenFunction::Destroyer *Destroy;
296  CleanupKind CleanupKind;
297  if (Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
298  const ValueDecl *VD = M->getExtendingDecl();
299  bool Precise =
300  VD && isa<VarDecl>(VD) && VD->hasAttr<ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr>();
301  CleanupKind = CGF.getARCCleanupKind();
302  Destroy = Precise ? &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongPrecise
303  : &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongImprecise;
304  } else {
305  // __weak objects always get EH cleanups; otherwise, exceptions
306  // could cause really nasty crashes instead of mere leaks.
307  CleanupKind = NormalAndEHCleanup;
308  Destroy = &CodeGenFunction::destroyARCWeak;
309  }
310  if (Duration == SD_FullExpression)
311  CGF.pushDestroy(CleanupKind, ReferenceTemporary,
312  M->getType(), *Destroy,
313  CleanupKind & EHCleanup);
314  else
315  CGF.pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(CleanupKind, ReferenceTemporary,
316  M->getType(),
317  *Destroy, CleanupKind & EHCleanup);
318  return;
319 
320  case SD_Dynamic:
321  llvm_unreachable("temporary cannot have dynamic storage duration");
322  }
323  llvm_unreachable("unknown storage duration");
324  }
325  }
326 
327  CXXDestructorDecl *ReferenceTemporaryDtor = nullptr;
328  if (const RecordType *RT =
329  E->getType()->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
330  // Get the destructor for the reference temporary.
331  auto *ClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
332  if (!ClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor())
333  ReferenceTemporaryDtor = ClassDecl->getDestructor();
334  }
335 
336  if (!ReferenceTemporaryDtor)
337  return;
338 
339  // Call the destructor for the temporary.
340  switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
341  case SD_Static:
342  case SD_Thread: {
343  llvm::FunctionCallee CleanupFn;
344  llvm::Constant *CleanupArg;
345  if (E->getType()->isArrayType()) {
346  CleanupFn = CodeGenFunction(CGF.CGM).generateDestroyHelper(
347  ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
348  CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject, CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions,
349  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()));
350  CleanupArg = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.Int8PtrTy);
351  } else {
352  CleanupFn = CGF.CGM.getAddrAndTypeOfCXXStructor(
353  GlobalDecl(ReferenceTemporaryDtor, Dtor_Complete));
354  CleanupArg = cast<llvm::Constant>(ReferenceTemporary.getPointer());
355  }
356  CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().registerGlobalDtor(
357  CGF, *cast<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()), CleanupFn, CleanupArg);
358  break;
359  }
360 
361  case SD_FullExpression:
362  CGF.pushDestroy(NormalAndEHCleanup, ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
363  CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject,
364  CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions);
365  break;
366 
367  case SD_Automatic:
368  CGF.pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(NormalAndEHCleanup,
369  ReferenceTemporary, E->getType(),
370  CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject,
371  CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions);
372  break;
373 
374  case SD_Dynamic:
375  llvm_unreachable("temporary cannot have dynamic storage duration");
376  }
377 }
378 
379 static Address createReferenceTemporary(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
380  const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M,
381  const Expr *Inner,
382  Address *Alloca = nullptr) {
383  auto &TCG = CGF.getTargetHooks();
384  switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
385  case SD_FullExpression:
386  case SD_Automatic: {
387  // If we have a constant temporary array or record try to promote it into a
388  // constant global under the same rules a normal constant would've been
389  // promoted. This is easier on the optimizer and generally emits fewer
390  // instructions.
391  QualType Ty = Inner->getType();
392  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().MergeAllConstants &&
393  (Ty->isArrayType() || Ty->isRecordType()) &&
394  CGF.CGM.isTypeConstant(Ty, true))
395  if (auto Init = ConstantEmitter(CGF).tryEmitAbstract(Inner, Ty)) {
396  auto AS = CGF.CGM.GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace();
397  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
398  CGF.CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(), /*isConstant=*/true,
399  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Init, ".ref.tmp", nullptr,
400  llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal,
401  CGF.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(AS));
402  CharUnits alignment = CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
403  GV->setAlignment(alignment.getAsAlign());
404  llvm::Constant *C = GV;
405  if (AS != LangAS::Default)
406  C = TCG.performAddrSpaceCast(
407  CGF.CGM, GV, AS, LangAS::Default,
408  GV->getValueType()->getPointerTo(
409  CGF.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default)));
410  // FIXME: Should we put the new global into a COMDAT?
411  return Address(C, GV->getValueType(), alignment);
412  }
413  return CGF.CreateMemTemp(Ty, "ref.tmp", Alloca);
414  }
415  case SD_Thread:
416  case SD_Static:
417  return CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalTemporary(M, Inner);
418 
419  case SD_Dynamic:
420  llvm_unreachable("temporary can't have dynamic storage duration");
421  }
422  llvm_unreachable("unknown storage duration");
423 }

425 /// Helper method to check if the underlying ABI is AAPCS
426 static bool isAAPCS(const TargetInfo &TargetInfo) {
427  return TargetInfo.getABI().startswith("aapcs");
428 }
429 
430 LValue CodeGenFunction::
431 EmitMaterializeTemporaryExpr(const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M) {
432  const Expr *E = M->getSubExpr();
433 
434  assert((!M->getExtendingDecl() || !isa<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl()) ||
435  !cast<VarDecl>(M->getExtendingDecl())->isARCPseudoStrong()) &&
436  "Reference should never be pseudo-strong!");
437 
438  // FIXME: ideally this would use EmitAnyExprToMem, however, we cannot do so
439  // as that will cause the lifetime adjustment to be lost for ARC
440  auto ownership = M->getType().getObjCLifetime();
441  if (ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_None &&
442  ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone) {
443  Address Object = createReferenceTemporary(*this, M, E);
444  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Object.getPointer())) {
445  llvm::Type *Ty = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType());
446  Object = Address(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
447  Var, Ty->getPointerTo(Object.getAddressSpace())),
448  Ty, Object.getAlignment());
449 
450  // createReferenceTemporary will promote the temporary to a global with a
451  // constant initializer if it can. It can only do this to a value of
452  // ARC-manageable type if the value is global and therefore "immune" to
453  // ref-counting operations. Therefore we have no need to emit either a
454  // dynamic initialization or a cleanup and we can just return the address
455  // of the temporary.
456  if (Var->hasInitializer())
457  return MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
458 
459  Var->setInitializer(CGM.EmitNullConstant(E->getType()));
460  }
461  LValue RefTempDst = MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(),
462  AlignmentSource::Decl);
463 
464  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
465  default: llvm_unreachable("expected scalar or aggregate expression");
466  case TEK_Scalar:
467  EmitScalarInit(E, M->getExtendingDecl(), RefTempDst, false);
468  break;
469  case TEK_Aggregate: {
470  EmitAggExpr(E, AggValueSlot::forAddr(Object,
471  E->getType().getQualifiers(),
472  AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
473  AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
474  AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
475  AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap));
476  break;
477  }
478  }
479 
480  pushTemporaryCleanup(*this, M, E, Object);
481  return RefTempDst;
482  }
483 
484  SmallVector<const Expr *, 2> CommaLHSs;
485  SmallVector<SubobjectAdjustment, 2> Adjustments;
486  E = E->skipRValueSubobjectAdjustments(CommaLHSs, Adjustments);
487 
488  for (const auto &Ignored : CommaLHSs)
489  EmitIgnoredExpr(Ignored);
490 
491  if (const auto *opaque = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E)) {
492  if (opaque->getType()->isRecordType()) {
493  assert(Adjustments.empty());
494  return EmitOpaqueValueLValue(opaque);
495  }
496  }
497 
498  // Create and initialize the reference temporary.
499  Address Alloca = Address::invalid();
500  Address Object = createReferenceTemporary(*this, M, E, &Alloca);
501  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
502  Object.getPointer()->stripPointerCasts())) {
503  llvm::Type *TemporaryType = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType());
504  Object = Address(llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
505  cast<llvm::Constant>(Object.getPointer()),
506  TemporaryType->getPointerTo()),
507  TemporaryType,
508  Object.getAlignment());
509  // If the temporary is a global and has a constant initializer or is a
510  // constant temporary that we promoted to a global, we may have already
511  // initialized it.
512  if (!Var->hasInitializer()) {
513  Var->setInitializer(CGM.EmitNullConstant(E->getType()));
514  EmitAnyExprToMem(E, Object, Qualifiers(), /*IsInit*/true);
515  }
516  } else {
517  switch (M->getStorageDuration()) {
518  case SD_Automatic:
519  if (auto *Size = EmitLifetimeStart(
520  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Alloca.getElementType()),
521  Alloca.getPointer())) {
522  pushCleanupAfterFullExpr<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker,
523  Alloca, Size);
524  }
525  break;
526 
527  case SD_FullExpression: {
528  if (!ShouldEmitLifetimeMarkers)
529  break;
530 
531  // Avoid creating a conditional cleanup just to hold an llvm.lifetime.end
532  // marker. Instead, start the lifetime of a conditional temporary earlier
533  // so that it's unconditional. Don't do this with sanitizers which need
534  // more precise lifetime marks.
535  ConditionalEvaluation *OldConditional = nullptr;
536  CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint OldIP;
537  if (isInConditionalBranch() && !E->getType().isDestructedType() &&
538  !SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::HWAddress) &&
539  !SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Memory) &&
540  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeAddressUseAfterScope) {
541  OldConditional = OutermostConditional;
542  OutermostConditional = nullptr;
543 
544  OldIP = Builder.saveIP();
545  llvm::BasicBlock *Block = OldConditional->getStartingBlock();
546  Builder.restoreIP(CGBuilderTy::InsertPoint(
547  Block, llvm::BasicBlock::iterator(Block->back())));
548  }
549 
550  if (auto *Size = EmitLifetimeStart(
551  CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Alloca.getElementType()),
552  Alloca.getPointer())) {
553  pushFullExprCleanup<CallLifetimeEnd>(NormalEHLifetimeMarker, Alloca,
554  Size);
555  }
556 
557  if (OldConditional) {
558  OutermostConditional = OldConditional;
559  Builder.restoreIP(OldIP);
560  }
561  break;
562  }
563 
564  default:
565  break;
566  }
567  EmitAnyExprToMem(E, Object, Qualifiers(), /*IsInit*/true);
568  }
569  pushTemporaryCleanup(*this, M, E, Object);
570 
571  // Perform derived-to-base casts and/or field accesses, to get from the
572  // temporary object we created (and, potentially, for which we extended
573  // the lifetime) to the subobject we're binding the reference to.
574  for (SubobjectAdjustment &Adjustment : llvm::reverse(Adjustments)) {
575  switch (Adjustment.Kind) {
576  case SubobjectAdjustment::DerivedToBaseAdjustment:
577  Object =
578  GetAddressOfBaseClass(Object, Adjustment.DerivedToBase.DerivedClass,
579  Adjustment.DerivedToBase.BasePath->path_begin(),
580  Adjustment.DerivedToBase.BasePath->path_end(),
581  /*NullCheckValue=*/ false, E->getExprLoc());
582  break;
583 
584  case SubobjectAdjustment::FieldAdjustment: {
585  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Object, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
586  LV = EmitLValueForField(LV, Adjustment.Field);
587  assert(LV.isSimple() &&
588  "materialized temporary field is not a simple lvalue");
589  Object = LV.getAddress(*this);
590  break;
591  }
592 
593  case SubobjectAdjustment::MemberPointerAdjustment: {
594  llvm::Value *Ptr = EmitScalarExpr(Adjustment.Ptr.RHS);
595  Object = EmitCXXMemberDataPointerAddress(E, Object, Ptr,
596  Adjustment.Ptr.MPT);
597  break;
598  }
599  }
600  }
601 
602  return MakeAddrLValue(Object, M->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
603 }
604 
605 RValue
606 CodeGenFunction::EmitReferenceBindingToExpr(const Expr *E) {
607  // Emit the expression as an lvalue.
608  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E);
609  assert(LV.isSimple());
610  llvm::Value *Value = LV.getPointer(*this);
611 
612  if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck() && !E->getType()->isFunctionType()) {
613  // C++11 [dcl.ref]p5 (as amended by core issue 453):
614  // If a glvalue to which a reference is directly bound designates neither
615  // an existing object or function of an appropriate type nor a region of
616  // storage of suitable size and alignment to contain an object of the
617  // reference's type, the behavior is undefined.
618  QualType Ty = E->getType();
619  EmitTypeCheck(TCK_ReferenceBinding, E->getExprLoc(), Value, Ty);
620  }
621 
622  return RValue::get(Value);
623 }
