626 /// getAccessedFieldNo - Given an encoded value and a result number, return the
627 /// input field number being accessed.
628 unsigned CodeGenFunction::getAccessedFieldNo(unsigned Idx,
629  const llvm::Constant *Elts) {
630  return cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Elts->getAggregateElement(Idx))
631  ->getZExtValue();
632 }
633 
634 /// Emit the hash_16_bytes function from include/llvm/ADT/Hashing.h.
635 static llvm::Value *emitHash16Bytes(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Value *Low,
636  llvm::Value *High) {
637  llvm::Value *KMul = Builder.getInt64(0x9ddfea08eb382d69ULL);
638  llvm::Value *K47 = Builder.getInt64(47);
639  llvm::Value *A0 = Builder.CreateMul(Builder.CreateXor(Low, High), KMul);
640  llvm::Value *A1 = Builder.CreateXor(Builder.CreateLShr(A0, K47), A0);
641  llvm::Value *B0 = Builder.CreateMul(Builder.CreateXor(High, A1), KMul);
642  llvm::Value *B1 = Builder.CreateXor(Builder.CreateLShr(B0, K47), B0);
643  return Builder.CreateMul(B1, KMul);
644 }
645 
646 bool CodeGenFunction::isNullPointerAllowed(TypeCheckKind TCK) {
647  return TCK == TCK_DowncastPointer || TCK == TCK_Upcast ||
648  TCK == TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase || TCK == TCK_DynamicOperation;
649 }
650 
651 bool CodeGenFunction::isVptrCheckRequired(TypeCheckKind TCK, QualType Ty) {
652  CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
653  return (RD && RD->hasDefinition() && RD->isDynamicClass()) &&
654  (TCK == TCK_MemberAccess || TCK == TCK_MemberCall ||
655  TCK == TCK_DowncastPointer || TCK == TCK_DowncastReference ||
656  TCK == TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase || TCK == TCK_DynamicOperation);
657 }
658 
659 bool CodeGenFunction::sanitizePerformTypeCheck() const {
660  return SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Null) ||
661  SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment) ||
662  SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) ||
663  SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr);
664 }
665 
666 void CodeGenFunction::EmitTypeCheck(TypeCheckKind TCK, SourceLocation Loc,
667  llvm::Value *Ptr, QualType Ty,
668  CharUnits Alignment,
669  SanitizerSet SkippedChecks,
670  llvm::Value *ArraySize) {
671  if (!sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
672  return;
673 
674  // Don't check pointers outside the default address space. The null check
675  // isn't correct, the object-size check isn't supported by LLVM, and we can't
676  // communicate the addresses to the runtime handler for the vptr check.
677  if (Ptr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())
678  return;
679 
680  // Don't check pointers to volatile data. The behavior here is implementation-
681  // defined.
682  if (Ty.isVolatileQualified())
683  return;
684 
685  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
686 
687  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 3> Checks;
688  llvm::BasicBlock *Done = nullptr;
689 
690  // Quickly determine whether we have a pointer to an alloca. It's possible
691  // to skip null checks, and some alignment checks, for these pointers. This
692  // can reduce compile-time significantly.
693  auto PtrToAlloca = dyn_cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(Ptr->stripPointerCasts());
694 
695  llvm::Value *True = llvm::ConstantInt::getTrue(getLLVMContext());
696  llvm::Value *IsNonNull = nullptr;
697  bool IsGuaranteedNonNull =
698  SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Null) || PtrToAlloca;
699  bool AllowNullPointers = isNullPointerAllowed(TCK);
700  if ((SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Null) || AllowNullPointers) &&
701  !IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
702  // The glvalue must not be an empty glvalue.
703  IsNonNull = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
704 
705  // The IR builder can constant-fold the null check if the pointer points to
706  // a constant.
707  IsGuaranteedNonNull = IsNonNull == True;
708 
709  // Skip the null check if the pointer is known to be non-null.
710  if (!IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
711  if (AllowNullPointers) {
712  // When performing pointer casts, it's OK if the value is null.
713  // Skip the remaining checks in that case.
714  Done = createBasicBlock("null");
715  llvm::BasicBlock *Rest = createBasicBlock("not.null");
716  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNonNull, Rest, Done);
717  EmitBlock(Rest);
718  } else {
719  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(IsNonNull, SanitizerKind::Null));
720  }
721  }
722  }
723 
724  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) &&
725  !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::ObjectSize) &&
726  !Ty->isIncompleteType()) {
727  uint64_t TySize = CGM.getMinimumObjectSize(Ty).getQuantity();
728  llvm::Value *Size = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, TySize);
729  if (ArraySize)
730  Size = Builder.CreateMul(Size, ArraySize);
731 
732  // Degenerate case: new X[0] does not need an objectsize check.
733  llvm::Constant *ConstantSize = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(Size);
734  if (!ConstantSize || !ConstantSize->isNullValue()) {
735  // The glvalue must refer to a large enough storage region.
736  // FIXME: If Address Sanitizer is enabled, insert dynamic instrumentation
737  // to check this.
738  // FIXME: Get object address space
739  llvm::Type *Tys[2] = { IntPtrTy, Int8PtrTy };
740  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::objectsize, Tys);
741  llvm::Value *Min = Builder.getFalse();
742  llvm::Value *NullIsUnknown = Builder.getFalse();
743  llvm::Value *Dynamic = Builder.getFalse();
744  llvm::Value *CastAddr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, Int8PtrTy);
745  llvm::Value *LargeEnough = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(
746  Builder.CreateCall(F, {CastAddr, Min, NullIsUnknown, Dynamic}), Size);
747  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(LargeEnough, SanitizerKind::ObjectSize));
748  }
749  }
750 
751  uint64_t AlignVal = 0;
752  llvm::Value *PtrAsInt = nullptr;
753 
754  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment) &&
755  !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Alignment)) {
756  AlignVal = Alignment.getQuantity();
757  if (!Ty->isIncompleteType() && !AlignVal)
758  AlignVal = CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(Ty, nullptr, nullptr,
759  /*ForPointeeType=*/true)
760  .getQuantity();
761 
762  // The glvalue must be suitably aligned.
763  if (AlignVal > 1 &&
764  (!PtrToAlloca || PtrToAlloca->getAlignment() < AlignVal)) {
765  PtrAsInt = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Ptr, IntPtrTy);
766  llvm::Value *Align = Builder.CreateAnd(
767  PtrAsInt, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, AlignVal - 1));
768  llvm::Value *Aligned =
769  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Align, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, 0));
770  if (Aligned != True)
771  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(Aligned, SanitizerKind::Alignment));
772  }
773  }
774 
775  if (Checks.size() > 0) {
776  // Make sure we're not losing information. Alignment needs to be a power of
777  // 2
778  assert(!AlignVal || (uint64_t)1 << llvm::Log2_64(AlignVal) == AlignVal);
779  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
780  EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty),
781  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, AlignVal ? llvm::Log2_64(AlignVal) : 1),
782  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, TCK)};
783  EmitCheck(Checks, SanitizerHandler::TypeMismatch, StaticData,
784  PtrAsInt ? PtrAsInt : Ptr);
785  }
786 
787  // If possible, check that the vptr indicates that there is a subobject of
788  // type Ty at offset zero within this object.
789  //
790  // C++11 [basic.life]p5,6:
791  // [For storage which does not refer to an object within its lifetime]
792  // The program has undefined behavior if:
793  // -- the [pointer or glvalue] is used to access a non-static data member
794  // or call a non-static member function
795  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr) &&
796  !SkippedChecks.has(SanitizerKind::Vptr) && isVptrCheckRequired(TCK, Ty)) {
797  // Ensure that the pointer is non-null before loading it. If there is no
798  // compile-time guarantee, reuse the run-time null check or emit a new one.
799  if (!IsGuaranteedNonNull) {
800  if (!IsNonNull)
801  IsNonNull = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
802  if (!Done)
803  Done = createBasicBlock("vptr.null");
804  llvm::BasicBlock *VptrNotNull = createBasicBlock("vptr.not.null");
805  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNonNull, VptrNotNull, Done);
806  EmitBlock(VptrNotNull);
807  }
808 
809  // Compute a hash of the mangled name of the type.
810  //
811  // FIXME: This is not guaranteed to be deterministic! Move to a
812  // fingerprinting mechanism once LLVM provides one. For the time
813  // being the implementation happens to be deterministic.
814  SmallString<64> MangledName;
815  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
816  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTI(Ty.getUnqualifiedType(),
817  Out);
818 
819  // Contained in NoSanitizeList based on the mangled type.
820  if (!CGM.getContext().getNoSanitizeList().containsType(SanitizerKind::Vptr,
821  Out.str())) {
822  llvm::hash_code TypeHash = hash_value(Out.str());
823 
824  // Load the vptr, and compute hash_16_bytes(TypeHash, vptr).
825  llvm::Value *Low = llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, TypeHash);
826  llvm::Type *VPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(IntPtrTy, 0);
827  Address VPtrAddr(Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, VPtrTy), IntPtrTy,
828  getPointerAlign());
829  llvm::Value *VPtrVal = Builder.CreateLoad(VPtrAddr);
830  llvm::Value *High = Builder.CreateZExt(VPtrVal, Int64Ty);
831 
832  llvm::Value *Hash = emitHash16Bytes(Builder, Low, High);
833  Hash = Builder.CreateTrunc(Hash, IntPtrTy);
834 
835  // Look the hash up in our cache.
836  const int CacheSize = 128;
837  llvm::Type *HashTable = llvm::ArrayType::get(IntPtrTy, CacheSize);
838  llvm::Value *Cache = CGM.CreateRuntimeVariable(HashTable,
839  "__ubsan_vptr_type_cache");
840  llvm::Value *Slot = Builder.CreateAnd(Hash,
841  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy,
842  CacheSize-1));
843  llvm::Value *Indices[] = { Builder.getInt32(0), Slot };
844  llvm::Value *CacheVal = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
845  IntPtrTy, Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(HashTable, Cache, Indices),
846  getPointerAlign());
847 
848  // If the hash isn't in the cache, call a runtime handler to perform the
849  // hard work of checking whether the vptr is for an object of the right
850  // type. This will either fill in the cache and return, or produce a
851  // diagnostic.
852  llvm::Value *EqualHash = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CacheVal, Hash);
853  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
854  EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
855  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty),
856  CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(Ty.getUnqualifiedType()),
857  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, TCK)
858  };
859  llvm::Value *DynamicData[] = { Ptr, Hash };
860  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(EqualHash, SanitizerKind::Vptr),
861  SanitizerHandler::DynamicTypeCacheMiss, StaticData,
862  DynamicData);
863  }
864  }
865 
866  if (Done) {
867  Builder.CreateBr(Done);
868  EmitBlock(Done);
869  }
870 }
871 
872 /// Determine whether this expression refers to a flexible array member in a
873 /// struct. We disable array bounds checks for such members.
874 static bool isFlexibleArrayMemberExpr(const Expr *E) {
875  // For compatibility with existing code, we treat arrays of length 0 or
876  // 1 as flexible array members.
877  // FIXME: This is inconsistent with the warning code in SemaChecking. Unify
878  // the two mechanisms.
879  const ArrayType *AT = E->getType()->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
880  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)) {
881  // FIXME: Sema doesn't treat [1] as a flexible array member if the bound
882  // was produced by macro expansion.
883  if (CAT->getSize().ugt(1))
884  return false;
885  } else if (!isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT))
886  return false;
887 
888  E = E->IgnoreParens();
889 
890  // A flexible array member must be the last member in the class.
891  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
892  // FIXME: If the base type of the member expr is not FD->getParent(),
893  // this should not be treated as a flexible array member access.
894  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
895  // FIXME: Sema doesn't treat a T[1] union member as a flexible array
896  // member, only a T[0] or T[] member gets that treatment.
897  if (FD->getParent()->isUnion())
898  return true;
899  RecordDecl::field_iterator FI(
900  DeclContext::decl_iterator(const_cast<FieldDecl *>(FD)));
901  return ++FI == FD->getParent()->field_end();
902  }
903  } else if (const auto *IRE = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E)) {
904  return IRE->getDecl()->getNextIvar() == nullptr;
905  }
906 
907  return false;
908 }
909 
910 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::LoadPassedObjectSize(const Expr *E,
911  QualType EltTy) {
912  ASTContext &C = getContext();
913  uint64_t EltSize = C.getTypeSizeInChars(EltTy).getQuantity();
914  if (!EltSize)
915  return nullptr;
916 
917  auto *ArrayDeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
918  if (!ArrayDeclRef)
919  return nullptr;
920 
921  auto *ParamDecl = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(ArrayDeclRef->getDecl());
922  if (!ParamDecl)
923  return nullptr;
924 
925  auto *POSAttr = ParamDecl->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>();
926  if (!POSAttr)
927  return nullptr;
928 
929  // Don't load the size if it's a lower bound.
930  int POSType = POSAttr->getType();
931  if (POSType != 0 && POSType != 1)
932  return nullptr;
933 
934  // Find the implicit size parameter.
935  auto PassedSizeIt = SizeArguments.find(ParamDecl);
936  if (PassedSizeIt == SizeArguments.end())
937  return nullptr;
938 
939  const ImplicitParamDecl *PassedSizeDecl = PassedSizeIt->second;
940  assert(LocalDeclMap.count(PassedSizeDecl) && "Passed size not loadable");
941  Address AddrOfSize = LocalDeclMap.find(PassedSizeDecl)->second;
942  llvm::Value *SizeInBytes = EmitLoadOfScalar(AddrOfSize, /*Volatile=*/false,
943  C.getSizeType(), E->getExprLoc());
944  llvm::Value *SizeOfElement =
945  llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeInBytes->getType(), EltSize);
946  return Builder.CreateUDiv(SizeInBytes, SizeOfElement);
947 }
948 
949 /// If Base is known to point to the start of an array, return the length of
950 /// that array. Return 0 if the length cannot be determined.
951 static llvm::Value *getArrayIndexingBound(
952  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *Base, QualType &IndexedType) {
953  // For the vector indexing extension, the bound is the number of elements.
954  if (const VectorType *VT = Base->getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
955  IndexedType = Base->getType();
956  return CGF.Builder.getInt32(VT->getNumElements());
957  }
958 
959  Base = Base->IgnoreParens();
960 
961  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Base)) {
962  if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_ArrayToPointerDecay &&
963  !isFlexibleArrayMemberExpr(CE->getSubExpr())) {
964  IndexedType = CE->getSubExpr()->getType();
965  const ArrayType *AT = IndexedType->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
966  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
967  return CGF.Builder.getInt(CAT->getSize());
968  else if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(AT))
969  return CGF.getVLASize(VAT).NumElts;
970  // Ignore pass_object_size here. It's not applicable on decayed pointers.
971  }
972  }
973 
974  QualType EltTy{Base->getType()->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(), 0};
975  if (llvm::Value *POS = CGF.LoadPassedObjectSize(Base, EltTy)) {
976  IndexedType = Base->getType();
977  return POS;
978  }
979 
980  return nullptr;
981 }
982 
983 void CodeGenFunction::EmitBoundsCheck(const Expr *E, const Expr *Base,
984  llvm::Value *Index, QualType IndexType,
985  bool Accessed) {
986  assert(SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds) &&
987  "should not be called unless adding bounds checks");
988  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
989 
990  QualType IndexedType;
991  llvm::Value *Bound = getArrayIndexingBound(*this, Base, IndexedType);
992  if (!Bound)
993  return;
994 
995  bool IndexSigned = IndexType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
996  llvm::Value *IndexVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(Index, SizeTy, IndexSigned);
997  llvm::Value *BoundVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(Bound, SizeTy, false);
998 
999  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
1000  EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getExprLoc()),
1001  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(IndexedType),
1002  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(IndexType)
1003  };
1004  llvm::Value *Check = Accessed ? Builder.CreateICmpULT(IndexVal, BoundVal)
1005  : Builder.CreateICmpULE(IndexVal, BoundVal);
1006  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Check, SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds),
1007  SanitizerHandler::OutOfBounds, StaticData, Index);
1008 }
1009 
1010 
1011 CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy CodeGenFunction::
1012 EmitComplexPrePostIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E, LValue LV,
1013  bool isInc, bool isPre) {
1014  ComplexPairTy InVal = EmitLoadOfComplex(LV, E->getExprLoc());
1015 
1016  llvm::Value *NextVal;
1017  if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(InVal.first->getType())) {
1018  uint64_t AmountVal = isInc ? 1 : -1;
1019  NextVal = llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal.first->getType(), AmountVal, true);
1020 
1021  // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
1022  NextVal = Builder.CreateAdd(InVal.first, NextVal, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
1023  } else {
1024  QualType ElemTy = E->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
1025  llvm::APFloat FVal(getContext().getFloatTypeSemantics(ElemTy), 1);
1026  if (!isInc)
1027  FVal.changeSign();
1028  NextVal = llvm::ConstantFP::get(getLLVMContext(), FVal);
1029 
1030  // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
1031  NextVal = Builder.CreateFAdd(InVal.first, NextVal, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
1032  }
1033 
1034  ComplexPairTy IncVal(NextVal, InVal.second);
1035 
1036  // Store the updated result through the lvalue.
1037  EmitStoreOfComplex(IncVal, LV, /*init*/ false);
1038  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP)
1039  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(*this,
1040  E->getSubExpr());
1041 
1042  // If this is a postinc, return the value read from memory, otherwise use the
1043  // updated value.
1044  return isPre ? IncVal : InVal;
1045 }
1046 
1047 void CodeGenModule::EmitExplicitCastExprType(const ExplicitCastExpr *E,
1048  CodeGenFunction *CGF) {
1049  // Bind VLAs in the cast type.
1050  if (CGF && E->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
1051  CGF->EmitVariablyModifiedType(E->getType());
1052 
1053  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
1054  DI->EmitExplicitCastType(E->getType());
1055 }
1056 
1057 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1058 // LValue Expression Emission
1059 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1060 
1061 /// EmitPointerWithAlignment - Given an expression of pointer type, try to
1062 /// derive a more accurate bound on the alignment of the pointer.
1063 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitPointerWithAlignment(const Expr *E,
1064  LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
1065  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
1066  // We allow this with ObjC object pointers because of fragile ABIs.
1067  assert(E->getType()->isPointerType() ||
1068  E->getType()->isObjCObjectPointerType());
1069  E = E->IgnoreParens();
1070 
1071  // Casts:
1072  if (const CastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(E)) {
1073  if (const auto *ECE = dyn_cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE))
1074  CGM.EmitExplicitCastExprType(ECE, this);
1075 
1076  switch (CE->getCastKind()) {
1077  // Non-converting casts (but not C's implicit conversion from void*).
1078  case CK_BitCast:
1079  case CK_NoOp:
1080  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion:
1081  if (auto PtrTy = CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
1082  if (PtrTy->getPointeeType()->isVoidType())
1083  break;
1084 
1085  LValueBaseInfo InnerBaseInfo;
1086  TBAAAccessInfo InnerTBAAInfo;
1087  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(CE->getSubExpr(),
1088  &InnerBaseInfo,
1089  &InnerTBAAInfo);
1090  if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = InnerBaseInfo;
1091  if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = InnerTBAAInfo;
1092 
1093  if (isa<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
1094  LValueBaseInfo TargetTypeBaseInfo;
1095  TBAAAccessInfo TargetTypeTBAAInfo;
1096  CharUnits Align = CGM.getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(
1097  E->getType(), &TargetTypeBaseInfo, &TargetTypeTBAAInfo);
1098  if (TBAAInfo)
1099  *TBAAInfo = CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForCast(*TBAAInfo,
1100  TargetTypeTBAAInfo);
1101  // If the source l-value is opaque, honor the alignment of the
1102  // casted-to type.
1103  if (InnerBaseInfo.getAlignmentSource() != AlignmentSource::Decl) {
1104  if (BaseInfo)
1105  BaseInfo->mergeForCast(TargetTypeBaseInfo);
1106  Addr = Address(Addr.getPointer(), Addr.getElementType(), Align);
1107  }
1108  }
1109 
1110  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast) &&
1111  CE->getCastKind() == CK_BitCast) {
1112  if (auto PT = E->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
1113  EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(PT->getPointeeType(), Addr,
1114  /*MayBeNull=*/true,
1115  CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
1116  CE->getBeginLoc());
1117  }
1118 
1119  llvm::Type *ElemTy = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType()->getPointeeType());
1120  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ElemTy);
1121  if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_AddressSpaceConversion)
1122  Addr = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(Addr, ConvertType(E->getType()));
1123  return Addr;
1124  }
1125  break;
1126 
1127  // Array-to-pointer decay.
1128  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
1129  return EmitArrayToPointerDecay(CE->getSubExpr(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
1130 
1131  // Derived-to-base conversions.
1132  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
1133  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
1134  // TODO: Support accesses to members of base classes in TBAA. For now, we
1135  // conservatively pretend that the complete object is of the base class
1136  // type.
1137  if (TBAAInfo)
1138  *TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(E->getType());
1139  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(CE->getSubExpr(), BaseInfo);
1140  auto Derived = CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
1141  return GetAddressOfBaseClass(Addr, Derived,
1142  CE->path_begin(), CE->path_end(),
1143  ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(CE),
1144  CE->getExprLoc());
1145  }
1146 
1147  // TODO: Is there any reason to treat base-to-derived conversions
1148  // specially?
1149  default:
1150  break;
1151  }
1152  }
1153 
1154  // Unary &.
1155  if (const UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
1156  if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf) {
1157  LValue LV = EmitLValue(UO->getSubExpr());
1158  if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = LV.getBaseInfo();
1159  if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = LV.getTBAAInfo();
1160  return LV.getAddress(*this);
1161  }
1162  }
1163 
1164  // TODO: conditional operators, comma.
1165 
1166  // Otherwise, use the alignment of the type.
1167  CharUnits Align =
1168  CGM.getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(E->getType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
1169  llvm::Type *ElemTy = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType()->getPointeeType());
1170  return Address(EmitScalarExpr(E), ElemTy, Align);
1171 }
1172 
1173 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitNonNullRValueCheck(RValue RV, QualType T) {
1174  llvm::Value *V = RV.getScalarVal();
1175  if (auto MPT = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
1176  return CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(*this, V, MPT);
1177  return Builder.CreateICmpNE(V, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(V->getType()));
1178 }
1179 
1180 RValue CodeGenFunction::GetUndefRValue(QualType Ty) {
1181  if (Ty->isVoidType())
1182  return RValue::get(nullptr);
1183 
1184  switch (getEvaluationKind(Ty)) {
1185  case TEK_Complex: {
1186  llvm::Type *EltTy =
1187  ConvertType(Ty->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType());
1188  llvm::Value *U = llvm::UndefValue::get(EltTy);
1189  return RValue::getComplex(std::make_pair(U, U));
1190  }
1191 
1192  // If this is a use of an undefined aggregate type, the aggregate must have an
1193  // identifiable address. Just because the contents of the value are undefined
1194  // doesn't mean that the address can't be taken and compared.
1195  case TEK_Aggregate: {
1196  Address DestPtr = CreateMemTemp(Ty, "undef.agg.tmp");
1197  return RValue::getAggregate(DestPtr);
1198  }
1199 
1200  case TEK_Scalar:
1201  return RValue::get(llvm::UndefValue::get(ConvertType(Ty)));
1202  }
1203  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
1204 }
1205 
1206 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitUnsupportedRValue(const Expr *E,
1207  const char *Name) {
1208  ErrorUnsupported(E, Name);
1209  return GetUndefRValue(E->getType());
1210 }
1211 
1212 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitUnsupportedLValue(const Expr *E,
1213  const char *Name) {
1214  ErrorUnsupported(E, Name);
1215  llvm::Type *ElTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
1216  llvm::Type *Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(ElTy);
1217  return MakeAddrLValue(
1218  Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(Ty), ElTy, CharUnits::One()), E->getType());
1219 }
1220 
1221 bool CodeGenFunction::IsWrappedCXXThis(const Expr *Obj) {
1222  const Expr *Base = Obj;
1223  while (!isa<CXXThisExpr>(Base)) {
1224  // The result of a dynamic_cast can be null.
1225  if (isa<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(Base))
1226  return false;
1227 
1228  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Base)) {
1229  Base = CE->getSubExpr();
1230  } else if (const auto *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(Base)) {
1231  Base = PE->getSubExpr();
1232  } else if (const auto *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Base)) {
1233  if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_Extension)
1234  Base = UO->getSubExpr();
1235  else
1236  return false;
1237  } else {
1238  return false;
1239  }
1240  }
1241  return true;
1242 }
1243 
1244 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckedLValue(const Expr *E, TypeCheckKind TCK) {
1245  LValue LV;
1246  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds) && isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E))
1247  LV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E), /*Accessed*/true);
1248  else
1249  LV = EmitLValue(E);
1250  if (!isa<DeclRefExpr>(E) && !LV.isBitField() && LV.isSimple()) {
1251  SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
1252  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
1253  bool IsBaseCXXThis = IsWrappedCXXThis(ME->getBase());
1254  if (IsBaseCXXThis)
1255  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Alignment, true);
1256  if (IsBaseCXXThis || isa<DeclRefExpr>(ME->getBase()))
1257  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, true);
1258  }
1259  EmitTypeCheck(TCK, E->getExprLoc(), LV.getPointer(*this), E->getType(),
1260  LV.getAlignment(), SkippedChecks);
1261  }
1262  return LV;
1263 }
1264 
1265 /// EmitLValue - Emit code to compute a designator that specifies the location
1266 /// of the expression.
1267 ///
1268 /// This can return one of two things: a simple address or a bitfield reference.
1269 /// In either case, the LLVM Value* in the LValue structure is guaranteed to be
1270 /// an LLVM pointer type.
1271 ///
1272 /// If this returns a bitfield reference, nothing about the pointee type of the
1273 /// LLVM value is known: For example, it may not be a pointer to an integer.
1274 ///
1275 /// If this returns a normal address, and if the lvalue's C type is fixed size,
1276 /// this method guarantees that the returned pointer type will point to an LLVM
1277 /// type of the same size of the lvalue's type. If the lvalue has a variable
1278 /// length type, this is not possible.
1279 ///
1280 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValue(const Expr *E) {
1281  ApplyDebugLocation DL(*this, E);
1282  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
1283  default: return EmitUnsupportedLValue(E, "l-value expression");
1284 
1285  case Expr::ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
1286  llvm_unreachable("cannot emit a property reference directly");
1287 
1288  case Expr::ObjCSelectorExprClass:
1289  return EmitObjCSelectorLValue(cast<ObjCSelectorExpr>(E));
1290  case Expr::ObjCIsaExprClass:
1291  return EmitObjCIsaExpr(cast<ObjCIsaExpr>(E));
1292  case Expr::BinaryOperatorClass:
1293  return EmitBinaryOperatorLValue(cast<BinaryOperator>(E));
1294  case Expr::CompoundAssignOperatorClass: {
1295  QualType Ty = E->getType();
1296  if (const AtomicType *AT = Ty->getAs<AtomicType>())
1297  Ty = AT->getValueType();
1298  if (!Ty->isAnyComplexType())
1299  return EmitCompoundAssignmentLValue(cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(E));
1300  return EmitComplexCompoundAssignmentLValue(cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(E));
1301  }
1302  case Expr::CallExprClass:
1303  case Expr::CXXMemberCallExprClass:
1304  case Expr::CXXOperatorCallExprClass:
1305  case Expr::UserDefinedLiteralClass:
1306  return EmitCallExprLValue(cast<CallExpr>(E));
1307  case Expr::CXXRewrittenBinaryOperatorClass:
1308  return EmitLValue(cast<CXXRewrittenBinaryOperator>(E)->getSemanticForm());
1309  case Expr::VAArgExprClass:
1310  return EmitVAArgExprLValue(cast<VAArgExpr>(E));
1311  case Expr::DeclRefExprClass:
1312  return EmitDeclRefLValue(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E));
1313  case Expr::ConstantExprClass: {
1314  const ConstantExpr *CE = cast<ConstantExpr>(E);
1315  if (llvm::Value *Result = ConstantEmitter(*this).tryEmitConstantExpr(CE)) {
1316  QualType RetType = cast<CallExpr>(CE->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImplicit())
1317  ->getCallReturnType(getContext())
1318  ->getPointeeType();
1319  return MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(Result, RetType);
1320  }
1321  return EmitLValue(cast<ConstantExpr>(E)->getSubExpr());
1322  }
1323  case Expr::ParenExprClass:
1324  return EmitLValue(cast<ParenExpr>(E)->getSubExpr());
1325  case Expr::GenericSelectionExprClass:
1326  return EmitLValue(cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)->getResultExpr());
1327  case Expr::PredefinedExprClass:
1328  return EmitPredefinedLValue(cast<PredefinedExpr>(E));
1329  case Expr::StringLiteralClass:
1330  return EmitStringLiteralLValue(cast<StringLiteral>(E));
1331  case Expr::ObjCEncodeExprClass:
1332  return EmitObjCEncodeExprLValue(cast<ObjCEncodeExpr>(E));
1333  case Expr::PseudoObjectExprClass:
1334  return EmitPseudoObjectLValue(cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(E));
1335  case Expr::InitListExprClass:
1336  return EmitInitListLValue(cast<InitListExpr>(E));
1337  case Expr::CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass:
1338  case Expr::CXXConstructExprClass:
1339  return EmitCXXConstructLValue(cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E));
1340  case Expr::CXXBindTemporaryExprClass:
1341  return EmitCXXBindTemporaryLValue(cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E));
1342  case Expr::CXXUuidofExprClass:
1343  return EmitCXXUuidofLValue(cast<CXXUuidofExpr>(E));
1344  case Expr::LambdaExprClass:
1345  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
1346 
1347  case Expr::ExprWithCleanupsClass: {
1348  const auto *cleanups = cast<ExprWithCleanups>(E);
1349  RunCleanupsScope Scope(*this);
1350  LValue LV = EmitLValue(cleanups->getSubExpr());
1351  if (LV.isSimple()) {
1352  // Defend against branches out of gnu statement expressions surrounded by
1353  // cleanups.
1354  Address Addr = LV.getAddress(*this);
1355  llvm::Value *V = Addr.getPointer();
1356  Scope.ForceCleanup({&V});
1357  return LValue::MakeAddr(Addr.withPointer(V), LV.getType(), getContext(),
1358  LV.getBaseInfo(), LV.getTBAAInfo());
1359  }
1360  // FIXME: Is it possible to create an ExprWithCleanups that produces a
1361  // bitfield lvalue or some other non-simple lvalue?
1362  return LV;
1363  }
1364 
1365  case Expr::CXXDefaultArgExprClass: {
1366  auto *DAE = cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E);
1367  CXXDefaultArgExprScope Scope(*this, DAE);
1368  return EmitLValue(DAE->getExpr());
1369  }
1370  case Expr::CXXDefaultInitExprClass: {
1371  auto *DIE = cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(E);
1372  CXXDefaultInitExprScope Scope(*this, DIE);
1373  return EmitLValue(DIE->getExpr());
1374  }
1375  case Expr::CXXTypeidExprClass:
1376  return EmitCXXTypeidLValue(cast<CXXTypeidExpr>(E));
1377 
1378  case Expr::ObjCMessageExprClass:
1379  return EmitObjCMessageExprLValue(cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E));
1380  case Expr::ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
1381  return EmitObjCIvarRefLValue(cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E));
1382  case Expr::StmtExprClass:
1383  return EmitStmtExprLValue(cast<StmtExpr>(E));
1384  case Expr::UnaryOperatorClass:
1385  return EmitUnaryOpLValue(cast<UnaryOperator>(E));
1386  case Expr::ArraySubscriptExprClass:
1387  return EmitArraySubscriptExpr(cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E));
1388  case Expr::MatrixSubscriptExprClass:
1389  return EmitMatrixSubscriptExpr(cast<MatrixSubscriptExpr>(E));
1390  case Expr::OMPArraySectionExprClass:
1391  return EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(E));
1392  case Expr::ExtVectorElementExprClass:
1393  return EmitExtVectorElementExpr(cast<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E));
1394  case Expr::MemberExprClass:
1395  return EmitMemberExpr(cast<MemberExpr>(E));
1396  case Expr::CompoundLiteralExprClass:
1397  return EmitCompoundLiteralLValue(cast<CompoundLiteralExpr>(E));
1398  case Expr::ConditionalOperatorClass:
1399  return EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(cast<ConditionalOperator>(E));
1400  case Expr::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass:
1401  return EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(cast<BinaryConditionalOperator>(E));
1402  case Expr::ChooseExprClass:
1403  return EmitLValue(cast<ChooseExpr>(E)->getChosenSubExpr());
1404  case Expr::OpaqueValueExprClass:
1405  return EmitOpaqueValueLValue(cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E));
1406  case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass:
1407  return EmitLValue(cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)->getReplacement());
1408  case Expr::ImplicitCastExprClass:
1409  case Expr::CStyleCastExprClass:
1410  case Expr::CXXFunctionalCastExprClass:
1411  case Expr::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
1412  case Expr::CXXDynamicCastExprClass:
1413  case Expr::CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
1414  case Expr::CXXConstCastExprClass:
1415  case Expr::CXXAddrspaceCastExprClass:
1416  case Expr::ObjCBridgedCastExprClass:
1417  return EmitCastLValue(cast<CastExpr>(E));
1418 
1419  case Expr::MaterializeTemporaryExprClass:
1420  return EmitMaterializeTemporaryExpr(cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(E));
1421 
1422  case Expr::CoawaitExprClass:
1423  return EmitCoawaitLValue(cast<CoawaitExpr>(E));
1424  case Expr::CoyieldExprClass:
1425  return EmitCoyieldLValue(cast<CoyieldExpr>(E));
1426  }
1427 }
1428 
1429 /// Given an object of the given canonical type, can we safely copy a
1430 /// value out of it based on its initializer?
1431 static bool isConstantEmittableObjectType(QualType type) {
1432  assert(type.isCanonical());
1433  assert(!type->isReferenceType());
1434 
1435  // Must be const-qualified but non-volatile.
1436  Qualifiers qs = type.getLocalQualifiers();
1437  if (!qs.hasConst() || qs.hasVolatile()) return false;
1438 
1439  // Otherwise, all object types satisfy this except C++ classes with
1440  // mutable subobjects or non-trivial copy/destroy behavior.
1441  if (const auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(type))
1442  if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
1443  if (RD->hasMutableFields() || !RD->isTrivial())
1444  return false;
1445 
1446  return true;
1447 }
1448 
1449 /// Can we constant-emit a load of a reference to a variable of the
1450 /// given type? This is different from predicates like
1451 /// Decl::mightBeUsableInConstantExpressions because we do want it to apply
1452 /// in situations that don't necessarily satisfy the language's rules
1453 /// for this (e.g. C++'s ODR-use rules). For example, we want to able
1454 /// to do this with const float variables even if those variables
1455 /// aren't marked 'constexpr'.
1456 enum ConstantEmissionKind {
1457  CEK_None,
1458  CEK_AsReferenceOnly,
1459  CEK_AsValueOrReference,
1460  CEK_AsValueOnly
1461 };
1462 static ConstantEmissionKind checkVarTypeForConstantEmission(QualType type) {
1463  type = type.getCanonicalType();
1464  if (const auto *ref = dyn_cast<ReferenceType>(type)) {
1465  if (isConstantEmittableObjectType(ref->getPointeeType()))
1466  return CEK_AsValueOrReference;
1467  return CEK_AsReferenceOnly;
1468  }
1469  if (isConstantEmittableObjectType(type))
1470  return CEK_AsValueOnly;
1471  return CEK_None;
1472 }
1473 
1474 /// Try to emit a reference to the given value without producing it as
1475 /// an l-value. This is just an optimization, but it avoids us needing
1476 /// to emit global copies of variables if they're named without triggering
1477 /// a formal use in a context where we can't emit a direct reference to them,
1478 /// for instance if a block or lambda or a member of a local class uses a
1479 /// const int variable or constexpr variable from an enclosing function.
1480 CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission
1481 CodeGenFunction::tryEmitAsConstant(DeclRefExpr *refExpr) {
1482  ValueDecl *value = refExpr->getDecl();
1483 
1484  // The value needs to be an enum constant or a constant variable.
1485  ConstantEmissionKind CEK;
1486  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(value)) {
1487  CEK = CEK_None;
1488  } else if (auto *var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(value)) {
1489  CEK = checkVarTypeForConstantEmission(var->getType());
1490  } else if (isa<EnumConstantDecl>(value)) {
1491  CEK = CEK_AsValueOnly;
1492  } else {
1493  CEK = CEK_None;
1494  }
1495  if (CEK == CEK_None) return ConstantEmission();
1496 
1497  Expr::EvalResult result;
1498  bool resultIsReference;
1499  QualType resultType;
1500 
1501  // It's best to evaluate all the way as an r-value if that's permitted.
1502  if (CEK != CEK_AsReferenceOnly &&
1503  refExpr->EvaluateAsRValue(result, getContext())) {
1504  resultIsReference = false;
1505  resultType = refExpr->getType();
1506 
1507  // Otherwise, try to evaluate as an l-value.
1508  } else if (CEK != CEK_AsValueOnly &&
1509  refExpr->EvaluateAsLValue(result, getContext())) {
1510  resultIsReference = true;
1511  resultType = value->getType();
1512 
1513  // Failure.
1514  } else {
1515  return ConstantEmission();
1516  }
1517 
1518  // In any case, if the initializer has side-effects, abandon ship.
1519  if (result.HasSideEffects)
1520  return ConstantEmission();
1521 
1522  // In CUDA/HIP device compilation, a lambda may capture a reference variable
1523  // referencing a global host variable by copy. In this case the lambda should
1524  // make a copy of the value of the global host variable. The DRE of the
1525  // captured reference variable cannot be emitted as load from the host
1526  // global variable as compile time constant, since the host variable is not
1527  // accessible on device. The DRE of the captured reference variable has to be
1528  // loaded from captures.
1529  if (CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && result.Val.isLValue() &&
1530  refExpr->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture()) {
1531  auto *MD = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl);
1532  if (MD && MD->getParent()->isLambda() &&
1533  MD->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_Call) {
1534  const APValue::LValueBase &base = result.Val.getLValueBase();
1535  if (const ValueDecl *D = base.dyn_cast<const ValueDecl *>()) {
1536  if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<const VarDecl>(D)) {
1537  if (!VD->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
1538  return ConstantEmission();
1539  }
1540  }
1541  }
1542  }
1543  }
1544 
1545  // Emit as a constant.
1546  auto C = ConstantEmitter(*this).emitAbstract(refExpr->getLocation(),
1547  result.Val, resultType);
1548 
1549  // Make sure we emit a debug reference to the global variable.
1550  // This should probably fire even for
1551  if (isa<VarDecl>(value)) {
1552  if (!getContext().DeclMustBeEmitted(cast<VarDecl>(value)))
1553  EmitDeclRefExprDbgValue(refExpr, result.Val);
1554  } else {
1555  assert(isa<EnumConstantDecl>(value));
1556  EmitDeclRefExprDbgValue(refExpr, result.Val);
1557  }
1558 
1559  // If we emitted a reference constant, we need to dereference that.
1560  if (resultIsReference)
1561  return ConstantEmission::forReference(C);
1562 
1563  return ConstantEmission::forValue(C);
1564 }
1565 
1566 static DeclRefExpr *tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1567  const MemberExpr *ME) {
1568  if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
1569  // Try to emit static variable member expressions as DREs.
1570  return DeclRefExpr::Create(
1571  CGF.getContext(), NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), SourceLocation(), VD,
1572  /*RefersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture=*/false, ME->getExprLoc(),
1573  ME->getType(), ME->getValueKind(), nullptr, nullptr, ME->isNonOdrUse());
1574  }
1575  return nullptr;
1576 }
1577 
1578 CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission
1579 CodeGenFunction::tryEmitAsConstant(const MemberExpr *ME) {
1580  if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(*this, ME))
1581  return tryEmitAsConstant(DRE);
1582  return ConstantEmission();
1583 }
1584 
1585 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::emitScalarConstant(
1586  const CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission &Constant, Expr *E) {
1587  assert(Constant && "not a constant");
1588  if (Constant.isReference())
1589  return EmitLoadOfLValue(Constant.getReferenceLValue(*this, E),
1590  E->getExprLoc())
1591  .getScalarVal();
1592  return Constant.getValue();
1593 }
1594 
1595 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfScalar(LValue lvalue,
1596  SourceLocation Loc) {
1597  return EmitLoadOfScalar(lvalue.getAddress(*this), lvalue.isVolatile(),
1598  lvalue.getType(), Loc, lvalue.getBaseInfo(),
1599  lvalue.getTBAAInfo(), lvalue.isNontemporal());
1600 }
1601 
1602 static bool hasBooleanRepresentation(QualType Ty) {
1603  if (Ty->isBooleanType())
1604  return true;
1605 
1606  if (const EnumType *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
1607  return ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType()->isBooleanType();
1608 
1609  if (const AtomicType *AT = Ty->getAs<AtomicType>())
1610  return hasBooleanRepresentation(AT->getValueType());
1611 
1612  return false;
1613 }
1614 
1615 static bool getRangeForType(CodeGenFunction &CGF, QualType Ty,
1616  llvm::APInt &Min, llvm::APInt &End,
1617  bool StrictEnums, bool IsBool) {
1618  const EnumType *ET = Ty->getAs<EnumType>();
1619  bool IsRegularCPlusPlusEnum = CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && StrictEnums &&
1620  ET && !ET->getDecl()->isFixed();
1621  if (!IsBool && !IsRegularCPlusPlusEnum)
1622  return false;
1623 
1624  if (IsBool) {
1625  Min = llvm::APInt(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 0);
1626  End = llvm::APInt(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 2);
1627  } else {
1628  const EnumDecl *ED = ET->getDecl();
1629  llvm::Type *LTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ED->getIntegerType());
1630  unsigned Bitwidth = LTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
1631  unsigned NumNegativeBits = ED->getNumNegativeBits();
1632  unsigned NumPositiveBits = ED->getNumPositiveBits();
1633 
1634  if (NumNegativeBits) {
1635  unsigned NumBits = std::max(NumNegativeBits, NumPositiveBits + 1);
1636  assert(NumBits <= Bitwidth);
1637  End = llvm::APInt(Bitwidth, 1) << (NumBits - 1);
1638  Min = -End;
1639  } else {
1640  assert(NumPositiveBits <= Bitwidth);
1641  End = llvm::APInt(Bitwidth, 1) << NumPositiveBits;
1642  Min = llvm::APInt::getZero(Bitwidth);
1643  }
1644  }
1645  return true;
1646 }
1647 
1648 llvm::MDNode *CodeGenFunction::getRangeForLoadFromType(QualType Ty) {
1649  llvm::APInt Min, End;
1650  if (!getRangeForType(*this, Ty, Min, End, CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictEnums,
1651  hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)))
1652  return nullptr;
1653 
1654  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
1655  return MDHelper.createRange(Min, End);
1656 }
1657 
1658 bool CodeGenFunction::EmitScalarRangeCheck(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty,
1659  SourceLocation Loc) {
1660  bool HasBoolCheck = SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Bool);
1661  bool HasEnumCheck = SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Enum);
1662  if (!HasBoolCheck && !HasEnumCheck)
1663  return false;
1664 
1665  bool IsBool = hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty) ||
1666  NSAPI(CGM.getContext()).isObjCBOOLType(Ty);
1667  bool NeedsBoolCheck = HasBoolCheck && IsBool;
1668  bool NeedsEnumCheck = HasEnumCheck && Ty->getAs<EnumType>();
1669  if (!NeedsBoolCheck && !NeedsEnumCheck)
1670  return false;
1671 
1672  // Single-bit booleans don't need to be checked. Special-case this to avoid
1673  // a bit width mismatch when handling bitfield values. This is handled by
1674  // EmitFromMemory for the non-bitfield case.
1675  if (IsBool &&
1676  cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Value->getType())->getBitWidth() == 1)
1677  return false;
1678 
1679  llvm::APInt Min, End;
1680  if (!getRangeForType(*this, Ty, Min, End, /*StrictEnums=*/true, IsBool))
1681  return true;
1682 
1683  auto &Ctx = getLLVMContext();
1684  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
1685  llvm::Value *Check;
1686  --End;
1687  if (!Min) {
1688  Check = Builder.CreateICmpULE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, End));
1689  } else {
1690  llvm::Value *Upper =
1691  Builder.CreateICmpSLE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, End));
1692  llvm::Value *Lower =
1693  Builder.CreateICmpSGE(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Ctx, Min));
1694  Check = Builder.CreateAnd(Upper, Lower);
1695  }
1696  llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
1697  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(Ty)};
1698  SanitizerMask Kind =
1699  NeedsEnumCheck ? SanitizerKind::Enum : SanitizerKind::Bool;
1700  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Check, Kind), SanitizerHandler::LoadInvalidValue,
1701  StaticArgs, EmitCheckValue(Value));
1702  return true;
1703 }
1704 
1705 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfScalar(Address Addr, bool Volatile,
1706  QualType Ty,
1707  SourceLocation Loc,
1708  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo,
1709  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo,
1710  bool isNontemporal) {
1711  if (const auto *ClangVecTy = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
1712  // Boolean vectors use `iN` as storage type.
1713  if (ClangVecTy->isExtVectorBoolType()) {
1714  llvm::Type *ValTy = ConvertType(Ty);
1715  unsigned ValNumElems =
1716  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(ValTy)->getNumElements();
1717  // Load the `iP` storage object (P is the padded vector size).
1718  auto *RawIntV = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr, Volatile, "load_bits");
1719  const auto *RawIntTy = RawIntV->getType();
1720  assert(RawIntTy->isIntegerTy() && "compressed iN storage for bitvectors");
1721  // Bitcast iP --> <P x i1>.
1722  auto *PaddedVecTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
1723  Builder.getInt1Ty(), RawIntTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
1724  llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateBitCast(RawIntV, PaddedVecTy);
1725  // Shuffle <P x i1> --> <N x i1> (N is the actual bit size).
1726  V = emitBoolVecConversion(V, ValNumElems, "extractvec");
1727 
1728  return EmitFromMemory(V, Ty);
1729  }
1730 
1731  // Handle vectors of size 3 like size 4 for better performance.
1732  const llvm::Type *EltTy = Addr.getElementType();
1733  const auto *VTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(EltTy);
1734 
1735  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type && VTy->getNumElements() == 3) {
1736 
1737  // Bitcast to vec4 type.
1738  llvm::VectorType *vec4Ty =
1739  llvm::FixedVectorType::get(VTy->getElementType(), 4);
1740  Address Cast = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, vec4Ty, "castToVec4");
1741  // Now load value.
1742  llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateLoad(Cast, Volatile, "loadVec4");
1743 
1744  // Shuffle vector to get vec3.
1745  V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, ArrayRef<int>{0, 1, 2}, "extractVec");
1746  return EmitFromMemory(V, Ty);
1747  }
1748  }
1749 
1750  // Atomic operations have to be done on integral types.
1751  LValue AtomicLValue =
1752  LValue::MakeAddr(Addr, Ty, getContext(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
1753  if (Ty->isAtomicType() || LValueIsSuitableForInlineAtomic(AtomicLValue)) {
1754  return EmitAtomicLoad(AtomicLValue, Loc).getScalarVal();
1755  }
1756 
1757  llvm::LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(Addr, Volatile);
1758  if (isNontemporal) {
1759  llvm::MDNode *Node = llvm::MDNode::get(
1760  Load->getContext(), llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(1)));
1761  Load->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("nontemporal"), Node);
1762  }
1763 
1764  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Load, TBAAInfo);
1765 
1766  if (EmitScalarRangeCheck(Load, Ty, Loc)) {
1767  // In order to prevent the optimizer from throwing away the check, don't
1768  // attach range metadata to the load.
1769  } else if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0)
1770  if (llvm::MDNode *RangeInfo = getRangeForLoadFromType(Ty))
1771  Load->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_range, RangeInfo);
1772 
1773  return EmitFromMemory(Load, Ty);
1774 }
1775 
1776 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitToMemory(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty) {
1777  // Bool has a different representation in memory than in registers.
1778  if (hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)) {
1779  // This should really always be an i1, but sometimes it's already
1780  // an i8, and it's awkward to track those cases down.
1781  if (Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(1))
1782  return Builder.CreateZExt(Value, ConvertTypeForMem(Ty), "frombool");
1783  assert(Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty)) &&
1784  "wrong value rep of bool");
1785  }
1786 
1787  return Value;
1788 }
1789 
1790 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitFromMemory(llvm::Value *Value, QualType Ty) {
1791  // Bool has a different representation in memory than in registers.
1792  if (hasBooleanRepresentation(Ty)) {
1793  assert(Value->getType()->isIntegerTy(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty)) &&
1794  "wrong value rep of bool");
1795  return Builder.CreateTrunc(Value, Builder.getInt1Ty(), "tobool");
1796  }
1797  if (Ty->isExtVectorBoolType()) {
1798  const auto *RawIntTy = Value->getType();
1799  // Bitcast iP --> <P x i1>.
1800  auto *PaddedVecTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
1801  Builder.getInt1Ty(), RawIntTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
1802  auto *V = Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, PaddedVecTy);
1803  // Shuffle <P x i1> --> <N x i1> (N is the actual bit size).
1804  llvm::Type *ValTy = ConvertType(Ty);
1805  unsigned ValNumElems = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(ValTy)->getNumElements();
1806  return emitBoolVecConversion(V, ValNumElems, "extractvec");
1807  }
1808 
1809  return Value;
1810 }
1811 
1812 // Convert the pointer of \p Addr to a pointer to a vector (the value type of
1813 // MatrixType), if it points to a array (the memory type of MatrixType).
1814 static Address MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(Address Addr, CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1815  bool IsVector = true) {
1816  auto *ArrayTy = dyn_cast<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType());
1817  if (ArrayTy && IsVector) {
1818  auto *VectorTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(ArrayTy->getElementType(),
1819  ArrayTy->getNumElements());
1820 
1821  return Address(CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, VectorTy));
1822  }
1823  auto *VectorTy = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(Addr.getElementType());
1824  if (VectorTy && !IsVector) {
1825  auto *ArrayTy = llvm::ArrayType::get(
1826  VectorTy->getElementType(),
1827  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(VectorTy)->getNumElements());
1828 
1829  return Address(CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ArrayTy));
1830  }
1831 
1832  return Addr;
1833 }
1834 
1835 // Emit a store of a matrix LValue. This may require casting the original
1836 // pointer to memory address (ArrayType) to a pointer to the value type
1837 // (VectorType).
1838 static void EmitStoreOfMatrixScalar(llvm::Value *value, LValue lvalue,
1839  bool isInit, CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1840  Address Addr = MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(lvalue.getAddress(CGF), CGF,
1841  value->getType()->isVectorTy());
1842  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(value, Addr, lvalue.isVolatile(), lvalue.getType(),
1843  lvalue.getBaseInfo(), lvalue.getTBAAInfo(), isInit,
1844  lvalue.isNontemporal());
1845 }
1846 
1847 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Value *Value, Address Addr,
1848  bool Volatile, QualType Ty,
1849  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo,
1850  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo,
1851  bool isInit, bool isNontemporal) {
1852  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Value->getType();
1853  if (const auto *ClangVecTy = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
1854  auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy);
1855  if (VecTy && ClangVecTy->isExtVectorBoolType()) {
1856  auto *MemIntTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Addr.getElementType());
1857  // Expand to the memory bit width.
1858  unsigned MemNumElems = MemIntTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1859  // <N x i1> --> <P x i1>.
1860  Value = emitBoolVecConversion(Value, MemNumElems, "insertvec");
1861  // <P x i1> --> iP.
1862  Value = Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, MemIntTy);
1863  } else if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PreserveVec3Type) {
1864  // Handle vec3 special.
1865  if (VecTy && cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(VecTy)->getNumElements() == 3) {
1866  // Our source is a vec3, do a shuffle vector to make it a vec4.
1867  Value = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Value, ArrayRef<int>{0, 1, 2, -1},
1868  "extractVec");
1869  SrcTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(VecTy->getElementType(), 4);
1870  }
1871  if (Addr.getElementType() != SrcTy) {
1872  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, SrcTy, "storetmp");
1873  }
1874  }
1875  }
1876 
1877  Value = EmitToMemory(Value, Ty);
1878 
1879  LValue AtomicLValue =
1880  LValue::MakeAddr(Addr, Ty, getContext(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
1881  if (Ty->isAtomicType() ||
1882  (!isInit && LValueIsSuitableForInlineAtomic(AtomicLValue))) {
1883  EmitAtomicStore(RValue::get(Value), AtomicLValue, isInit);
1884  return;
1885  }
1886 
1887  llvm::StoreInst *Store = Builder.CreateStore(Value, Addr, Volatile);
1888  if (isNontemporal) {
1889  llvm::MDNode *Node =
1890  llvm::MDNode::get(Store->getContext(),
1891  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(1)));
1892  Store->setMetadata(CGM.getModule().getMDKindID("nontemporal"), Node);
1893  }
1894 
1895  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Store, TBAAInfo);
1896 }
1897 
1898 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::Value *value, LValue lvalue,
1899  bool isInit) {
1900  if (lvalue.getType()->isConstantMatrixType()) {
1901  EmitStoreOfMatrixScalar(value, lvalue, isInit, *this);
1902  return;
1903  }
1904 
1905  EmitStoreOfScalar(value, lvalue.getAddress(*this), lvalue.isVolatile(),
1906  lvalue.getType(), lvalue.getBaseInfo(),
1907  lvalue.getTBAAInfo(), isInit, lvalue.isNontemporal());
1908 }
1909 
1910 // Emit a load of a LValue of matrix type. This may require casting the pointer
1911 // to memory address (ArrayType) to a pointer to the value type (VectorType).
1912 static RValue EmitLoadOfMatrixLValue(LValue LV, SourceLocation Loc,
1913  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1914  assert(LV.getType()->isConstantMatrixType());
1915  Address Addr = MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(LV.getAddress(CGF), CGF);
1916  LV.setAddress(Addr);
1917  return RValue::get(CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(LV, Loc));
1918 }
1919 
1920 /// EmitLoadOfLValue - Given an expression that represents a value lvalue, this
1921 /// method emits the address of the lvalue, then loads the result as an rvalue,
1922 /// returning the rvalue.
1923 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfLValue(LValue LV, SourceLocation Loc) {
1924  if (LV.isObjCWeak()) {
1925  // load of a __weak object.
1926  Address AddrWeakObj = LV.getAddress(*this);
1927  return RValue::get(CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCWeakRead(*this,
1928  AddrWeakObj));
1929  }
1930  if (LV.getQuals().getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak) {
1931  // In MRC mode, we do a load+autorelease.
1932  if (!getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) {
1933  return RValue::get(EmitARCLoadWeak(LV.getAddress(*this)));
1934  }
1935 
1936  // In ARC mode, we load retained and then consume the value.
1937  llvm::Value *Object = EmitARCLoadWeakRetained(LV.getAddress(*this));
1938  Object = EmitObjCConsumeObject(LV.getType(), Object);
1939  return RValue::get(Object);
1940  }
1941 
1942  if (LV.isSimple()) {
1943  assert(!LV.getType()->isFunctionType());
1944 
1945  if (LV.getType()->isConstantMatrixType())
1946  return EmitLoadOfMatrixLValue(LV, Loc, *this);
1947 
1948  // Everything needs a load.
1949  return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(LV, Loc));
1950  }
1951 
1952  if (LV.isVectorElt()) {
1953  llvm::LoadInst *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getVectorAddress(),
1954  LV.isVolatileQualified());
1955  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Load, LV.getVectorIdx(),
1956  "vecext"));
1957  }
1958 
1959  // If this is a reference to a subset of the elements of a vector, either
1960  // shuffle the input or extract/insert them as appropriate.
1961  if (LV.isExtVectorElt()) {
1962  return EmitLoadOfExtVectorElementLValue(LV);
1963  }
1964 
1965  // Global Register variables always invoke intrinsics
1966  if (LV.isGlobalReg())
1967  return EmitLoadOfGlobalRegLValue(LV);
1968 
1969  if (LV.isMatrixElt()) {
1970  llvm::Value *Idx = LV.getMatrixIdx();
1971  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0) {
1972  const auto *const MatTy = LV.getType()->castAs<ConstantMatrixType>();
1973  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
1974  MB.CreateIndexAssumption(Idx, MatTy->getNumElementsFlattened());
1975  }
1976  llvm::LoadInst *Load =
1977  Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getMatrixAddress(), LV.isVolatileQualified());
1978  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Load, Idx, "matrixext"));
1979  }
1980 
1981  assert(LV.isBitField() && "Unknown LValue type!");
1982  return EmitLoadOfBitfieldLValue(LV, Loc);
1983 }
1984 
1985 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfBitfieldLValue(LValue LV,
1986  SourceLocation Loc) {
1987  const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = LV.getBitFieldInfo();
1988 
1989  // Get the output type.
1990  llvm::Type *ResLTy = ConvertType(LV.getType());
1991 
1992  Address Ptr = LV.getBitFieldAddress();
1993  llvm::Value *Val =
1994  Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, LV.isVolatileQualified(), "bf.load");
1995 
1996  bool UseVolatile = LV.isVolatileQualified() &&
1997  Info.VolatileStorageSize != 0 && isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget());
1998  const unsigned Offset = UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileOffset : Info.Offset;
1999  const unsigned StorageSize =
2000  UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileStorageSize : Info.StorageSize;
2001  if (Info.IsSigned) {
2002  assert(static_cast<unsigned>(Offset + Info.Size) <= StorageSize);
2003  unsigned HighBits = StorageSize - Offset - Info.Size;
2004  if (HighBits)
2005  Val = Builder.CreateShl(Val, HighBits, "bf.shl");
2006  if (Offset + HighBits)
2007  Val = Builder.CreateAShr(Val, Offset + HighBits, "bf.ashr");
2008  } else {
2009  if (Offset)
2010  Val = Builder.CreateLShr(Val, Offset, "bf.lshr");
2011  if (static_cast<unsigned>(Offset) + Info.Size < StorageSize)
2012  Val = Builder.CreateAnd(
2013  Val, llvm::APInt::getLowBitsSet(StorageSize, Info.Size), "bf.clear");
2014  }
2015  Val = Builder.CreateIntCast(Val, ResLTy, Info.IsSigned, "bf.cast");
2016  EmitScalarRangeCheck(Val, LV.getType(), Loc);
2017  return RValue::get(Val);
2018 }
2019 
2020 // If this is a reference to a subset of the elements of a vector, create an
2021 // appropriate shufflevector.
2022 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfExtVectorElementLValue(LValue LV) {
2023  llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(LV.getExtVectorAddress(),
2024  LV.isVolatileQualified());
2025 
2026  const llvm::Constant *Elts = LV.getExtVectorElts();
2027 
2028  // If the result of the expression is a non-vector type, we must be extracting
2029  // a single element. Just codegen as an extractelement.
2030  const VectorType *ExprVT = LV.getType()->getAs<VectorType>();
2031  if (!ExprVT) {
2032  unsigned InIdx = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2033  llvm::Value *Elt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, InIdx);
2034  return RValue::get(Builder.CreateExtractElement(Vec, Elt));
2035  }
2036 
2037  // Always use shuffle vector to try to retain the original program structure
2038  unsigned NumResultElts = ExprVT->getNumElements();
2039 
2040  SmallVector<int, 4> Mask;
2041  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumResultElts; ++i)
2042  Mask.push_back(getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts));
2043 
2044  Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, Mask);
2045  return RValue::get(Vec);
2046 }
2047 
2048 /// Generates lvalue for partial ext_vector access.
2049 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitExtVectorElementLValue(LValue LV) {
2050  Address VectorAddress = LV.getExtVectorAddress();
2051  QualType EQT = LV.getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2052  llvm::Type *VectorElementTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(EQT);
2053 
2054  Address CastToPointerElement =
2055  Builder.CreateElementBitCast(VectorAddress, VectorElementTy,
2056  "conv.ptr.element");
2057 
2058  const llvm::Constant *Elts = LV.getExtVectorElts();
2059  unsigned ix = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2060 
2061  Address VectorBasePtrPlusIx =
2062  Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(CastToPointerElement, ix,
2063  "vector.elt");
2064 
2065  return VectorBasePtrPlusIx;
2066 }
2067 
2068 /// Load of global gamed gegisters are always calls to intrinsics.
2069 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfGlobalRegLValue(LValue LV) {
2070  assert((LV.getType()->isIntegerType() || LV.getType()->isPointerType()) &&
2071  "Bad type for register variable");
2072  llvm::MDNode *RegName = cast<llvm::MDNode>(
2073  cast<llvm::MetadataAsValue>(LV.getGlobalReg())->getMetadata());
2074 
2075  // We accept integer and pointer types only
2076  llvm::Type *OrigTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(LV.getType());
2077  llvm::Type *Ty = OrigTy;
2078  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2079  Ty = CGM.getTypes().getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(OrigTy);
2080  llvm::Type *Types[] = { Ty };
2081 
2082  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::read_register, Types);
2083  llvm::Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(
2084  F, llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Ty->getContext(), RegName));
2085  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2086  Call = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Call, OrigTy);
2087  return RValue::get(Call);
2088 }
2089 
2090 /// EmitStoreThroughLValue - Store the specified rvalue into the specified
2091 /// lvalue, where both are guaranteed to the have the same type, and that type
2092 /// is 'Ty'.
2093 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst,
2094  bool isInit) {
2095  if (!Dst.isSimple()) {
2096  if (Dst.isVectorElt()) {
2097  // Read/modify/write the vector, inserting the new element.
2098  llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(Dst.getVectorAddress(),
2099  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2100  auto *IRStoreTy = dyn_cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Vec->getType());
2101  if (IRStoreTy) {
2102  auto *IRVecTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
2103  Builder.getInt1Ty(), IRStoreTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
2104  Vec = Builder.CreateBitCast(Vec, IRVecTy);
2105  // iN --> <N x i1>.
2106  }
2107  Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, Src.getScalarVal(),
2108  Dst.getVectorIdx(), "vecins");
2109  if (IRStoreTy) {
2110  // <N x i1> --> <iN>.
2111  Vec = Builder.CreateBitCast(Vec, IRStoreTy);
2112  }
2113  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getVectorAddress(),
2114  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2115  return;
2116  }
2117 
2118  // If this is an update of extended vector elements, insert them as
2119  // appropriate.
2120  if (Dst.isExtVectorElt())
2121  return EmitStoreThroughExtVectorComponentLValue(Src, Dst);
2122 
2123  if (Dst.isGlobalReg())
2124  return EmitStoreThroughGlobalRegLValue(Src, Dst);
2125 
2126  if (Dst.isMatrixElt()) {
2127  llvm::Value *Idx = Dst.getMatrixIdx();
2128  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0) {
2129  const auto *const MatTy = Dst.getType()->castAs<ConstantMatrixType>();
2130  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
2131  MB.CreateIndexAssumption(Idx, MatTy->getNumElementsFlattened());
2132  }
2133  llvm::Instruction *Load = Builder.CreateLoad(Dst.getMatrixAddress());
2134  llvm::Value *Vec =
2135  Builder.CreateInsertElement(Load, Src.getScalarVal(), Idx, "matins");
2136  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getMatrixAddress(),
2137  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2138  return;
2139  }
2140 
2141  assert(Dst.isBitField() && "Unknown LValue type");
2142  return EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(Src, Dst);
2143  }
2144 
2145  // There's special magic for assigning into an ARC-qualified l-value.
2146  if (Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime = Dst.getQuals().getObjCLifetime()) {
2147  switch (Lifetime) {
2148  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
2149  llvm_unreachable("present but none");
2150 
2151  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2152  // nothing special
2153  break;
2154 
2155  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2156  if (isInit) {
2157  Src = RValue::get(EmitARCRetain(Dst.getType(), Src.getScalarVal()));
2158  break;
2159  }
2160  EmitARCStoreStrong(Dst, Src.getScalarVal(), /*ignore*/ true);
2161  return;
2162 
2163  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2164  if (isInit)
2165  // Initialize and then skip the primitive store.
2166  EmitARCInitWeak(Dst.getAddress(*this), Src.getScalarVal());
2167  else
2168  EmitARCStoreWeak(Dst.getAddress(*this), Src.getScalarVal(),
2169  /*ignore*/ true);
2170  return;
2171 
2172  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
2173  Src = RValue::get(EmitObjCExtendObjectLifetime(Dst.getType(),
2174  Src.getScalarVal()));
2175  // fall into the normal path
2176  break;
2177  }
2178  }
2179 
2180  if (Dst.isObjCWeak() && !Dst.isNonGC()) {
2181  // load of a __weak object.
2182  Address LvalueDst = Dst.getAddress(*this);
2183  llvm::Value *src = Src.getScalarVal();
2184  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCWeakAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst);
2185  return;
2186  }
2187 
2188  if (Dst.isObjCStrong() && !Dst.isNonGC()) {
2189  // load of a __strong object.
2190  Address LvalueDst = Dst.getAddress(*this);
2191  llvm::Value *src = Src.getScalarVal();
2192  if (Dst.isObjCIvar()) {
2193  assert(Dst.getBaseIvarExp() && "BaseIvarExp is NULL");
2194  llvm::Type *ResultType = IntPtrTy;
2195  Address dst = EmitPointerWithAlignment(Dst.getBaseIvarExp());
2196  llvm::Value *RHS = dst.getPointer();
2197  RHS = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(RHS, ResultType, "sub.ptr.rhs.cast");
2198  llvm::Value *LHS =
2199  Builder.CreatePtrToInt(LvalueDst.getPointer(), ResultType,
2200  "sub.ptr.lhs.cast");
2201  llvm::Value *BytesBetween = Builder.CreateSub(LHS, RHS, "ivar.offset");
2202  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCIvarAssign(*this, src, dst,
2203  BytesBetween);
2204  } else if (Dst.isGlobalObjCRef()) {
2205  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCGlobalAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst,
2206  Dst.isThreadLocalRef());
2207  }
2208  else
2209  CGM.getObjCRuntime().EmitObjCStrongCastAssign(*this, src, LvalueDst);
2210  return;
2211  }
2212 
2213  assert(Src.isScalar() && "Can't emit an agg store with this method");
2214  EmitStoreOfScalar(Src.getScalarVal(), Dst, isInit);
2215 }
2216 
2217 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst,
2218  llvm::Value **Result) {
2219  const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = Dst.getBitFieldInfo();
2220  llvm::Type *ResLTy = ConvertTypeForMem(Dst.getType());
2221  Address Ptr = Dst.getBitFieldAddress();
2222 
2223  // Get the source value, truncated to the width of the bit-field.
2224  llvm::Value *SrcVal = Src.getScalarVal();
2225 
2226  // Cast the source to the storage type and shift it into place.
2227  SrcVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(SrcVal, Ptr.getElementType(),
2228  /*isSigned=*/false);
2229  llvm::Value *MaskedVal = SrcVal;
2230 
2231  const bool UseVolatile =
2232  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().AAPCSBitfieldWidth && Dst.isVolatileQualified() &&
2233  Info.VolatileStorageSize != 0 && isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget());
2234  const unsigned StorageSize =
2235  UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileStorageSize : Info.StorageSize;
2236  const unsigned Offset = UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileOffset : Info.Offset;
2237  // See if there are other bits in the bitfield's storage we'll need to load
2238  // and mask together with source before storing.
2239  if (StorageSize != Info.Size) {
2240  assert(StorageSize > Info.Size && "Invalid bitfield size.");
2241  llvm::Value *Val =
2242  Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, Dst.isVolatileQualified(), "bf.load");
2243 
2244  // Mask the source value as needed.
2245  if (!hasBooleanRepresentation(Dst.getType()))
2246  SrcVal = Builder.CreateAnd(
2247  SrcVal, llvm::APInt::getLowBitsSet(StorageSize, Info.Size),
2248  "bf.value");
2249  MaskedVal = SrcVal;
2250  if (Offset)
2251  SrcVal = Builder.CreateShl(SrcVal, Offset, "bf.shl");
2252 
2253  // Mask out the original value.
2254  Val = Builder.CreateAnd(
2255  Val, ~llvm::APInt::getBitsSet(StorageSize, Offset, Offset + Info.Size),
2256  "bf.clear");
2257 
2258  // Or together the unchanged values and the source value.
2259  SrcVal = Builder.CreateOr(Val, SrcVal, "bf.set");
2260  } else {
2261  assert(Offset == 0);
2262  // According to the AACPS:
2263  // When a volatile bit-field is written, and its container does not overlap
2264  // with any non-bit-field member, its container must be read exactly once
2265  // and written exactly once using the access width appropriate to the type
2266  // of the container. The two accesses are not atomic.
2267  if (Dst.isVolatileQualified() && isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget()) &&
2268  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ForceAAPCSBitfieldLoad)
2269  Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr, true, "bf.load");
2270  }
2271 
2272  // Write the new value back out.
2273  Builder.CreateStore(SrcVal, Ptr, Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2274 
2275  // Return the new value of the bit-field, if requested.
2276  if (Result) {
2277  llvm::Value *ResultVal = MaskedVal;
2278 
2279  // Sign extend the value if needed.
2280  if (Info.IsSigned) {
2281  assert(Info.Size <= StorageSize);
2282  unsigned HighBits = StorageSize - Info.Size;
2283  if (HighBits) {
2284  ResultVal = Builder.CreateShl(ResultVal, HighBits, "bf.result.shl");
2285  ResultVal = Builder.CreateAShr(ResultVal, HighBits, "bf.result.ashr");
2286  }
2287  }
2288 
2289  ResultVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(ResultVal, ResLTy, Info.IsSigned,
2290  "bf.result.cast");
2291  *Result = EmitFromMemory(ResultVal, Dst.getType());
2292  }
2293 }
2294 
2295 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughExtVectorComponentLValue(RValue Src,
2296  LValue Dst) {
2297  // This access turns into a read/modify/write of the vector. Load the input
2298  // value now.
2299  llvm::Value *Vec = Builder.CreateLoad(Dst.getExtVectorAddress(),
2300  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2301  const llvm::Constant *Elts = Dst.getExtVectorElts();
2302 
2303  llvm::Value *SrcVal = Src.getScalarVal();
2304 
2305  if (const VectorType *VTy = Dst.getType()->getAs<VectorType>()) {
2306  unsigned NumSrcElts = VTy->getNumElements();
2307  unsigned NumDstElts =
2308  cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType())->getNumElements();
2309  if (NumDstElts == NumSrcElts) {
2310  // Use shuffle vector is the src and destination are the same number of
2311  // elements and restore the vector mask since it is on the side it will be
2312  // stored.
2313  SmallVector<int, 4> Mask(NumDstElts);
2314  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2315  Mask[getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts)] = i;
2316 
2317  Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(SrcVal, Mask);
2318  } else if (NumDstElts > NumSrcElts) {
2319  // Extended the source vector to the same length and then shuffle it
2320  // into the destination.
2321  // FIXME: since we're shuffling with undef, can we just use the indices
2322  // into that? This could be simpler.
2323  SmallVector<int, 4> ExtMask;
2324  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2325  ExtMask.push_back(i);
2326  ExtMask.resize(NumDstElts, -1);
2327  llvm::Value *ExtSrcVal = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(SrcVal, ExtMask);
2328  // build identity
2329  SmallVector<int, 4> Mask;
2330  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumDstElts; ++i)
2331  Mask.push_back(i);
2332 
2333  // When the vector size is odd and .odd or .hi is used, the last element
2334  // of the Elts constant array will be one past the size of the vector.
2335  // Ignore the last element here, if it is greater than the mask size.
2336  if (getAccessedFieldNo(NumSrcElts - 1, Elts) == Mask.size())
2337  NumSrcElts--;
2338 
2339  // modify when what gets shuffled in
2340  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumSrcElts; ++i)
2341  Mask[getAccessedFieldNo(i, Elts)] = i + NumDstElts;
2342  Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, ExtSrcVal, Mask);
2343  } else {
2344  // We should never shorten the vector
2345  llvm_unreachable("unexpected shorten vector length");
2346  }
2347  } else {
2348  // If the Src is a scalar (not a vector) it must be updating one element.
2349  unsigned InIdx = getAccessedFieldNo(0, Elts);
2350  llvm::Value *Elt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, InIdx);
2351  Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, SrcVal, Elt);
2352  }
2353 
2354  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, Dst.getExtVectorAddress(),
2355  Dst.isVolatileQualified());
2356 }
2357 
2358 /// Store of global named registers are always calls to intrinsics.
2359 void CodeGenFunction::EmitStoreThroughGlobalRegLValue(RValue Src, LValue Dst) {
2360  assert((Dst.getType()->isIntegerType() || Dst.getType()->isPointerType()) &&
2361  "Bad type for register variable");
2362  llvm::MDNode *RegName = cast<llvm::MDNode>(
2363  cast<llvm::MetadataAsValue>(Dst.getGlobalReg())->getMetadata());
2364  assert(RegName && "Register LValue is not metadata");
2365 
2366  // We accept integer and pointer types only
2367  llvm::Type *OrigTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(Dst.getType());
2368  llvm::Type *Ty = OrigTy;
2369  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2370  Ty = CGM.getTypes().getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(OrigTy);
2371  llvm::Type *Types[] = { Ty };
2372 
2373  llvm::Function *F = CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::write_register, Types);
2374  llvm::Value *Value = Src.getScalarVal();
2375  if (OrigTy->isPointerTy())
2376  Value = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Value, Ty);
2377  Builder.CreateCall(
2378  F, {llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(Ty->getContext(), RegName), Value});
2379 }
2380 
2381 // setObjCGCLValueClass - sets class of the lvalue for the purpose of
2382 // generating write-barries API. It is currently a global, ivar,
2383 // or neither.
2384 static void setObjCGCLValueClass(const ASTContext &Ctx, const Expr *E,
2385  LValue &LV,
2386  bool IsMemberAccess=false) {
2387  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC)
2388  return;
2389 
2390  if (isa<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E)) {
2391  QualType ExpTy = E->getType();
2392  if (IsMemberAccess && ExpTy->isPointerType()) {
2393  // If ivar is a structure pointer, assigning to field of
2394  // this struct follows gcc's behavior and makes it a non-ivar
2395  // writer-barrier conservatively.
2396  ExpTy = ExpTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
2397  if (ExpTy->isRecordType()) {
2398  LV.setObjCIvar(false);
2399  return;
2400  }
2401  }
2402  LV.setObjCIvar(true);
2403  auto *Exp = cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
2404  LV.setBaseIvarExp(Exp->getBase());
2405  LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
2406  return;
2407  }
2408 
2409  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
2410  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Exp->getDecl())) {
2411  if (VD->hasGlobalStorage()) {
2412  LV.setGlobalObjCRef(true);
2413  LV.setThreadLocalRef(VD->getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None);
2414  }
2415  }
2416  LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
2417  return;
2418  }
2419 
2420  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
2421  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2422  return;
2423  }
2424 
2425  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
2426  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2427  if (LV.isObjCIvar()) {
2428  // If cast is to a structure pointer, follow gcc's behavior and make it
2429  // a non-ivar write-barrier.
2430  QualType ExpTy = E->getType();
2431  if (ExpTy->isPointerType())
2432  ExpTy = ExpTy->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
2433  if (ExpTy->isRecordType())
2434  LV.setObjCIvar(false);
2435  }
2436  return;
2437  }
2438 
2439  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(E)) {
2440  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getResultExpr(), LV);
2441  return;
2442  }
2443 
2444  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
2445  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2446  return;
2447  }
2448 
2449  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<CStyleCastExpr>(E)) {
2450  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2451  return;
2452  }
2453 
2454  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ObjCBridgedCastExpr>(E)) {
2455  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getSubExpr(), LV, IsMemberAccess);
2456  return;
2457  }
2458 
2459  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E)) {
2460  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getBase(), LV);
2461  if (LV.isObjCIvar() && !LV.isObjCArray())
2462  // Using array syntax to assigning to what an ivar points to is not
2463  // same as assigning to the ivar itself. {id *Names;} Names[i] = 0;
2464  LV.setObjCIvar(false);
2465  else if (LV.isGlobalObjCRef() && !LV.isObjCArray())
2466  // Using array syntax to assigning to what global points to is not
2467  // same as assigning to the global itself. {id *G;} G[i] = 0;
2468  LV.setGlobalObjCRef(false);
2469  return;
2470  }
2471 
2472  if (const auto *Exp = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
2473  setObjCGCLValueClass(Ctx, Exp->getBase(), LV, true);
2474  // We don't know if member is an 'ivar', but this flag is looked at
2475  // only in the context of LV.isObjCIvar().
2476  LV.setObjCArray(E->getType()->isArrayType());
2477  return;
2478  }
2479 }
2480 
2481 static llvm::Value *
2482 EmitBitCastOfLValueToProperType(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2483  llvm::Value *V, llvm::Type *IRType,
2484  StringRef Name = StringRef()) {
2485  unsigned AS = cast<llvm::PointerType>(V->getType())->getAddressSpace();
2486  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(V, IRType->getPointerTo(AS), Name);
2487 }

2489 static LValue EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(
2490  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const VarDecl *VD, QualType T, Address Addr,
2491  llvm::Type *RealVarTy, SourceLocation Loc) {
2492  if (CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIRBuilder)
2493  Addr = CodeGenFunction::OMPBuilderCBHelpers::getAddrOfThreadPrivate(
2494  CGF, VD, Addr, Loc);
2495  else
2496  Addr =
2497  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfThreadPrivate(CGF, VD, Addr, Loc);
2498 
2499  Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, RealVarTy);
2500  return CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2501 }
2502 
2503 static Address emitDeclTargetVarDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2504  const VarDecl *VD, QualType T) {
2505  llvm::Optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
2506  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD);
2507  // Return an invalid address if variable is MT_To and unified
2508  // memory is not enabled. For all other cases: MT_Link and
2509  // MT_To with unified memory, return a valid address.
2510  if (!Res || (*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To &&
2511  !CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory()))
2512  return Address::invalid();
2513  assert(((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link) ||
2514  (*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To &&
2515  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory())) &&
2516  "Expected link clause OR to clause with unified memory enabled.");
2517  QualType PtrTy = CGF.getContext().getPointerType(VD->getType());
2518  Address Addr = CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfDeclareTargetVar(VD);
2519  return CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(Addr, PtrTy->castAs<PointerType>());
2520 }

2522 Address
2523 CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfReference(LValue RefLVal,
2524  LValueBaseInfo *PointeeBaseInfo,
2525  TBAAAccessInfo *PointeeTBAAInfo) {
2526  llvm::LoadInst *Load =
2527  Builder.CreateLoad(RefLVal.getAddress(*this), RefLVal.isVolatile());
2528  CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Load, RefLVal.getTBAAInfo());
2529 
2530  QualType PointeeType = RefLVal.getType()->getPointeeType();
2531  CharUnits Align = CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(
2532  PointeeType, PointeeBaseInfo, PointeeTBAAInfo,
2533  /* forPointeeType= */ true);
2534  return Address(Load, ConvertTypeForMem(PointeeType), Align);
2535 }

2539  TBAAAccessInfo PointeeTBAAInfo;

2541  &PointeeTBAAInfo);
2542  return MakeAddrLValue(PointeeAddr, RefLVal.getType()->getPointeeType(),
2543  PointeeBaseInfo, PointeeTBAAInfo);
2544 }

2546 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfPointer(Address Ptr,
2547  const PointerType *PtrTy,
2548  LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
2549  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
2550  llvm::Value *Addr = Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr);
2551  return Address(Addr, ConvertTypeForMem(PtrTy->getPointeeType()),
2552  CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(PtrTy->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo,
2553  TBAAInfo,
2554  /*forPointeeType=*/true));
2555 }

2557 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLoadOfPointerLValue(Address PtrAddr,
