2565 static LValue EmitGlobalVarDeclLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2566  const Expr *E, const VarDecl *VD) {
2567  QualType T = E->getType();
2568 
2569  // If it's thread_local, emit a call to its wrapper function instead.
2570  if (VD->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic &&
2571  CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().usesThreadWrapperFunction(VD))
2572  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitThreadLocalVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T);
2573  // Check if the variable is marked as declare target with link clause in
2574  // device codegen.
2575  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice) {
2576  Address Addr = emitDeclTargetVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T);
2577  if (Addr.isValid())
2578  return CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2579  }
2580 
2581  llvm::Value *V = CGF.CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
2582  llvm::Type *RealVarTy = CGF.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType());
2583  V = EmitBitCastOfLValueToProperType(CGF, V, RealVarTy);
2584  CharUnits Alignment = CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
2585  Address Addr(V, RealVarTy, Alignment);
2586  // Emit reference to the private copy of the variable if it is an OpenMP
2587  // threadprivate variable.
2588  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP && !CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd &&
2589  VD->hasAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()) {
2590  return EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(CGF, VD, T, Addr, RealVarTy,
2591  E->getExprLoc());
2592  }
2593  LValue LV = VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ?
2594  CGF.EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(Addr, VD->getType(),
2595  AlignmentSource::Decl) :
2596  CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2597  setObjCGCLValueClass(CGF.getContext(), E, LV);
2598  return LV;
2599 }

2601 static llvm::Constant *EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2602  GlobalDecl GD) {
2603  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2604  if (FD->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>()) {
2605  ConstantAddress aliasee = CGM.GetWeakRefReference(FD);
2606  return aliasee.getPointer();
2607  }
2608 
2609  llvm::Constant *V = CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(GD);
2610  if (!FD->hasPrototype()) {
2611  if (const FunctionProtoType *Proto =
2612  FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
2613  // Ugly case: for a K&R-style definition, the type of the definition
2614  // isn't the same as the type of a use. Correct for this with a
2615  // bitcast.
2616  QualType NoProtoType =
2617  CGM.getContext().getFunctionNoProtoType(Proto->getReturnType());
2618  NoProtoType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(NoProtoType);
2619  V = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(V,
2620  CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(NoProtoType));
2621  }
2622  }
2623  return V;
2624 }

2630  CharUnits Alignment = CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(FD);

2635 static LValue EmitCapturedFieldLValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const FieldDecl *FD,

2642 /// Named Registers are named metadata pointing to the register name
2643 /// which will be read from/written to as an argument to the intrinsic
2644 /// @llvm.read/write_register.
2645 /// So far, only the name is being passed down, but other options such as
2646 /// register type, allocation type or even optimization options could be
2647 /// passed down via the metadata node.
2648 static LValue EmitGlobalNamedRegister(const VarDecl *VD, CodeGenModule &CGM) {
2649  SmallString<64> Name("llvm.named.register.");
2650  AsmLabelAttr *Asm = VD->getAttr<AsmLabelAttr>();
2651  assert(Asm->getLabel().size() < 64-Name.size() &&
2652  "Register name too big");
2653  Name.append(Asm->getLabel());
2654  llvm::NamedMDNode *M =
2655  CGM.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata(Name);
2656  if (M->getNumOperands() == 0) {
2657  llvm::MDString *Str = llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(),
2658  Asm->getLabel());
2659  llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = {Str};
2660  M->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Ops));
2661  }
2662 
2663  CharUnits Alignment = CGM.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
2664 
2665  llvm::Value *Ptr =
2666  llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), M->getOperand(0));
2667  return LValue::MakeGlobalReg(Ptr, Alignment, VD->getType());
2668 }
2669 
2670 /// Determine whether we can emit a reference to \p VD from the current
2671 /// context, despite not necessarily having seen an odr-use of the variable in
2672 /// this context.
2673 static bool canEmitSpuriousReferenceToVariable(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2674  const DeclRefExpr *E,
2675  const VarDecl *VD,
2676  bool IsConstant) {
2677  // For a variable declared in an enclosing scope, do not emit a spurious
2678  // reference even if we have a capture, as that will emit an unwarranted
2679  // reference to our capture state, and will likely generate worse code than
2680  // emitting a local copy.
2681  if (E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture())
2682  return false;
2683 
2684  // For a local declaration declared in this function, we can always reference
2685  // it even if we don't have an odr-use.
2686  if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
2687  return VD->getDeclContext() ==
2688  dyn_cast_or_null<DeclContext>(CGF.CurCodeDecl);
2689  }
2690 
2691  // For a global declaration, we can emit a reference to it if we know
2692  // for sure that we are able to emit a definition of it.
2693  VD = VD->getDefinition(CGF.getContext());
2694  if (!VD)
2695  return false;
2696 
2697  // Don't emit a spurious reference if it might be to a variable that only
2698  // exists on a different device / target.
2699  // FIXME: This is unnecessarily broad. Check whether this would actually be a
2700  // cross-target reference.
2701  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP || CGF.getLangOpts().CUDA ||
2702  CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
2703  return false;
2704  }
2705 
2706  // We can emit a spurious reference only if the linkage implies that we'll
2707  // be emitting a non-interposable symbol that will be retained until link
2708  // time.
2709  switch (CGF.CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD, IsConstant)) {
2710  case llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage:
2711  case llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage:
2712  case llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage:
2713  case llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage:
2714  case llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage:
2715  return true;
2716  default:
2717  return false;
2718  }
2719 }
2720 
2721 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitDeclRefLValue(const DeclRefExpr *E) {
2722  const NamedDecl *ND = E->getDecl();
2723  QualType T = E->getType();
2724 
2725  assert(E->isNonOdrUse() != NOUR_Unevaluated &&
2726  "should not emit an unevaluated operand");
2727 
2728  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
2729  // Global Named registers access via intrinsics only
2730  if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register &&
2731  VD->hasAttr<AsmLabelAttr>() && !VD->isLocalVarDecl())
2732  return EmitGlobalNamedRegister(VD, CGM);
2733 
2734  // If this DeclRefExpr does not constitute an odr-use of the variable,
2735  // we're not permitted to emit a reference to it in general, and it might
2736  // not be captured if capture would be necessary for a use. Emit the
2737  // constant value directly instead.
2738  if (E->isNonOdrUse() == NOUR_Constant &&
2739  (VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ||
2740  !canEmitSpuriousReferenceToVariable(*this, E, VD, true))) {
2741  VD->getAnyInitializer(VD);
2742  llvm::Constant *Val = ConstantEmitter(*this).emitAbstract(
2743  E->getLocation(), *VD->evaluateValue(), VD->getType());
2744  assert(Val && "failed to emit constant expression");
2745 
2746  Address Addr = Address::invalid();
2747  if (!VD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
2748  // Spill the constant value to a global.
2749  Addr = CGM.createUnnamedGlobalFrom(*VD, Val,
2750  getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
2751  llvm::Type *VarTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType());
2752  auto *PTy = llvm::PointerType::get(
2753  VarTy, getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(VD->getType()));
2754  Addr = Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Addr, PTy, VarTy);
2755  } else {
2756  // Should we be using the alignment of the constant pointer we emitted?
2757  CharUnits Alignment =
2758  CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(E->getType(),
2759  /* BaseInfo= */ nullptr,
2760  /* TBAAInfo= */ nullptr,
2761  /* forPointeeType= */ true);
2762  Addr = Address(Val, ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType()), Alignment);
2763  }
2764  return MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2765  }
2766 
2767  // FIXME: Handle other kinds of non-odr-use DeclRefExprs.
2768 
2769  // Check for captured variables.
2770  if (E->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture()) {
2771  VD = VD->getCanonicalDecl();
2772  if (auto *FD = LambdaCaptureFields.lookup(VD))
2773  return EmitCapturedFieldLValue(*this, FD, CXXABIThisValue);
2774  if (CapturedStmtInfo) {
2775  auto I = LocalDeclMap.find(VD);
2776  if (I != LocalDeclMap.end()) {
2777  LValue CapLVal;
2778  if (VD->getType()->isReferenceType())
2779  CapLVal = EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(I->second, VD->getType(),
2780  AlignmentSource::Decl);
2781  else
2782  CapLVal = MakeAddrLValue(I->second, T);
2783  // Mark lvalue as nontemporal if the variable is marked as nontemporal
2784  // in simd context.
2785  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP &&
2786  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().isNontemporalDecl(VD))
2787  CapLVal.setNontemporal(/*Value=*/true);
2788  return CapLVal;
2789  }
2790  LValue CapLVal =
2791  EmitCapturedFieldLValue(*this, CapturedStmtInfo->lookup(VD),
2792  CapturedStmtInfo->getContextValue());
2793  Address LValueAddress = CapLVal.getAddress(*this);
2794  CapLVal = MakeAddrLValue(
2795  Address(LValueAddress.getPointer(), LValueAddress.getElementType(),
2796  getContext().getDeclAlign(VD)),
2797  CapLVal.getType(), LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::Decl),
2798  CapLVal.getTBAAInfo());
2799  // Mark lvalue as nontemporal if the variable is marked as nontemporal
2800  // in simd context.
2801  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP &&
2802  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().isNontemporalDecl(VD))
2803  CapLVal.setNontemporal(/*Value=*/true);
2804  return CapLVal;
2805  }
2806 
2807  assert(isa<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl));
2808  Address addr = GetAddrOfBlockDecl(VD);
2809  return MakeAddrLValue(addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2810  }
2811  }
2812 
2813  // FIXME: We should be able to assert this for FunctionDecls as well!
2814  // FIXME: We should be able to assert this for all DeclRefExprs, not just
2815  // those with a valid source location.
2816  assert((ND->isUsed(false) || !isa<VarDecl>(ND) || E->isNonOdrUse() ||
2817  !E->getLocation().isValid()) &&
2818  "Should not use decl without marking it used!");
2819 
2820  if (ND->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>()) {
2821  const auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(ND);
2822  ConstantAddress Aliasee = CGM.GetWeakRefReference(VD);
2823  return MakeAddrLValue(Aliasee, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2824  }
2825 
2826  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
2827  // Check if this is a global variable.
2828  if (VD->hasLinkage() || VD->isStaticDataMember())
2829  return EmitGlobalVarDeclLValue(*this, E, VD);
2830 
2831  Address addr = Address::invalid();
2832 
2833  // The variable should generally be present in the local decl map.
2834  auto iter = LocalDeclMap.find(VD);
2835  if (iter != LocalDeclMap.end()) {
2836  addr = iter->second;
2837 
2838  // Otherwise, it might be static local we haven't emitted yet for
2839  // some reason; most likely, because it's in an outer function.
2840  } else if (VD->isStaticLocal()) {
2841  llvm::Constant *var = CGM.getOrCreateStaticVarDecl(
2842  *VD, CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD, /*IsConstant=*/false));
2843 
2844  // Force completion of static variable for SYCL since if it wasn't emitted
2845  // already that means it is defined in host code and its parent function
2846  // won't be emitted.
2847  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
2848  EmitStaticVarDecl(
2849  *VD, CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD, /*IsConstant=*/false));
2850 
2851  addr = Address(
2852  var, ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType()), getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
2853 
2854  // No other cases for now.
2855  } else {
2856  llvm_unreachable("DeclRefExpr for Decl not entered in LocalDeclMap?");
2857  }
2858 
2859 
2860  // Check for OpenMP threadprivate variables.
2861  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && !getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd &&
2862  VD->hasAttr<OMPThreadPrivateDeclAttr>()) {
2863  return EmitThreadPrivateVarDeclLValue(
2864  *this, VD, T, addr, getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType()),
2865  E->getExprLoc());
2866  }
2867 
2868  // Drill into block byref variables.
2869  bool isBlockByref = VD->isEscapingByref();
2870  if (isBlockByref) {
2871  addr = emitBlockByrefAddress(addr, VD);
2872  }
2873 
2874  // Drill into reference types.
2875  LValue LV = VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ?
2876  EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(addr, VD->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl) :
2877  MakeAddrLValue(addr, T, AlignmentSource::Decl);
2878 
2879  bool isLocalStorage = VD->hasLocalStorage();
2880 
2881  bool NonGCable = isLocalStorage &&
2882  !VD->getType()->isReferenceType() &&
2883  !isBlockByref;
2884  if (NonGCable) {
2885  LV.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
2886  LV.setNonGC(true);
2887  }
2888 
2889  bool isImpreciseLifetime =
2890  (isLocalStorage && !VD->hasAttr<ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr>());
2891  if (isImpreciseLifetime)
2892  LV.setARCPreciseLifetime(ARCImpreciseLifetime);
2893  setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
2894  return LV;
2895  }
2896 
2897  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND)) {
2898  LValue LV = EmitFunctionDeclLValue(*this, E, FD);
2899 
2900  // Emit debuginfo for the function declaration if the target wants to.
2901  if (getContext().getTargetInfo().allowDebugInfoForExternalRef()) {
2902  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = CGM.getModuleDebugInfo()) {
2903  auto *Fn =
2904  cast<llvm::Function>(LV.getPointer(*this)->stripPointerCasts());
2905  if (!Fn->getSubprogram())
2906  DI->EmitFunctionDecl(FD, FD->getLocation(), T, Fn);
2907  }
2908  }
2909 
2910  return LV;
2911  }
2912 
2913  // FIXME: While we're emitting a binding from an enclosing scope, all other
2914  // DeclRefExprs we see should be implicitly treated as if they also refer to
2915  // an enclosing scope.
2916  if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BindingDecl>(ND))
2917  return EmitLValue(BD->getBinding());
2918 
2919  // We can form DeclRefExprs naming GUID declarations when reconstituting
2920  // non-type template parameters into expressions.
2921  if (const auto *GD = dyn_cast<MSGuidDecl>(ND))
2922  return MakeAddrLValue(CGM.GetAddrOfMSGuidDecl(GD), T,
2923  AlignmentSource::Decl);
2924 
2925  if (const auto *TPO = dyn_cast<TemplateParamObjectDecl>(ND))
2926  return MakeAddrLValue(CGM.GetAddrOfTemplateParamObject(TPO), T,
2927  AlignmentSource::Decl);
2928 
2929  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled DeclRefExpr");
2930 }
2931 
2932 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitUnaryOpLValue(const UnaryOperator *E) {
2933  // __extension__ doesn't affect lvalue-ness.
2934  if (E->getOpcode() == UO_Extension)
2935  return EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
2936 
2937  QualType ExprTy = getContext().getCanonicalType(E->getSubExpr()->getType());
2938  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
2939  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown unary operator lvalue!");
2940  case UO_Deref: {
2941  QualType T = E->getSubExpr()->getType()->getPointeeType();
2942  assert(!T.isNull() && "CodeGenFunction::EmitUnaryOpLValue: Illegal type");
2943 
2944  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
2945  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
2946  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getSubExpr(), &BaseInfo,
2947  &TBAAInfo);
2948  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, T, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
2949  LV.getQuals().setAddressSpace(ExprTy.getAddressSpace());
2950 
2951  // We should not generate __weak write barrier on indirect reference
2952  // of a pointer to object; as in void foo (__weak id *param); *param = 0;
2953  // But, we continue to generate __strong write barrier on indirect write
2954  // into a pointer to object.
2955  if (getLangOpts().ObjC &&
2956  getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC &&
2957  LV.isObjCWeak())
2958  LV.setNonGC(!E->isOBJCGCCandidate(getContext()));
2959  return LV;
2960  }
2961  case UO_Real:
2962  case UO_Imag: {
2963  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
2964  assert(LV.isSimple() && "real/imag on non-ordinary l-value");
2965 
2966  // __real is valid on scalars. This is a faster way of testing that.
2967  // __imag can only produce an rvalue on scalars.
2968  if (E->getOpcode() == UO_Real &&
2969  !LV.getAddress(*this).getElementType()->isStructTy()) {
2970  assert(E->getSubExpr()->getType()->isArithmeticType());
2971  return LV;
2972  }
2973 
2974  QualType T = ExprTy->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
2975 
2976  Address Component =
2977  (E->getOpcode() == UO_Real
2978  ? emitAddrOfRealComponent(LV.getAddress(*this), LV.getType())
2979  : emitAddrOfImagComponent(LV.getAddress(*this), LV.getType()));
2980  LValue ElemLV = MakeAddrLValue(Component, T, LV.getBaseInfo(),
2981  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, T));
2982  ElemLV.getQuals().addQualifiers(LV.getQuals());
2983  return ElemLV;
2984  }
2985  case UO_PreInc:
2986  case UO_PreDec: {
2987  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
2988  bool isInc = E->getOpcode() == UO_PreInc;
2989 
2990  if (E->getType()->isAnyComplexType())
2991  EmitComplexPrePostIncDec(E, LV, isInc, true/*isPre*/);
2992  else
2993  EmitScalarPrePostIncDec(E, LV, isInc, true/*isPre*/);
2994  return LV;
2995  }
2996  }
2997 }

3001  E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);

3009 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPredefinedLValue(const PredefinedExpr *E) {
3010  auto SL = E->getFunctionName();
3011  assert(SL != nullptr && "No StringLiteral name in PredefinedExpr");
3012  StringRef FnName = CurFn->getName();
3013  if (FnName.startswith("\01"))
3014  FnName = FnName.substr(1);
3015  StringRef NameItems[] = {
3016  PredefinedExpr::getIdentKindName(E->getIdentKind()), FnName};
3017  std::string GVName = llvm::join(NameItems, NameItems + 2, ".");
3018  if (auto *BD = dyn_cast_or_null<BlockDecl>(CurCodeDecl)) {
3019  std::string Name = std::string(SL->getString());
3020  if (!Name.empty()) {
3021  unsigned Discriminator =
3022  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().getBlockId(BD, true);
3023  if (Discriminator)
3024  Name += "_" + Twine(Discriminator + 1).str();
3025  auto C = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(Name, GVName.c_str());
3026  return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3027  } else {
3028  auto C =
3029  CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(std::string(FnName), GVName.c_str());
3030  return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3031  }
3032  }
3033  auto C = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral(SL, GVName);
3034  return MakeAddrLValue(C, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
3035 }

3037 /// Emit a type description suitable for use by a runtime sanitizer library. The
3038 /// format of a type descriptor is
3039 ///
3040 /// \code
3041 /// { i16 TypeKind, i16 TypeInfo }
3042 /// \endcode
3043 ///
3044 /// followed by an array of i8 containing the type name. TypeKind is 0 for an
3045 /// integer, 1 for a floating point value, and -1 for anything else.
3046 llvm::Constant *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType T) {
3047  // Only emit each type's descriptor once.
3048  if (llvm::Constant *C = CGM.getTypeDescriptorFromMap(T))
3049  return C;
3050 
3051  uint16_t TypeKind = -1;
3052  uint16_t TypeInfo = 0;
3053 
3054  if (T->isIntegerType()) {
3055  TypeKind = 0;
3056  TypeInfo = (llvm::Log2_32(getContext().getTypeSize(T)) << 1) |
3057  (T->isSignedIntegerType() ? 1 : 0);
3058  } else if (T->isFloatingType()) {
3059  TypeKind = 1;
3060  TypeInfo = getContext().getTypeSize(T);
3061  }
3062 
3063  // Format the type name as if for a diagnostic, including quotes and
3064  // optionally an 'aka'.
3065  SmallString<32> Buffer;
3066  CGM.getDiags().ConvertArgToString(DiagnosticsEngine::ak_qualtype,
3067  (intptr_t)T.getAsOpaquePtr(),
3068  StringRef(), StringRef(), None, Buffer,
3069  None);
3070 
3071  llvm::Constant *Components[] = {
3072  Builder.getInt16(TypeKind), Builder.getInt16(TypeInfo),
3073  llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(getLLVMContext(), Buffer)
3074  };
3075  llvm::Constant *Descriptor = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Components);
3076 
3077  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3078  CGM.getModule(), Descriptor->getType(),
3079  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Descriptor);
3080  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3081  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(GV);
3082 
3083  // Remember the descriptor for this type.
3084  CGM.setTypeDescriptorInMap(T, GV);
3085 
3086  return GV;
3087 }
3088 
3089 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckValue(llvm::Value *V) {
3090  llvm::Type *TargetTy = IntPtrTy;
3091 
3092  if (V->getType() == TargetTy)
3093  return V;
3094 
3095  // Floating-point types which fit into intptr_t are bitcast to integers
3096  // and then passed directly (after zero-extension, if necessary).
3097  if (V->getType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
3098  unsigned Bits = V->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedSize();
3099  if (Bits <= TargetTy->getIntegerBitWidth())
3100  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(),
3101  Bits));
3102  }
3103 
3104  // Integers which fit in intptr_t are zero-extended and passed directly.
3105  if (V->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
3106  V->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth() <= TargetTy->getIntegerBitWidth())
3107  return Builder.CreateZExt(V, TargetTy);
3108 
3109  // Pointers are passed directly, everything else is passed by address.
3110  if (!V->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3111  Address Ptr = CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(V->getType());
3112  Builder.CreateStore(V, Ptr);
3113  V = Ptr.getPointer();
3114  }
3115  return Builder.CreatePtrToInt(V, TargetTy);
3116 }
3117 
3118 /// Emit a representation of a SourceLocation for passing to a handler
3119 /// in a sanitizer runtime library. The format for this data is:
3120 /// \code
3121 /// struct SourceLocation {
3122 /// const char *Filename;
3123 /// int32_t Line, Column;
3124 /// };
3125 /// \endcode
3126 /// For an invalid SourceLocation, the Filename pointer is null.
3127 llvm::Constant *CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckSourceLocation(SourceLocation Loc) {
3128  llvm::Constant *Filename;
3129  int Line, Column;
3130 
3131  PresumedLoc PLoc = getContext().getSourceManager().getPresumedLoc(Loc);
3132  if (PLoc.isValid()) {
3133  StringRef FilenameString = PLoc.getFilename();
3134 
3135  int PathComponentsToStrip =
3136  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCheckPathComponentsToStrip;
3137  if (PathComponentsToStrip < 0) {
3138  assert(PathComponentsToStrip != INT_MIN);
3139  int PathComponentsToKeep = -PathComponentsToStrip;
3140  auto I = llvm::sys::path::rbegin(FilenameString);
3141  auto E = llvm::sys::path::rend(FilenameString);
3142  while (I != E && --PathComponentsToKeep)
3143  ++I;
3144 
3145  FilenameString = FilenameString.substr(I - E);
3146  } else if (PathComponentsToStrip > 0) {
3147  auto I = llvm::sys::path::begin(FilenameString);
3148  auto E = llvm::sys::path::end(FilenameString);
3149  while (I != E && PathComponentsToStrip--)
3150  ++I;
3151 
3152  if (I != E)
3153  FilenameString =
3154  FilenameString.substr(I - llvm::sys::path::begin(FilenameString));
3155  else
3156  FilenameString = llvm::sys::path::filename(FilenameString);
3157  }
3158 
3159  auto FilenameGV =
3160  CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(std::string(FilenameString), ".src");
3161  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(
3162  cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(FilenameGV.getPointer()));
3163  Filename = FilenameGV.getPointer();
3164  Line = PLoc.getLine();
3165  Column = PLoc.getColumn();
3166  } else {
3167  Filename = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int8PtrTy);
3168  Line = Column = 0;
3169  }
3170 
3171  llvm::Constant *Data[] = {Filename, Builder.getInt32(Line),
3172  Builder.getInt32(Column)};
3173 
3174  return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Data);
3175 }

3177 namespace {
3178 /// Specify under what conditions this check can be recovered
3179 enum class CheckRecoverableKind {
3180  /// Always terminate program execution if this check fails.
3181  Unrecoverable,
3182  /// Check supports recovering, runtime has both fatal (noreturn) and
3183  /// non-fatal handlers for this check.
3184  Recoverable,
3185  /// Runtime conditionally aborts, always need to support recovery.
3186  AlwaysRecoverable
3187 };
3188 }
3189 
3190 static CheckRecoverableKind getRecoverableKind(SanitizerMask Kind) {
3191  assert(Kind.countPopulation() == 1);
3192  if (Kind == SanitizerKind::Function || Kind == SanitizerKind::Vptr)
3193  return CheckRecoverableKind::AlwaysRecoverable;
3194  else if (Kind == SanitizerKind::Return || Kind == SanitizerKind::Unreachable)
3195  return CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable;
3196  else
3197  return CheckRecoverableKind::Recoverable;
3198 }

3200 namespace {
3201 struct SanitizerHandlerInfo {
3202  char const *const Name;
3203  unsigned Version;
3204 };
3205 }
3206 
3207 const SanitizerHandlerInfo SanitizerHandlers[] = {
3208 #define SANITIZER_CHECK(Enum, Name, Version) {#Name, Version},
3209  LIST_SANITIZER_CHECKS
3210 #undef SANITIZER_CHECK
3211 };

3213 static void emitCheckHandlerCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3214  llvm::FunctionType *FnType,
3215  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> FnArgs,
3216  SanitizerHandler CheckHandler,
3217  CheckRecoverableKind RecoverKind, bool IsFatal,
3218  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB) {
3219  assert(IsFatal || RecoverKind != CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable);
3220  Optional<ApplyDebugLocation> DL;
3221  if (!CGF.Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation()) {
3222  // Ensure that the call has at least an artificial debug location.
3223  DL.emplace(CGF, SourceLocation());
3224  }
3225  bool NeedsAbortSuffix =
3226  IsFatal && RecoverKind != CheckRecoverableKind::Unrecoverable;
3227  bool MinimalRuntime = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMinimalRuntime;
3228  const SanitizerHandlerInfo &CheckInfo = SanitizerHandlers[CheckHandler];
3229  const StringRef CheckName = CheckInfo.Name;
3230  std::string FnName = "__ubsan_handle_" + CheckName.str();
3231  if (CheckInfo.Version && !MinimalRuntime)
3232  FnName += "_v" + llvm::utostr(CheckInfo.Version);
3233  if (MinimalRuntime)
3234  FnName += "_minimal";
3235  if (NeedsAbortSuffix)
3236  FnName += "_abort";
3237  bool MayReturn =
3238  !IsFatal || RecoverKind == CheckRecoverableKind::AlwaysRecoverable;
3239 
3240  llvm::AttrBuilder B(CGF.getLLVMContext());
3241  if (!MayReturn) {
3242  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoReturn)
3243  .addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
3244  }
3245  B.addUWTableAttr(llvm::UWTableKind::Default);
3246 
3247  llvm::FunctionCallee Fn = CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
3248  FnType, FnName,
3249  llvm::AttributeList::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(),
3250  llvm::AttributeList::FunctionIndex, B),
3251  /*Local=*/true);
3252  llvm::CallInst *HandlerCall = CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn, FnArgs);
3253  if (!MayReturn) {
3254  HandlerCall->setDoesNotReturn();
3255  CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3256  } else {
3257  CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
3258  }
3259 }
3260 
3261 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCheck(
3262  ArrayRef<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>> Checked,
3263  SanitizerHandler CheckHandler, ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> StaticArgs,
3264  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> DynamicArgs) {
3265  assert(IsSanitizerScope);
3266  assert(Checked.size() > 0);
3267  assert(CheckHandler >= 0 &&
3268  size_t(CheckHandler) < llvm::array_lengthof(SanitizerHandlers));
3269  const StringRef CheckName = SanitizerHandlers[CheckHandler].Name;
3270 
3271  llvm::Value *FatalCond = nullptr;
3272  llvm::Value *RecoverableCond = nullptr;
3273  llvm::Value *TrapCond = nullptr;
3274  for (int i = 0, n = Checked.size(); i < n; ++i) {
3275  llvm::Value *Check = Checked[i].first;
3276  // -fsanitize-trap= overrides -fsanitize-recover=.
3277  llvm::Value *&Cond =
3278  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(Checked[i].second)
3279  ? TrapCond
3280  : CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeRecover.has(Checked[i].second)
3281  ? RecoverableCond
3282  : FatalCond;
3283  Cond = Cond ? Builder.CreateAnd(Cond, Check) : Check;
3284  }
3285 
3286  if (TrapCond)
3287  EmitTrapCheck(TrapCond, CheckHandler);
3288  if (!FatalCond && !RecoverableCond)
3289  return;
3290 
3291  llvm::Value *JointCond;
3292  if (FatalCond && RecoverableCond)
3293  JointCond = Builder.CreateAnd(FatalCond, RecoverableCond);
3294  else
3295  JointCond = FatalCond ? FatalCond : RecoverableCond;
3296  assert(JointCond);
3297 
3298  CheckRecoverableKind RecoverKind = getRecoverableKind(Checked[0].second);
3299  assert(SanOpts.has(Checked[0].second));
3300 #ifndef NDEBUG
3301  for (int i = 1, n = Checked.size(); i < n; ++i) {
3302  assert(RecoverKind == getRecoverableKind(Checked[i].second) &&
3303  "All recoverable kinds in a single check must be same!");
3304  assert(SanOpts.has(Checked[i].second));
3305  }
3306 #endif
3307 
3308  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
3309  llvm::BasicBlock *Handlers = createBasicBlock("handler." + CheckName);
3310  llvm::Instruction *Branch = Builder.CreateCondBr(JointCond, Cont, Handlers);
3311  // Give hint that we very much don't expect to execute the handler
3312  // Value chosen to match UR_NONTAKEN_WEIGHT, see BranchProbabilityInfo.cpp
3313  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
3314  llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createBranchWeights((1U << 20) - 1, 1);
3315  Branch->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_prof, Node);
3316  EmitBlock(Handlers);
3317 
3318  // Handler functions take an i8* pointing to the (handler-specific) static
3319  // information block, followed by a sequence of intptr_t arguments
3320  // representing operand values.
3321  SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 4> Args;
3322  SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 4> ArgTypes;
3323  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMinimalRuntime) {
3324  Args.reserve(DynamicArgs.size() + 1);
3325  ArgTypes.reserve(DynamicArgs.size() + 1);
3326 
3327  // Emit handler arguments and create handler function type.
3328  if (!StaticArgs.empty()) {
3329  llvm::Constant *Info = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(StaticArgs);
3330  auto *InfoPtr =
3331  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Info->getType(), false,
3332  llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Info);
3333  InfoPtr->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3334  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(InfoPtr);
3335  Args.push_back(Builder.CreateBitCast(InfoPtr, Int8PtrTy));
3336  ArgTypes.push_back(Int8PtrTy);
3337  }
3338 
3339  for (size_t i = 0, n = DynamicArgs.size(); i != n; ++i) {
3340  Args.push_back(EmitCheckValue(DynamicArgs[i]));
3341  ArgTypes.push_back(IntPtrTy);
3342  }
3343  }
3344 
3345  llvm::FunctionType *FnType =
3346  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, ArgTypes, false);
3347 
3348  if (!FatalCond || !RecoverableCond) {
3349  // Simple case: we need to generate a single handler call, either
3350  // fatal, or non-fatal.
3351  emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind,
3352  (FatalCond != nullptr), Cont);
3353  } else {
3354  // Emit two handler calls: first one for set of unrecoverable checks,
3355  // another one for recoverable.
3356  llvm::BasicBlock *NonFatalHandlerBB =
3357  createBasicBlock("non_fatal." + CheckName);
3358  llvm::BasicBlock *FatalHandlerBB = createBasicBlock("fatal." + CheckName);
3359  Builder.CreateCondBr(FatalCond, NonFatalHandlerBB, FatalHandlerBB);
3360  EmitBlock(FatalHandlerBB);
3361  emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind, true,
3362  NonFatalHandlerBB);
3363  EmitBlock(NonFatalHandlerBB);
3364  emitCheckHandlerCall(*this, FnType, Args, CheckHandler, RecoverKind, false,
3365  Cont);
3366  }
3367 
3368  EmitBlock(Cont);
3369 }
3370 
3371 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiSlowPathCheck(
3372  SanitizerMask Kind, llvm::Value *Cond, llvm::ConstantInt *TypeId,
3373  llvm::Value *Ptr, ArrayRef<llvm::Constant *> StaticArgs) {
3374  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cfi.cont");
3375 
3376  llvm::BasicBlock *CheckBB = createBasicBlock("cfi.slowpath");
3377  llvm::BranchInst *BI = Builder.CreateCondBr(Cond, Cont, CheckBB);
3378 
3379  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
3380  llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createBranchWeights((1U << 20) - 1, 1);
3381  BI->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_prof, Node);
3382 
3383  EmitBlock(CheckBB);
3384 
3385  bool WithDiag = !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(Kind);
3386 
3387  llvm::CallInst *CheckCall;
3388  llvm::FunctionCallee SlowPathFn;
3389  if (WithDiag) {
3390  llvm::Constant *Info = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(StaticArgs);
3391  auto *InfoPtr =
3392  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Info->getType(), false,
3393  llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage, Info);
3394  InfoPtr->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3395  CGM.getSanitizerMetadata()->disableSanitizerForGlobal(InfoPtr);
3396 
3397  SlowPathFn = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertFunction(
3398  "__cfi_slowpath_diag",
3399  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy},
3400  false));
3401  CheckCall = Builder.CreateCall(
3402  SlowPathFn, {TypeId, Ptr, Builder.CreateBitCast(InfoPtr, Int8PtrTy)});
3403  } else {
3404  SlowPathFn = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertFunction(
3405  "__cfi_slowpath",
3406  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy}, false));
3407  CheckCall = Builder.CreateCall(SlowPathFn, {TypeId, Ptr});
3408  }
3409 
3410  CGM.setDSOLocal(
3411  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(SlowPathFn.getCallee()->stripPointerCasts()));
3412  CheckCall->setDoesNotThrow();
3413 
3414  EmitBlock(Cont);
3415 }

3417 // Emit a stub for __cfi_check function so that the linker knows about this
3418 // symbol in LTO mode.
3419 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiCheckStub() {
3420  llvm::Module *M = &CGM.getModule();
3421  auto &Ctx = M->getContext();
3422  llvm::Function *F = llvm::Function::Create(
3423  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {Int64Ty, Int8PtrTy, Int8PtrTy}, false),
3424  llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, "__cfi_check", M);
3425  CGM.setDSOLocal(F);
3426  llvm::BasicBlock *BB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "entry", F);
3427  // FIXME: consider emitting an intrinsic call like
3428  // call void @llvm.cfi_check(i64 %0, i8* %1, i8* %2)
3429  // which can be lowered in CrossDSOCFI pass to the actual contents of
3430  // __cfi_check. This would allow inlining of __cfi_check calls.
3431  llvm::CallInst::Create(
3432  llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, llvm::Intrinsic::trap), "", BB);
3433  llvm::ReturnInst::Create(Ctx, nullptr, BB);
3434 }
3435 
3436 // This function is basically a switch over the CFI failure kind, which is
3437 // extracted from CFICheckFailData (1st function argument). Each case is either
3438 // llvm.trap or a call to one of the two runtime handlers, based on
3439 // -fsanitize-trap and -fsanitize-recover settings. Default case (invalid
3440 // failure kind) traps, but this should really never happen. CFICheckFailData
3441 // can be nullptr if the calling module has -fsanitize-trap behavior for this
3442 // check kind; in this case __cfi_check_fail traps as well.
3443 void CodeGenFunction::EmitCfiCheckFail() {
3444  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3445  FunctionArgList Args;
3446  ImplicitParamDecl ArgData(getContext(), getContext().VoidPtrTy,
3447  ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3448  ImplicitParamDecl ArgAddr(getContext(), getContext().VoidPtrTy,
3449  ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
3450  Args.push_back(&ArgData);
3451  Args.push_back(&ArgAddr);
3452 
3453  const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
3454  CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(getContext().VoidTy, Args);
3455 
3456  llvm::Function *F = llvm::Function::Create(
3457  llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, {VoidPtrTy, VoidPtrTy}, false),
3458  llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage, "__cfi_check_fail", &CGM.getModule());
3459 
3460  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI, F, /*IsThunk=*/false);
3461  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(nullptr, F);
3462  F->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
3463 
3464  StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), CGM.getContext().VoidTy, F, FI, Args,
3465  SourceLocation());
3466 
3467  // This function is not affected by NoSanitizeList. This function does
3468  // not have a source location, but "src:*" would still apply. Revert any
3469  // changes to SanOpts made in StartFunction.
3470  SanOpts = CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize;
3471 
3472  llvm::Value *Data =
3473  EmitLoadOfScalar(GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ArgData), /*Volatile=*/false,
3474  CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy, ArgData.getLocation());
3475  llvm::Value *Addr =
3476  EmitLoadOfScalar(GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ArgAddr), /*Volatile=*/false,
3477  CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy, ArgAddr.getLocation());
3478 
3479  // Data == nullptr means the calling module has trap behaviour for this check.
3480  llvm::Value *DataIsNotNullPtr =
3481  Builder.CreateICmpNE(Data, llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(Int8PtrTy));
3482  EmitTrapCheck(DataIsNotNullPtr, SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail);
3483 
3484  llvm::StructType *SourceLocationTy =
3485  llvm::StructType::get(VoidPtrTy, Int32Ty, Int32Ty);
3486  llvm::StructType *CfiCheckFailDataTy =
3487  llvm::StructType::get(Int8Ty, SourceLocationTy, VoidPtrTy);
3488 
3489  llvm::Value *V = Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(
3490  CfiCheckFailDataTy,
3491  Builder.CreatePointerCast(Data, CfiCheckFailDataTy->getPointerTo(0)), 0,
3492  0);
3493 
3494  Address CheckKindAddr(V, Int8Ty, getIntAlign());
3495  llvm::Value *CheckKind = Builder.CreateLoad(CheckKindAddr);
3496 
3497  llvm::Value *AllVtables = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(
3498  CGM.getLLVMContext(),
3499  llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables"));
3500  llvm::Value *ValidVtable = Builder.CreateZExt(
3501  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test),
3502  {Addr, AllVtables}),
3503  IntPtrTy);
3504 
3505  const std::pair<int, SanitizerMask> CheckKinds[] = {
3506  {CFITCK_VCall, SanitizerKind::CFIVCall},
3507  {CFITCK_NVCall, SanitizerKind::CFINVCall},
3508  {CFITCK_DerivedCast, SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast},
3509  {CFITCK_UnrelatedCast, SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast},
3510  {CFITCK_ICall, SanitizerKind::CFIICall}};
3511 
3512  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 5> Checks;
3513  for (auto CheckKindMaskPair : CheckKinds) {
3514  int Kind = CheckKindMaskPair.first;
3515  SanitizerMask Mask = CheckKindMaskPair.second;
3516  llvm::Value *Cond =
3517  Builder.CreateICmpNE(CheckKind, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, Kind));
3518  if (CGM.getLangOpts().Sanitize.has(Mask))
3519  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(Cond, Mask), SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, {},
3520  {Data, Addr, ValidVtable});
3521  else
3522  EmitTrapCheck(Cond, SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail);
3523  }
3524 
3525  FinishFunction();
3526  // The only reference to this function will be created during LTO link.
3527  // Make sure it survives until then.
3528  CGM.addUsedGlobal(F);
3529 }

3531 void CodeGenFunction::EmitUnreachable(SourceLocation Loc) {
3532  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Unreachable)) {
3533  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
3534  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(static_cast<llvm::Value *>(Builder.getFalse()),
3535  SanitizerKind::Unreachable),
3536  SanitizerHandler::BuiltinUnreachable,
3537  EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc), None);
3538  }
3539  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3540 }
3541 
3542 void CodeGenFunction::EmitTrapCheck(llvm::Value *Checked,
3543  SanitizerHandler CheckHandlerID) {
3544  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
3545 
3546  // If we're optimizing, collapse all calls to trap down to just one per
3547  // check-type per function to save on code size.
3548  if (TrapBBs.size() <= CheckHandlerID)
3549  TrapBBs.resize(CheckHandlerID + 1);
3550  llvm::BasicBlock *&TrapBB = TrapBBs[CheckHandlerID];
3551 
3552  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel || !TrapBB) {
3553  TrapBB = createBasicBlock("trap");
3554  Builder.CreateCondBr(Checked, Cont, TrapBB);
3555  EmitBlock(TrapBB);
3556 
3557  llvm::CallInst *TrapCall =
3558  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::ubsantrap),
3559  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, CheckHandlerID));
3560 
3561  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName.empty()) {
3562  auto A = llvm::Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), "trap-func-name",
3563  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName);
3564  TrapCall->addFnAttr(A);
3565  }
3566  TrapCall->setDoesNotReturn();
3567  TrapCall->setDoesNotThrow();
3568  Builder.CreateUnreachable();
3569  } else {
3570  auto Call = TrapBB->begin();
3571  assert(isa<llvm::CallInst>(Call) && "Expected call in trap BB");
3572 
3573  Call->applyMergedLocation(Call->getDebugLoc(),
3574  Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation());
3575  Builder.CreateCondBr(Checked, Cont, TrapBB);
3576  }
3577 
3578  EmitBlock(Cont);
3579 }
3580 
3581 llvm::CallInst *CodeGenFunction::EmitTrapCall(llvm::Intrinsic::ID IntrID) {
3582  llvm::CallInst *TrapCall =
3583  Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(IntrID));
3584 
3585  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName.empty()) {
3586  auto A = llvm::Attribute::get(getLLVMContext(), "trap-func-name",
3587  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().TrapFuncName);
3588  TrapCall->addFnAttr(A);
3589  }
3590 
3591  return TrapCall;
3592 }
3593 
3594 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitArrayToPointerDecay(const Expr *E,
3595  LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
3596  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
3597  assert(E->getType()->isArrayType() &&
3598  "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
3599 
3600  // Expressions of array type can't be bitfields or vector elements.
3601  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E);
3602  Address Addr = LV.getAddress(*this);
3603 
3604  // If the array type was an incomplete type, we need to make sure
3605  // the decay ends up being the right type.
3606  llvm::Type *NewTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
3607  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, NewTy);
3608 
3609  // Note that VLA pointers are always decayed, so we don't need to do
3610  // anything here.
3611  if (!E->getType()->isVariableArrayType()) {
3612  assert(isa<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType()) &&
3613  "Expected pointer to array");
3614  Addr = Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(Addr, 0, "arraydecay");
3615  }
3616 
3617  // The result of this decay conversion points to an array element within the
3618  // base lvalue. However, since TBAA currently does not support representing
3619  // accesses to elements of member arrays, we conservatively represent accesses
3620  // to the pointee object as if it had no any base lvalue specified.
3621  // TODO: Support TBAA for member arrays.
3622  QualType EltType = E->getType()->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe()->getElementType();
3623  if (BaseInfo) *BaseInfo = LV.getBaseInfo();
3624  if (TBAAInfo) *TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAAccessInfo(EltType);
3625 
3626  return Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ConvertTypeForMem(EltType));
3627 }

3629 /// isSimpleArrayDecayOperand - If the specified expr is a simple decay from an
3630 /// array to pointer, return the array subexpression.
3631 static const Expr *isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(const Expr *E) {
3632  // If this isn't just an array->pointer decay, bail out.
3633  const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(E);
3634  if (!CE || CE->getCastKind() != CK_ArrayToPointerDecay)
3635  return nullptr;
3636 
3637  // If this is a decay from variable width array, bail out.
3638  const Expr *SubExpr = CE->getSubExpr();
3639  if (SubExpr->getType()->isVariableArrayType())
3640  return nullptr;
3641 
3642  return SubExpr;
3643 }

3645 static llvm::Value *emitArraySubscriptGEP(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3646  llvm::Type *elemType,
3647  llvm::Value *ptr,
3648  ArrayRef<llvm::Value*> indices,
3649  bool inbounds,
3650  bool signedIndices,
3651  SourceLocation loc,
3652  const llvm::Twine &name = "arrayidx") {
3653  if (inbounds) {
3654  return CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(elemType, ptr, indices, signedIndices,
3655  CodeGenFunction::NotSubtraction, loc,
3656  name);
3657  } else {
3658  return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(elemType, ptr, indices, name);
3659  }
3660 }
