3662 static CharUnits getArrayElementAlign(CharUnits arrayAlign,
3663  llvm::Value *idx,
3664  CharUnits eltSize) {
3665  // If we have a constant index, we can use the exact offset of the
3666  // element we're accessing.
3667  if (auto constantIdx = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx)) {
3668  CharUnits offset = constantIdx->getZExtValue() * eltSize;
3669  return arrayAlign.alignmentAtOffset(offset);
3670 
3671  // Otherwise, use the worst-case alignment for any element.
3672  } else {
3673  return arrayAlign.alignmentOfArrayElement(eltSize);
3674  }
3675 }
3676 
3677 static QualType getFixedSizeElementType(const ASTContext &ctx,
3678  const VariableArrayType *vla) {
3679  QualType eltType;
3680  do {
3681  eltType = vla->getElementType();
3682  } while ((vla = ctx.getAsVariableArrayType(eltType)));
3683  return eltType;
3684 }
3685 
3686 static void AddIVDepMetadata(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const ValueDecl *ArrayDecl,
3687  llvm::Value *EltPtr) {
3688  if (!ArrayDecl)
3689  return;
3690 
3691  // Only handle actual GEPs, ConstantExpr GEPs don't have metadata.
3692  if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<llvm::GetElementPtrInst>(EltPtr))
3693  CGF.LoopStack.addIVDepMetadata(ArrayDecl, GEP);
3694 }
3695 
3696 /// Given an array base, check whether its member access belongs to a record
3697 /// with preserve_access_index attribute or not.
3698 static bool IsPreserveAIArrayBase(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *ArrayBase) {
3699  if (!ArrayBase || !CGF.getDebugInfo())
3700  return false;
3701 
3702  // Only support base as either a MemberExpr or DeclRefExpr.
3703  // DeclRefExpr to cover cases like:
3704  // struct s { int a; int b[10]; };
3705  // struct s *p;
3706  // p[1].a
3707  // p[1] will generate a DeclRefExpr and p[1].a is a MemberExpr.
3708  // p->b[5] is a MemberExpr example.
3709  const Expr *E = ArrayBase->IgnoreImpCasts();
3710  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
3711  return ME->getMemberDecl()->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>();
3712 
3713  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
3714  const auto *VarDef = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
3715  if (!VarDef)
3716  return false;
3717 
3718  const auto *PtrT = VarDef->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
3719  if (!PtrT)
3720  return false;
3721 
3722  const auto *PointeeT = PtrT->getPointeeType()
3723  ->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
3724  if (const auto *RecT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(PointeeT))
3725  return RecT->getDecl()->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>();
3726  return false;
3727  }
3728 
3729  return false;
3730 }
3731 
3732 static Address emitArraySubscriptGEP(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address addr,
3733  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> indices,
3734  QualType eltType, bool inbounds,
3735  bool signedIndices, SourceLocation loc,
3736  QualType *arrayType = nullptr,
3737  const Expr *Base = nullptr,
3738  const llvm::Twine &name = "arrayidx",
3739  const ValueDecl *arrayDecl = nullptr) {
3740  // All the indices except that last must be zero.
3741 #ifndef NDEBUG
3742  for (auto idx : indices.drop_back())
3743  assert(isa<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx) &&
3744  cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(idx)->isZero());
3745 #endif
3746 
3747  // Determine the element size of the statically-sized base. This is
3748  // the thing that the indices are expressed in terms of.
3749  if (auto vla = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(eltType)) {
3750  eltType = getFixedSizeElementType(CGF.getContext(), vla);
3751  }
3752 
3753  // We can use that to compute the best alignment of the element.
3754  CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(eltType);
3755  CharUnits eltAlign =
3756  getArrayElementAlign(addr.getAlignment(), indices.back(), eltSize);
3757 
3758  llvm::Value *eltPtr;
3759  auto LastIndex = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(indices.back());
3760  if (!LastIndex ||
3761  (!CGF.IsInPreservedAIRegion && !IsPreserveAIArrayBase(CGF, Base))) {
3762  eltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
3763  CGF, addr.getElementType(), addr.getPointer(), indices, inbounds,
3764  signedIndices, loc, name);
3765  AddIVDepMetadata(CGF, arrayDecl, eltPtr);
3766  } else {
3767  // Remember the original array subscript for bpf target
3768  unsigned idx = LastIndex->getZExtValue();
3769  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = nullptr;
3770  if (arrayType)
3771  DbgInfo = CGF.getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(*arrayType, loc);
3772  eltPtr = CGF.Builder.CreatePreserveArrayAccessIndex(addr.getElementType(),
3773  addr.getPointer(),
3774  indices.size() - 1,
3775  idx, DbgInfo);
3776  }
3777 
3778  return Address(eltPtr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(eltType), eltAlign);
3779 }
3780 
3781 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitArraySubscriptExpr(const ArraySubscriptExpr *E,
3782  bool Accessed) {
3783  // The index must always be an integer, which is not an aggregate. Emit it
3784  // in lexical order (this complexity is, sadly, required by C++17).
3785  llvm::Value *IdxPre =
3786  (E->getLHS() == E->getIdx()) ? EmitScalarExpr(E->getIdx()) : nullptr;
3787  bool SignedIndices = false;
3788  auto EmitIdxAfterBase = [&, IdxPre](bool Promote) -> llvm::Value * {
3789  auto *Idx = IdxPre;
3790  if (E->getLHS() != E->getIdx()) {
3791  assert(E->getRHS() == E->getIdx() && "index was neither LHS nor RHS");
3792  Idx = EmitScalarExpr(E->getIdx());
3793  }
3794 
3795  QualType IdxTy = E->getIdx()->getType();
3796  bool IdxSigned = IdxTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3797  SignedIndices |= IdxSigned;
3798 
3799  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
3800  EmitBoundsCheck(E, E->getBase(), Idx, IdxTy, Accessed);
3801 
3802  // Extend or truncate the index type to 32 or 64-bits.
3803  if (Promote && Idx->getType() != IntPtrTy)
3804  Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(Idx, IntPtrTy, IdxSigned, "idxprom");
3805 
3806  return Idx;
3807  };
3808  IdxPre = nullptr;
3809 
3810  // If the base is a vector type, then we are forming a vector element lvalue
3811  // with this subscript.
3812  if (E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType() &&
3813  !isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E->getBase())) {
3814  // Emit the vector as an lvalue to get its address.
3815  LValue LHS = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
3816  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/false);
3817  assert(LHS.isSimple() && "Can only subscript lvalue vectors here!");
3818  return LValue::MakeVectorElt(LHS.getAddress(*this), Idx,
3819  E->getBase()->getType(), LHS.getBaseInfo(),
3820  TBAAAccessInfo());
3821  }
3822 
3823  // All the other cases basically behave like simple offsetting.
3824 
3825  // Handle the extvector case we ignored above.
3826  if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E->getBase())) {
3827  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
3828  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
3829  Address Addr = EmitExtVectorElementLValue(LV);
3830 
3831  QualType EltType = LV.getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
3832  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, EltType, /*inbounds*/ true,
3833  SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc());
3834  return MakeAddrLValue(Addr, EltType, LV.getBaseInfo(),
3835  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, EltType));
3836  }
3837 
3838  LValueBaseInfo EltBaseInfo;
3839  TBAAAccessInfo EltTBAAInfo;
3840  Address Addr = Address::invalid();
3841  if (const VariableArrayType *vla =
3842  getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(E->getType())) {
3843  // The base must be a pointer, which is not an aggregate. Emit
3844  // it. It needs to be emitted first in case it's what captures
3845  // the VLA bounds.
3846  Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
3847  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
3848 
3849  // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
3850  llvm::Value *numElements = getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
3851 
3852  // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
3853  // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
3854  // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
3855  // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
3856  if (getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined()) {
3857  Idx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, numElements);
3858  } else {
3859  Idx = Builder.CreateNSWMul(Idx, numElements);
3860  }
3861 
3862  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, vla->getElementType(),
3863  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
3864  SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc());
3865 
3866  } else if (const ObjCObjectType *OIT = E->getType()->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()){
3867  // Indexing over an interface, as in "NSString *P; P[4];"
3868 
3869  // Emit the base pointer.
3870  Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
3871  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
3872 
3873  CharUnits InterfaceSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(OIT);
3874  llvm::Value *InterfaceSizeVal =
3875  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Idx->getType(), InterfaceSize.getQuantity());
3876 
3877  llvm::Value *ScaledIdx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, InterfaceSizeVal);
3878 
3879  // We don't necessarily build correct LLVM struct types for ObjC
3880  // interfaces, so we can't rely on GEP to do this scaling
3881  // correctly, so we need to cast to i8*. FIXME: is this actually
3882  // true? A lot of other things in the fragile ABI would break...
3883  llvm::Type *OrigBaseElemTy = Addr.getElementType();
3884  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, Int8Ty);
3885 
3886  // Do the GEP.
3887  CharUnits EltAlign =
3888  getArrayElementAlign(Addr.getAlignment(), Idx, InterfaceSize);
3889  llvm::Value *EltPtr =
3890  emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr.getElementType(), Addr.getPointer(),
3891  ScaledIdx, false, SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc());
3892  Addr = Address(EltPtr, Addr.getElementType(), EltAlign);
3893 
3894  // Cast back.
3895  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, OrigBaseElemTy);
3896  } else if (const Expr *Array = isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(E->getBase())) {
3897  // If this is A[i] where A is an array, the frontend will have decayed the
3898  // base to be a ArrayToPointerDecay implicit cast. While correct, it is
3899  // inefficient at -O0 to emit a "gep A, 0, 0" when codegen'ing it, then a
3900  // "gep x, i" here. Emit one "gep A, 0, i".
3901  assert(Array->getType()->isArrayType() &&
3902  "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
3903  LValue ArrayLV;
3904  // For simple multidimensional array indexing, set the 'accessed' flag for
3905  // better bounds-checking of the base expression.
3906  if (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Array))
3907  ArrayLV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(ASE, /*Accessed*/ true);
3908  else
3909  ArrayLV = EmitLValue(Array);
3910  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
3911 
3912  const ValueDecl *ArrayDecl = nullptr;
3913  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Array->IgnoreParenCasts()))
3914  ArrayDecl = DRE->getDecl();
3915  else if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Array->IgnoreParenCasts()))
3916  ArrayDecl = ME->getMemberDecl();
3917 
3918  // Propagate the alignment from the array itself to the result.
3919  QualType arrayType = Array->getType();
3920  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
3921  *this, ArrayLV.getAddress(*this), {CGM.getSize(CharUnits::Zero()), Idx},
3922  E->getType(), !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(), SignedIndices,
3923  E->getExprLoc(), &arrayType, E->getBase(), "arrayidx", ArrayDecl);
3924  EltBaseInfo = ArrayLV.getBaseInfo();
3925  EltTBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(ArrayLV, E->getType());
3926  } else {
3927  // The base must be a pointer; emit it with an estimate of its alignment.
3928  Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &EltBaseInfo, &EltTBAAInfo);
3929  auto *Idx = EmitIdxAfterBase(/*Promote*/true);
3930  QualType ptrType = E->getBase()->getType();
3931 
3932  const ValueDecl *PtrDecl = nullptr;
3933  if (const auto *DRE =
3934  dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts()))
3935  PtrDecl = DRE->getDecl();
3936  else if (const auto *ME =
3937  dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts()))
3938  PtrDecl = ME->getMemberDecl();
3939 
3940  Addr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Addr, Idx, E->getType(),
3941  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
3942  SignedIndices, E->getExprLoc(), &ptrType,
3943  E->getBase(), "arrayidx", PtrDecl);
3944  }
3945 
3946  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, E->getType(), EltBaseInfo, EltTBAAInfo);
3947 
3948  if (getLangOpts().ObjC &&
3949  getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
3950  LV.setNonGC(!E->isOBJCGCCandidate(getContext()));
3951  setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
3952  }
3953  return LV;
3954 }
3955 
3956 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitMatrixSubscriptExpr(const MatrixSubscriptExpr *E) {
3957  assert(
3958  !E->isIncomplete() &&
3959  "incomplete matrix subscript expressions should be rejected during Sema");
3960  LValue Base = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
3961  llvm::Value *RowIdx = EmitScalarExpr(E->getRowIdx());
3962  llvm::Value *ColIdx = EmitScalarExpr(E->getColumnIdx());
3963  llvm::Value *NumRows = Builder.getIntN(
3964  RowIdx->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits(),
3965  E->getBase()->getType()->castAs<ConstantMatrixType>()->getNumRows());
3966  llvm::Value *FinalIdx =
3967  Builder.CreateAdd(Builder.CreateMul(ColIdx, NumRows), RowIdx);
3968  return LValue::MakeMatrixElt(
3969  MaybeConvertMatrixAddress(Base.getAddress(*this), *this), FinalIdx,
3970  E->getBase()->getType(), Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
3971 }
3972 
3973 static Address emitOMPArraySectionBase(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *Base,
3974  LValueBaseInfo &BaseInfo,
3975  TBAAAccessInfo &TBAAInfo,
3976  QualType BaseTy, QualType ElTy,
3977  bool IsLowerBound) {
3978  LValue BaseLVal;
3979  if (auto *ASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(Base->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
3980  BaseLVal = CGF.EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(ASE, IsLowerBound);
3981  if (BaseTy->isArrayType()) {
3982  Address Addr = BaseLVal.getAddress(CGF);
3983  BaseInfo = BaseLVal.getBaseInfo();
3984 
3985  // If the array type was an incomplete type, we need to make sure
3986  // the decay ends up being the right type.
3987  llvm::Type *NewTy = CGF.ConvertType(BaseTy);
3988  Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, NewTy);
3989 
3990  // Note that VLA pointers are always decayed, so we don't need to do
3991  // anything here.
3992  if (!BaseTy->isVariableArrayType()) {
3993  assert(isa<llvm::ArrayType>(Addr.getElementType()) &&
3994  "Expected pointer to array");
3995  Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(Addr, 0, "arraydecay");
3996  }
3997 
3998  return CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr,
3999  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ElTy));
4000  }
4001  LValueBaseInfo TypeBaseInfo;
4002  TBAAAccessInfo TypeTBAAInfo;
4003  CharUnits Align =
4004  CGF.CGM.getNaturalTypeAlignment(ElTy, &TypeBaseInfo, &TypeTBAAInfo);
4005  BaseInfo.mergeForCast(TypeBaseInfo);
4006  TBAAInfo = CGF.CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForCast(TBAAInfo, TypeTBAAInfo);
4007  return Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(BaseLVal.getAddress(CGF)),
4008  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ElTy), Align);
4009  }
4010  return CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(Base, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4011 }
4012 
4013 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(const OMPArraySectionExpr *E,
4014  bool IsLowerBound) {
4015  QualType BaseTy = OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(E->getBase());
4016  QualType ResultExprTy;
4017  if (auto *AT = getContext().getAsArrayType(BaseTy))
4018  ResultExprTy = AT->getElementType();
4019  else
4020  ResultExprTy = BaseTy->getPointeeType();
4021  llvm::Value *Idx = nullptr;
4022  if (IsLowerBound || E->getColonLocFirst().isInvalid()) {
4023  // Requesting lower bound or upper bound, but without provided length and
4024  // without ':' symbol for the default length -> length = 1.
4025  // Idx = LowerBound ?: 0;
4026  if (auto *LowerBound = E->getLowerBound()) {
4027  Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(
4028  EmitScalarExpr(LowerBound), IntPtrTy,
4029  LowerBound->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation());
4030  } else
4031  Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
4032  } else {
4033  // Try to emit length or lower bound as constant. If this is possible, 1
4034  // is subtracted from constant length or lower bound. Otherwise, emit LLVM
4035  // IR (LB + Len) - 1.
4036  auto &C = CGM.getContext();
4037  auto *Length = E->getLength();
4038  llvm::APSInt ConstLength;
4039  if (Length) {
4040  // Idx = LowerBound + Length - 1;
4041  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> CL = Length->getIntegerConstantExpr(C)) {
4042  ConstLength = CL->zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4043  Length = nullptr;
4044  }
4045  auto *LowerBound = E->getLowerBound();
4046  llvm::APSInt ConstLowerBound(PointerWidthInBits, /*isUnsigned=*/false);
4047  if (LowerBound) {
4048  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> LB = LowerBound->getIntegerConstantExpr(C)) {
4049  ConstLowerBound = LB->zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4050  LowerBound = nullptr;
4051  }
4052  }
4053  if (!Length)
4054  --ConstLength;
4055  else if (!LowerBound)
4056  --ConstLowerBound;
4057 
4058  if (Length || LowerBound) {
4059  auto *LowerBoundVal =
4060  LowerBound
4061  ? Builder.CreateIntCast(
4062  EmitScalarExpr(LowerBound), IntPtrTy,
4063  LowerBound->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation())
4064  : llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLowerBound);
4065  auto *LengthVal =
4066  Length
4067  ? Builder.CreateIntCast(
4068  EmitScalarExpr(Length), IntPtrTy,
4069  Length->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation())
4070  : llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength);
4071  Idx = Builder.CreateAdd(LowerBoundVal, LengthVal, "lb_add_len",
4072  /*HasNUW=*/false,
4073  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4074  if (Length && LowerBound) {
4075  Idx = Builder.CreateSub(
4076  Idx, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, /*V=*/1), "idx_sub_1",
4077  /*HasNUW=*/false, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4078  }
4079  } else
4080  Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength + ConstLowerBound);
4081  } else {
4082  // Idx = ArraySize - 1;
4083  QualType ArrayTy = BaseTy->isPointerType()
4084  ? E->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts()->getType()
4085  : BaseTy;
4086  if (auto *VAT = C.getAsVariableArrayType(ArrayTy)) {
4087  Length = VAT->getSizeExpr();
4088  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> L = Length->getIntegerConstantExpr(C)) {
4089  ConstLength = *L;
4090  Length = nullptr;
4091  }
4092  } else {
4093  auto *CAT = C.getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayTy);
4094  ConstLength = CAT->getSize();
4095  }
4096  if (Length) {
4097  auto *LengthVal = Builder.CreateIntCast(
4098  EmitScalarExpr(Length), IntPtrTy,
4099  Length->getType()->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation());
4100  Idx = Builder.CreateSub(
4101  LengthVal, llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, /*V=*/1), "len_sub_1",
4102  /*HasNUW=*/false, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined());
4103  } else {
4104  ConstLength = ConstLength.zextOrTrunc(PointerWidthInBits);
4105  --ConstLength;
4106  Idx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, ConstLength);
4107  }
4108  }
4109  }
4110  assert(Idx);
4111 
4112  Address EltPtr = Address::invalid();
4113  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4114  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4115  if (auto *VLA = getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(ResultExprTy)) {
4116  // The base must be a pointer, which is not an aggregate. Emit
4117  // it. It needs to be emitted first in case it's what captures
4118  // the VLA bounds.
4119  Address Base =
4120  emitOMPArraySectionBase(*this, E->getBase(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo,
4121  BaseTy, VLA->getElementType(), IsLowerBound);
4122  // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
4123  llvm::Value *NumElements = getVLASize(VLA).NumElts;
4124 
4125  // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
4126  // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
4127  // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
4128  // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
4129  if (getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
4130  Idx = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, NumElements);
4131  else
4132  Idx = Builder.CreateNSWMul(Idx, NumElements);
4133  EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Base, Idx, VLA->getElementType(),
4134  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4135  /*signedIndices=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
4136  } else if (const Expr *Array = isSimpleArrayDecayOperand(E->getBase())) {
4137  // If this is A[i] where A is an array, the frontend will have decayed the
4138  // base to be a ArrayToPointerDecay implicit cast. While correct, it is
4139  // inefficient at -O0 to emit a "gep A, 0, 0" when codegen'ing it, then a
4140  // "gep x, i" here. Emit one "gep A, 0, i".
4141  assert(Array->getType()->isArrayType() &&
4142  "Array to pointer decay must have array source type!");
4143  LValue ArrayLV;
4144  // For simple multidimensional array indexing, set the 'accessed' flag for
4145  // better bounds-checking of the base expression.
4146  if (const auto *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Array))
4147  ArrayLV = EmitArraySubscriptExpr(ASE, /*Accessed*/ true);
4148  else
4149  ArrayLV = EmitLValue(Array);
4150 
4151  // Propagate the alignment from the array itself to the result.
4152  EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(
4153  *this, ArrayLV.getAddress(*this), {CGM.getSize(CharUnits::Zero()), Idx},
4154  ResultExprTy, !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4155  /*signedIndices=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
4156  BaseInfo = ArrayLV.getBaseInfo();
4157  TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(ArrayLV, ResultExprTy);
4158  } else {
4159  Address Base = emitOMPArraySectionBase(*this, E->getBase(), BaseInfo,
4160  TBAAInfo, BaseTy, ResultExprTy,
4161  IsLowerBound);
4162  EltPtr = emitArraySubscriptGEP(*this, Base, Idx, ResultExprTy,
4163  !getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined(),
4164  /*signedIndices=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
4165  }
4166 
4167  return MakeAddrLValue(EltPtr, ResultExprTy, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4168 }
4169 
4170 LValue CodeGenFunction::
4171 EmitExtVectorElementExpr(const ExtVectorElementExpr *E) {
4172  // Emit the base vector as an l-value.
4173  LValue Base;
4174 
4175  // ExtVectorElementExpr's base can either be a vector or pointer to vector.
4176  if (E->isArrow()) {
4177  // If it is a pointer to a vector, emit the address and form an lvalue with
4178  // it.
4179  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4180  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4181  Address Ptr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getBase(), &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4182  const auto *PT = E->getBase()->getType()->castAs<PointerType>();
4183  Base = MakeAddrLValue(Ptr, PT->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4184  Base.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
4185  } else if (E->getBase()->isGLValue()) {
4186  // Otherwise, if the base is an lvalue ( as in the case of foo.x.x),
4187  // emit the base as an lvalue.
4188  assert(E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType());
4189  Base = EmitLValue(E->getBase());
4190  } else {
4191  // Otherwise, the base is a normal rvalue (as in (V+V).x), emit it as such.
4192  assert(E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType() &&
4193  "Result must be a vector");
4194  llvm::Value *Vec = EmitScalarExpr(E->getBase());
4195 
4196  // Store the vector to memory (because LValue wants an address).
4197  Address VecMem = CreateMemTemp(E->getBase()->getType());
4198  Builder.CreateStore(Vec, VecMem);
4199  Base = MakeAddrLValue(VecMem, E->getBase()->getType(),
4200  AlignmentSource::Decl);
4201  }
4202 
4203  QualType type =
4204  E->getType().withCVRQualifiers(Base.getQuals().getCVRQualifiers());
4205 
4206  // Encode the element access list into a vector of unsigned indices.
4207  SmallVector<uint32_t, 4> Indices;
4208  E->getEncodedElementAccess(Indices);
4209 
4210  if (Base.isSimple()) {
4211  llvm::Constant *CV =
4212  llvm::ConstantDataVector::get(getLLVMContext(), Indices);
4213  return LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(Base.getAddress(*this), CV, type,
4214  Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4215  }
4216  assert(Base.isExtVectorElt() && "Can only subscript lvalue vec elts here!");
4217 
4218  llvm::Constant *BaseElts = Base.getExtVectorElts();
4219  SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> CElts;
4220 
4221  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Indices.size(); i != e; ++i)
4222  CElts.push_back(BaseElts->getAggregateElement(Indices[i]));
4223  llvm::Constant *CV = llvm::ConstantVector::get(CElts);
4224  return LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(Base.getExtVectorAddress(), CV, type,
4225  Base.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo());
4226 }
4227 
4228 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitMemberExpr(const MemberExpr *E) {
4229  if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = tryToConvertMemberExprToDeclRefExpr(*this, E)) {
4230  EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getBase());
4231  return EmitDeclRefLValue(DRE);
4232  }
4233 
4234  Expr *BaseExpr = E->getBase();
4235  // If this is s.x, emit s as an lvalue. If it is s->x, emit s as a scalar.
4236  LValue BaseLV;
4237  if (E->isArrow()) {
4238  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
4239  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
4240  Address Addr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(BaseExpr, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
4241  QualType PtrTy = BaseExpr->getType()->getPointeeType();
4242  SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
4243  bool IsBaseCXXThis = IsWrappedCXXThis(BaseExpr);
4244  if (IsBaseCXXThis)
4245  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Alignment, true);
4246  if (IsBaseCXXThis || isa<DeclRefExpr>(BaseExpr))
4247  SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, true);
4248  EmitTypeCheck(TCK_MemberAccess, E->getExprLoc(), Addr.getPointer(), PtrTy,
4249  /*Alignment=*/CharUnits::Zero(), SkippedChecks);
4250  BaseLV = MakeAddrLValue(Addr, PtrTy, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
4251  } else
4252  BaseLV = EmitCheckedLValue(BaseExpr, TCK_MemberAccess);
4253 
4254  NamedDecl *ND = E->getMemberDecl();
4255  if (auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ND)) {
4256  LValue LV = EmitLValueForField(BaseLV, Field);
4257  setObjCGCLValueClass(getContext(), E, LV);
4258  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP) {
4259  // If the member was explicitly marked as nontemporal, mark it as
4260  // nontemporal. If the base lvalue is marked as nontemporal, mark access
4261  // to children as nontemporal too.
4262  if ((IsWrappedCXXThis(BaseExpr) &&
4263  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().isNontemporalDecl(Field)) ||
4264  BaseLV.isNontemporal())
4265  LV.setNontemporal(/*Value=*/true);
4266  }
4267  return LV;
4268  }
4269 
4270  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND))
4271  return EmitFunctionDeclLValue(*this, E, FD);
4272 
4273  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled member declaration!");
4274 }
4275 
4276 /// Given that we are currently emitting a lambda, emit an l-value for
4277 /// one of its members.
4278 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForLambdaField(const FieldDecl *Field) {
4279  if (CurCodeDecl) {
4280  assert(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl)->getParent()->isLambda());
4281  assert(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl)->getParent() == Field->getParent());
4282  }
4283  QualType LambdaTagType =
4284  getContext().getTagDeclType(Field->getParent());
4285  LValue LambdaLV = MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(CXXABIThisValue, LambdaTagType);
4286  return EmitLValueForField(LambdaLV, Field);
4287 }
4288 
4289 /// Get the field index in the debug info. The debug info structure/union
4290 /// will ignore the unnamed bitfields.
4291 unsigned CodeGenFunction::getDebugInfoFIndex(const RecordDecl *Rec,
4292  unsigned FieldIndex) {
4293  unsigned I = 0, Skipped = 0;
4294 
4295  for (auto F : Rec->getDefinition()->fields()) {
4296  if (I == FieldIndex)
4297  break;
4298  if (F->isUnnamedBitfield())
4299  Skipped++;
4300  I++;
4301  }
4302 
4303  return FieldIndex - Skipped;
4304 }
4305 
4306 /// Get the address of a zero-sized field within a record. The resulting
4307 /// address doesn't necessarily have the right type.
4308 static Address emitAddrOfZeroSizeField(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Base,
4309  const FieldDecl *Field) {
4310  CharUnits Offset = CGF.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
4311  CGF.getContext().getFieldOffset(Field));
4312  if (Offset.isZero())
4313  return Base;
4314  Base = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Base, CGF.Int8Ty);
4315  return CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Base, Offset);
4316 }
4317 
4318 /// Drill down to the storage of a field without walking into
4319 /// reference types.
4320 ///
4321 /// The resulting address doesn't necessarily have the right type.
4322 static Address emitAddrOfFieldStorage(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address base,
4323  const FieldDecl *field) {
4324  if (field->isZeroSize(CGF.getContext()))
4325  return emitAddrOfZeroSizeField(CGF, base, field);
4326 
4327  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4328 
4329  unsigned idx =
4330  CGF.CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(rec).getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4331 
4332  return CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(base, idx, field->getName());
4333 }
4334 
4335 static Address emitPreserveStructAccess(CodeGenFunction &CGF, LValue base,
4336  Address addr, const FieldDecl *field) {
4337  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4338  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = CGF.getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(
4339  base.getType(), rec->getLocation());
4340 
4341  unsigned idx =
4342  CGF.CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(rec).getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4343 
4344  return CGF.Builder.CreatePreserveStructAccessIndex(
4345  addr, idx, CGF.getDebugInfoFIndex(rec, field->getFieldIndex()), DbgInfo);
4346 }
4347 
4348 static bool hasAnyVptr(const QualType Type, const ASTContext &Context) {
4349  const auto *RD = Type.getTypePtr()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4350  if (!RD)
4351  return false;
4352 
4353  if (RD->isDynamicClass())
4354  return true;
4355 
4356  for (const auto &Base : RD->bases())
4357  if (hasAnyVptr(Base.getType(), Context))
4358  return true;
4359 
4360  for (const FieldDecl *Field : RD->fields())
4361  if (hasAnyVptr(Field->getType(), Context))
4362  return true;
4363 
4364  return false;
4365 }
4366 
4367 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForField(LValue base,
4368  const FieldDecl *field) {
4369  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo = base.getBaseInfo();
4370 
4371  if (field->isBitField()) {
4372  const CGRecordLayout &RL =
4373  CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(field->getParent());
4374  const CGBitFieldInfo &Info = RL.getBitFieldInfo(field);
4375  const bool UseVolatile = isAAPCS(CGM.getTarget()) &&
4376  CGM.getCodeGenOpts().AAPCSBitfieldWidth &&
4377  Info.VolatileStorageSize != 0 &&
4378  field->getType()
4379  .withCVRQualifiers(base.getVRQualifiers())
4380  .isVolatileQualified();
4381  Address Addr = base.getAddress(*this);
4382  unsigned Idx = RL.getLLVMFieldNo(field);
4383  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4384  if (!UseVolatile) {
4385  if (!IsInPreservedAIRegion &&
4386  (!getDebugInfo() || !rec->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>())) {
4387  if (Idx != 0)
4388  // For structs, we GEP to the field that the record layout suggests.
4389  Addr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(Addr, Idx, field->getName());
4390  } else {
4391  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateRecordType(
4392  getContext().getRecordType(rec), rec->getLocation());
4393  Addr = Builder.CreatePreserveStructAccessIndex(
4394  Addr, Idx, getDebugInfoFIndex(rec, field->getFieldIndex()),
4395  DbgInfo);
4396  }
4397  }
4398  const unsigned SS =
4399  UseVolatile ? Info.VolatileStorageSize : Info.StorageSize;
4400  // Get the access type.
4401  llvm::Type *FieldIntTy = llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getLLVMContext(), SS);
4402  if (Addr.getElementType() != FieldIntTy)
4403  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, FieldIntTy);
4404  if (UseVolatile) {
4405  const unsigned VolatileOffset = Info.VolatileStorageOffset.getQuantity();
4406  if (VolatileOffset)
4407  Addr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP(Addr, VolatileOffset);
4408  }
4409 
4410  QualType fieldType =
4411  field->getType().withCVRQualifiers(base.getVRQualifiers());
4412  // TODO: Support TBAA for bit fields.
4413  LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource());
4414  return LValue::MakeBitfield(Addr, Info, fieldType, FieldBaseInfo,
4415  TBAAAccessInfo());
4416  }
4417 
4418  // Fields of may-alias structures are may-alias themselves.
4419  // FIXME: this should get propagated down through anonymous structs
4420  // and unions.
4421  QualType FieldType = field->getType();
4422  const RecordDecl *rec = field->getParent();
4423  AlignmentSource BaseAlignSource = BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource();
4424  LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(getFieldAlignmentSource(BaseAlignSource));
4425  TBAAAccessInfo FieldTBAAInfo;
4426  if (base.getTBAAInfo().isMayAlias() ||
4427  rec->hasAttr<MayAliasAttr>() || FieldType->isVectorType()) {
4428  FieldTBAAInfo = TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo();
4429  } else if (rec->isUnion()) {
4430  // TODO: Support TBAA for unions.
4431  FieldTBAAInfo = TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo();
4432  } else {
4433  // If no base type been assigned for the base access, then try to generate
4434  // one for this base lvalue.
4435  FieldTBAAInfo = base.getTBAAInfo();
4436  if (!FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType) {
4437  FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType = CGM.getTBAABaseTypeInfo(base.getType());
4438  assert(!FieldTBAAInfo.Offset &&
4439  "Nonzero offset for an access with no base type!");
4440  }
4441 
4442  // Adjust offset to be relative to the base type.
4443  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
4444  getContext().getASTRecordLayout(field->getParent());
4445  unsigned CharWidth = getContext().getCharWidth();
4446  if (FieldTBAAInfo.BaseType)
4447  FieldTBAAInfo.Offset +=
4448  Layout.getFieldOffset(field->getFieldIndex()) / CharWidth;
4449 
4450  // Update the final access type and size.
4451  FieldTBAAInfo.AccessType = CGM.getTBAATypeInfo(FieldType);
4452  FieldTBAAInfo.Size =
4453  getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(FieldType).getQuantity();
4454  }
4455 
4456  Address addr = base.getAddress(*this);
4457  if (auto *ClassDef = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(rec)) {
4458  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4459  ClassDef->isDynamicClass()) {
4460  // Getting to any field of dynamic object requires stripping dynamic
4461  // information provided by invariant.group. This is because accessing
4462  // fields may leak the real address of dynamic object, which could result
4463  // in miscompilation when leaked pointer would be compared.
4464  auto *stripped = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(addr.getPointer());
4465  addr = Address(stripped, addr.getElementType(), addr.getAlignment());
4466  }
4467  }
4468 
4469  unsigned RecordCVR = base.getVRQualifiers();
4470  if (rec->isUnion()) {
4471  // For unions, there is no pointer adjustment.
4472  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4473  hasAnyVptr(FieldType, getContext()))
4474  // Because unions can easily skip invariant.barriers, we need to add
4475  // a barrier every time CXXRecord field with vptr is referenced.
4476  addr = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(addr);
4477 
4478  if (IsInPreservedAIRegion ||
4479  (getDebugInfo() && rec->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>())) {
4480  // Remember the original union field index
4481  llvm::DIType *DbgInfo = getDebugInfo()->getOrCreateStandaloneType(base.getType(),
4482  rec->getLocation());
4483  addr = Address(
4484  Builder.CreatePreserveUnionAccessIndex(
4485  addr.getPointer(), getDebugInfoFIndex(rec, field->getFieldIndex()), DbgInfo),
4486  addr.getElementType(), addr.getAlignment());
4487  }
4488 
4489  if (FieldType->isReferenceType())
4490  addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(
4491  addr, CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType), field->getName());
4492  } else {
4493  if (!IsInPreservedAIRegion &&
4494  (!getDebugInfo() || !rec->hasAttr<BPFPreserveAccessIndexAttr>()))
4495  // For structs, we GEP to the field that the record layout suggests.
4496  addr = emitAddrOfFieldStorage(*this, addr, field);
4497  else
4498  // Remember the original struct field index
4499  addr = emitPreserveStructAccess(*this, base, addr, field);
4500  }
4501 
4502  // If this is a reference field, load the reference right now.
4503  if (FieldType->isReferenceType()) {
4504  LValue RefLVal =
4505  MakeAddrLValue(addr, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo, FieldTBAAInfo);
4506  if (RecordCVR & Qualifiers::Volatile)
4507  RefLVal.getQuals().addVolatile();
4508  addr = EmitLoadOfReference(RefLVal, &FieldBaseInfo, &FieldTBAAInfo);
4509 
4510  // Qualifiers on the struct don't apply to the referencee.
4511  RecordCVR = 0;
4512  FieldType = FieldType->getPointeeType();
4513  }
4514 
4515  // Make sure that the address is pointing to the right type. This is critical
4516  // for both unions and structs. A union needs a bitcast, a struct element
4517  // will need a bitcast if the LLVM type laid out doesn't match the desired
4518  // type.
4519  addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(
4520  addr, CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType), field->getName());
4521 
4522  if (field->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>())
4523  addr = EmitFieldAnnotations(field, addr);
4524 
4525  // Emit attribute annotation for a field.
4526  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
4527  SmallString<256> AnnotStr;
4528  CGM.generateIntelFPGAAnnotation(field, AnnotStr);
4529  if (!AnnotStr.empty())
4530  addr = EmitIntelFPGAFieldAnnotations(field, addr, AnnotStr);
4531  }
4532 
4533  LValue LV = MakeAddrLValue(addr, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo, FieldTBAAInfo);
4534  LV.getQuals().addCVRQualifiers(RecordCVR);
4535 
4536  // __weak attribute on a field is ignored.
4537  if (LV.getQuals().getObjCGCAttr() == Qualifiers::Weak)
4538  LV.getQuals().removeObjCGCAttr();
4539 
4540  return LV;
4541 }
4542 
4543 LValue
4544 CodeGenFunction::EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(LValue Base,
4545  const FieldDecl *Field) {
4546  QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
4547 
4548  if (!FieldType->isReferenceType())
4549  return EmitLValueForField(Base, Field);
4550 
4551  Address V = emitAddrOfFieldStorage(*this, Base.getAddress(*this), Field);
4552 
4553  // Make sure that the address is pointing to the right type.
4554  llvm::Type *llvmType = ConvertTypeForMem(FieldType);
4555  V = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(V, llvmType, Field->getName());
4556 
4557  // TODO: Generate TBAA information that describes this access as a structure
4558  // member access and not just an access to an object of the field's type. This
4559  // should be similar to what we do in EmitLValueForField().
4560  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo = Base.getBaseInfo();
4561  AlignmentSource FieldAlignSource = BaseInfo.getAlignmentSource();
4562  LValueBaseInfo FieldBaseInfo(getFieldAlignmentSource(FieldAlignSource));
4563  return MakeAddrLValue(V, FieldType, FieldBaseInfo,
4564  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(Base, FieldType));
4565 }
4566 
4567 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCompoundLiteralLValue(const CompoundLiteralExpr *E){
4568  if (E->isFileScope()) {
4569  ConstantAddress GlobalPtr = CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCompoundLiteral(E);
4570  return MakeAddrLValue(GlobalPtr, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
4571  }
4572  if (E->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
4573  // make sure to emit the VLA size.
4574  EmitVariablyModifiedType(E->getType());
4575 
4576  Address DeclPtr = CreateMemTemp(E->getType(), ".compoundliteral");
4577  const Expr *InitExpr = E->getInitializer();
4578  LValue Result = MakeAddrLValue(DeclPtr, E->getType(), AlignmentSource::Decl);
4579 
4580  EmitAnyExprToMem(InitExpr, DeclPtr, E->getType().getQualifiers(),
4581  /*Init*/ true);
4582 
4583  // Block-scope compound literals are destroyed at the end of the enclosing
4584  // scope in C.
4585  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4586  if (QualType::DestructionKind DtorKind = E->getType().isDestructedType())
4587  pushLifetimeExtendedDestroy(getCleanupKind(DtorKind), DeclPtr,
4588  E->getType(), getDestroyer(DtorKind),
4589  DtorKind & EHCleanup);
4590 
4591  return Result;
4592 }

4594 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitInitListLValue(const InitListExpr *E) {
4595  if (!E->isGLValue())
4596  // Initializing an aggregate temporary in C++11: T{...}.
4597  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
4598 
4599  // An lvalue initializer list must be initializing a reference.
4600  assert(E->isTransparent() && "non-transparent glvalue init list");
4601  return EmitLValue(E->getInit(0));
4602 }
4603 
4604 /// Emit the operand of a glvalue conditional operator. This is either a glvalue
4605 /// or a (possibly-parenthesized) throw-expression. If this is a throw, no
4606 /// LValue is returned and the current block has been terminated.
4607 static Optional<LValue> EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4608  const Expr *Operand) {
4609  if (auto *ThrowExpr = dyn_cast<CXXThrowExpr>(Operand->IgnoreParens())) {
4610  CGF.EmitCXXThrowExpr(ThrowExpr, /*KeepInsertionPoint*/false);
4611  return None;
4612  }
4613 
4614  return CGF.EmitLValue(Operand);
4615 }
4616 
4617 LValue CodeGenFunction::
4618 EmitConditionalOperatorLValue(const AbstractConditionalOperator *expr) {
4619  if (!expr->isGLValue()) {
4620  // ?: here should be an aggregate.
4621  assert(hasAggregateEvaluationKind(expr->getType()) &&
4622  "Unexpected conditional operator!");
4623  return EmitAggExprToLValue(expr);
4624  }
4625 
4626  OpaqueValueMapping binding(*this, expr);
4627 
4628  const Expr *condExpr = expr->getCond();
4629  bool CondExprBool;
4630  if (ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(condExpr, CondExprBool)) {
4631  const Expr *live = expr->getTrueExpr(), *dead = expr->getFalseExpr();
4632  if (!CondExprBool) std::swap(live, dead);
4633 
4634  if (!ContainsLabel(dead)) {
4635  // If the true case is live, we need to track its region.
4636  if (CondExprBool)
4637  incrementProfileCounter(expr);
4638  // If a throw expression we emit it and return an undefined lvalue
4639  // because it can't be used.
4640  if (auto *ThrowExpr = dyn_cast<CXXThrowExpr>(live->IgnoreParens())) {
4641  EmitCXXThrowExpr(ThrowExpr);
4642  llvm::Type *ElemTy = ConvertType(dead->getType());
4643  llvm::Type *Ty = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(ElemTy);
4644  return MakeAddrLValue(
4645  Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(Ty), ElemTy, CharUnits::One()),
4646  dead->getType());
4647  }
4648  return EmitLValue(live);
4649  }
4650  }
4651 
4652  llvm::BasicBlock *lhsBlock = createBasicBlock("cond.true");
4653  llvm::BasicBlock *rhsBlock = createBasicBlock("cond.false");
4654  llvm::BasicBlock *contBlock = createBasicBlock("cond.end");
4655 
4656  ConditionalEvaluation eval(*this);
4657  EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(condExpr, lhsBlock, rhsBlock, getProfileCount(expr));
4658 
4659  // Any temporaries created here are conditional.
4660  EmitBlock(lhsBlock);
4661  incrementProfileCounter(expr);
4662  eval.begin(*this);
4663  Optional<LValue> lhs =
4664  EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(*this, expr->getTrueExpr());
4665  eval.end(*this);
4666 
4667  if (lhs && !lhs->isSimple())
4668  return EmitUnsupportedLValue(expr, "conditional operator");
4669 
4670  lhsBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4671  if (lhs)
4672  Builder.CreateBr(contBlock);
4673 
4674  // Any temporaries created here are conditional.
4675  EmitBlock(rhsBlock);
4676  eval.begin(*this);
4677  Optional<LValue> rhs =
4678  EmitLValueOrThrowExpression(*this, expr->getFalseExpr());
4679  eval.end(*this);
4680  if (rhs && !rhs->isSimple())
4681  return EmitUnsupportedLValue(expr, "conditional operator");
4682  rhsBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4683 
4684  EmitBlock(contBlock);
4685 
4686  if (lhs && rhs) {
4687  Address lhsAddr = lhs->getAddress(*this);
4688  Address rhsAddr = rhs->getAddress(*this);
4689  llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(lhsAddr.getType(), 2, "cond-lvalue");
4690  phi->addIncoming(lhsAddr.getPointer(), lhsBlock);
4691  phi->addIncoming(rhsAddr.getPointer(), rhsBlock);
4692  Address result(phi, lhsAddr.getElementType(),
4693  std::min(lhsAddr.getAlignment(), rhsAddr.getAlignment()));
4694  AlignmentSource alignSource =
4695  std::max(lhs->getBaseInfo().getAlignmentSource(),
4696  rhs->getBaseInfo().getAlignmentSource());
4697  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo = CGM.mergeTBAAInfoForConditionalOperator(
4698  lhs->getTBAAInfo(), rhs->getTBAAInfo());
4699  return MakeAddrLValue(result, expr->getType(), LValueBaseInfo(alignSource),
4700  TBAAInfo);
4701  } else {
4702  assert((lhs || rhs) &&
4703  "both operands of glvalue conditional are throw-expressions?");
4704  return lhs ? *lhs : *rhs;
4705  }
4706 }
4707 
4708 /// EmitCastLValue - Casts are never lvalues unless that cast is to a reference
4709 /// type. If the cast is to a reference, we can have the usual lvalue result,
4710 /// otherwise if a cast is needed by the code generator in an lvalue context,
4711 /// then it must mean that we need the address of an aggregate in order to
4712 /// access one of its members. This can happen for all the reasons that casts
4713 /// are permitted with aggregate result, including noop aggregate casts, and
4714 /// cast from scalar to union.
4715 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCastLValue(const CastExpr *E) {
4716  switch (E->getCastKind()) {
4717  case CK_ToVoid:
4718  case CK_BitCast:
4719  case CK_LValueToRValueBitCast:
4720  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
4721  case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
4722  case CK_NullToMemberPointer:
4723  case CK_NullToPointer:
4724  case CK_IntegralToPointer:
4725  case CK_PointerToIntegral:
4726  case CK_PointerToBoolean:
4727  case CK_VectorSplat:
4728  case CK_IntegralCast:
4729  case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral:
4730  case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
4731  case CK_IntegralToFloating:
4732  case CK_FloatingToIntegral:
4733  case CK_FloatingToBoolean:
4734  case CK_FloatingCast:
4735  case CK_FloatingRealToComplex:
4736  case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
4737  case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
4738  case CK_FloatingComplexCast:
4739  case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex:
4740  case CK_IntegralRealToComplex:
4741  case CK_IntegralComplexToReal:
4742  case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean:
4743  case CK_IntegralComplexCast:
4744  case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex:
4745  case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer:
4746  case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
4747  case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean:
4748  case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
4749  case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
4750  case CK_ARCProduceObject:
4751  case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
4752  case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
4753  case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
4754  case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
4755  case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
4756  case CK_FloatingToFixedPoint:
4757  case CK_FixedPointToFloating:
4758  case CK_FixedPointCast:
4759  case CK_FixedPointToBoolean:
4760  case CK_FixedPointToIntegral:
4761  case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
4762  case CK_MatrixCast:
4763  return EmitUnsupportedLValue(E, "unexpected cast lvalue");
4764 
4765  case CK_Dependent:
4766  llvm_unreachable("dependent cast kind in IR gen!");
4767 
4768  case CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr:
4769  llvm_unreachable("builtin functions are handled elsewhere");
4770 
4771  // These are never l-values; just use the aggregate emission code.
4772  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
4773  case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
4774  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
4775 
4776  case CK_Dynamic: {
4777  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4778  Address V = LV.getAddress(*this);
4779  const auto *DCE = cast<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(E);
4780  return MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(EmitDynamicCast(V, DCE), E->getType());
4781  }
4782 
4783  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
4784  case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
4785  case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
4786  case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
4787  case CK_LValueToRValue:
4788  return EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4789 
4790  case CK_NoOp: {
4791  // CK_NoOp can model a qualification conversion, which can remove an array
4792  // bound and change the IR type.
4793  // FIXME: Once pointee types are removed from IR, remove this.
4794  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4795  if (LV.isSimple()) {
4796  Address V = LV.getAddress(*this);
4797  if (V.isValid()) {
4798  llvm::Type *T = ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType());
4799  if (V.getElementType() != T)
4800  LV.setAddress(Builder.CreateElementBitCast(V, T));
4801  }
4802  }
4803  return LV;
4804  }
4805 
4806  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
4807  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
4808  const auto *DerivedClassTy =
4809  E->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<RecordType>();
4810  auto *DerivedClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DerivedClassTy->getDecl());
4811 
4812  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4813  Address This = LV.getAddress(*this);
4814 
4815  // Perform the derived-to-base conversion
4816  Address Base = GetAddressOfBaseClass(
4817  This, DerivedClassDecl, E->path_begin(), E->path_end(),
4818  /*NullCheckValue=*/false, E->getExprLoc());
4819 
4820  // TODO: Support accesses to members of base classes in TBAA. For now, we
4821  // conservatively pretend that the complete object is of the base class
4822  // type.
4823  return MakeAddrLValue(Base, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
4824  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
4825  }
4826  case CK_ToUnion:
4827  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
4828  case CK_BaseToDerived: {
4829  const auto *DerivedClassTy = E->getType()->castAs<RecordType>();
4830  auto *DerivedClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DerivedClassTy->getDecl());
4831 
4832  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4833 
4834  // Perform the base-to-derived conversion
4835  Address Derived = GetAddressOfDerivedClass(
4836  LV.getAddress(*this), DerivedClassDecl, E->path_begin(), E->path_end(),
4837  /*NullCheckValue=*/false);
4838 
4839  // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p2: Behavior is undefined if a downcast is
4840  // performed and the object is not of the derived type.
4841  if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
4842  EmitTypeCheck(TCK_DowncastReference, E->getExprLoc(),
4843  Derived.getPointer(), E->getType());
4844 
4845  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast))
4846  EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(E->getType(), Derived,
4847  /*MayBeNull=*/false, CFITCK_DerivedCast,
4848  E->getBeginLoc());
4849 
4850  return MakeAddrLValue(Derived, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
4851  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
4852  }
4853  case CK_LValueBitCast: {
4854  // This must be a reinterpret_cast (or c-style equivalent).
4855  const auto *CE = cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(E);
4856 
4857  CGM.EmitExplicitCastExprType(CE, this);
4858  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4859  Address V = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(
4860  LV.getAddress(*this),
4861  ConvertTypeForMem(CE->getTypeAsWritten()->getPointeeType()));
4862 
4863  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast))
4864  EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(E->getType(), V,
4865  /*MayBeNull=*/false, CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
4866  E->getBeginLoc());
4867 
4868  return MakeAddrLValue(V, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
4869  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
4870  }
4871  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion: {
4872  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4873  QualType DestTy = getContext().getPointerType(E->getType());
4874  llvm::Value *V = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
4875  *this, LV.getPointer(*this),
4876  E->getSubExpr()->getType().getAddressSpace(),
4877  E->getType().getAddressSpace(), ConvertType(DestTy));
4878  return MakeAddrLValue(Address(V, ConvertTypeForMem(E->getType()),
4879  LV.getAddress(*this).getAlignment()),
4880  E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(), LV.getTBAAInfo());
4881  }
4882  case CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast: {
4883  LValue LV = EmitLValue(E->getSubExpr());
4884  Address V = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(LV.getAddress(*this),
4885  ConvertType(E->getType()));
4886  return MakeAddrLValue(V, E->getType(), LV.getBaseInfo(),
4887  CGM.getTBAAInfoForSubobject(LV, E->getType()));
4888  }
4889  case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType:
4890  llvm_unreachable("NULL to OpenCL opaque type lvalue cast is not valid");
4891  }
4892 
4893  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled lvalue cast kind?");
4894 }
4895 
4896 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitOpaqueValueLValue(const OpaqueValueExpr *e) {
4897  assert(OpaqueValueMappingData::shouldBindAsLValue(e));
4898  return getOrCreateOpaqueLValueMapping(e);
4899 }
4900 
4901 LValue
4902 CodeGenFunction::getOrCreateOpaqueLValueMapping(const OpaqueValueExpr *e) {
4903  assert(OpaqueValueMapping::shouldBindAsLValue(e));
4904 
4905  llvm::DenseMap<const OpaqueValueExpr*,LValue>::iterator
4906  it = OpaqueLValues.find(e);
4907 
4908  if (it != OpaqueLValues.end())
4909  return it->second;
4910 
4911  assert(e->isUnique() && "LValue for a nonunique OVE hasn't been emitted");
4912  return EmitLValue(e->getSourceExpr());
4913 }
4914 
4915 RValue
4916 CodeGenFunction::getOrCreateOpaqueRValueMapping(const OpaqueValueExpr *e) {
4917  assert(!OpaqueValueMapping::shouldBindAsLValue(e));
4918 
4919  llvm::DenseMap<const OpaqueValueExpr*,RValue>::iterator
4920  it = OpaqueRValues.find(e);
4921 
4922  if (it != OpaqueRValues.end())
4923  return it->second;
4924 
4925  assert(e->isUnique() && "RValue for a nonunique OVE hasn't been emitted");
4926  return EmitAnyExpr(e->getSourceExpr());
4927 }
4928 
4929 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitRValueForField(LValue LV,
4930  const FieldDecl *FD,
4931  SourceLocation Loc) {
4932  QualType FT = FD->getType();
4933  LValue FieldLV = EmitLValueForField(LV, FD);
4934  switch (getEvaluationKind(FT)) {
4935  case TEK_Complex:
4936  return RValue::getComplex(EmitLoadOfComplex(FieldLV, Loc));
4937  case TEK_Aggregate:
4938  return FieldLV.asAggregateRValue(*this);
4939  case TEK_Scalar:
4940  // This routine is used to load fields one-by-one to perform a copy, so
4941  // don't load reference fields.
4942  if (FD->getType()->isReferenceType())
4943  return RValue::get(FieldLV.getPointer(*this));
4944  // Call EmitLoadOfScalar except when the lvalue is a bitfield to emit a
4945  // primitive load.
4946  if (FieldLV.isBitField())
4947  return EmitLoadOfLValue(FieldLV, Loc);
4948  return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(FieldLV, Loc));
4949  }
4950  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
4951 }

4953 //===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4954 // Expression Emission
4955 //===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4956 
4957 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
4958  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
4959  // Builtins never have block type.
4960  if (E->getCallee()->getType()->isBlockPointerType())
4961  return EmitBlockCallExpr(E, ReturnValue);
4962 
4963  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CXXMemberCallExpr>(E))
4964  return EmitCXXMemberCallExpr(CE, ReturnValue);
4965 
4966  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CUDAKernelCallExpr>(E))
4967  return EmitCUDAKernelCallExpr(CE, ReturnValue);
4968 
4969  if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E))
4970  if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD =
4971  dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(CE->getCalleeDecl()))
4972  return EmitCXXOperatorMemberCallExpr(CE, MD, ReturnValue);
4973 
4974  CGCallee callee = EmitCallee(E->getCallee());
4975 
4976  if (callee.isBuiltin()) {
4977  return EmitBuiltinExpr(callee.getBuiltinDecl(), callee.getBuiltinID(),
4978  E, ReturnValue);
4979  }
4980 
4981  if (callee.isPseudoDestructor()) {
4982  return EmitCXXPseudoDestructorExpr(callee.getPseudoDestructorExpr());
4983  }
4984 
4985  return EmitCall(E->getCallee()->getType(), callee, E, ReturnValue);
4986 }
4987 
4988 /// Emit a CallExpr without considering whether it might be a subclass.
4989 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitSimpleCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
4990  ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
4991  CGCallee Callee = EmitCallee(E->getCallee());
4992  return EmitCall(E->getCallee()->getType(), Callee, E, ReturnValue);
4993 }
4994 
4995 static CGCallee EmitDirectCallee(CodeGenFunction &CGF, GlobalDecl GD) {
4996  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4997 
4998  if (auto builtinID = FD->getBuiltinID()) {
4999  std::string FDInlineName = (FD->getName() + ".inline").str();
5000  // When directing calling an inline builtin, call it through it's mangled
5001  // name to make it clear it's not the actual builtin.
5002  if (FD->isInlineBuiltinDeclaration() &&
5003  CGF.CurFn->getName() != FDInlineName) {
5004  llvm::Constant *CalleePtr = EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CGF.CGM, GD);
5005  llvm::Function *Fn = llvm::cast<llvm::Function>(CalleePtr);
5006  llvm::Module *M = Fn->getParent();
5007  llvm::Function *Clone = M->getFunction(FDInlineName);
5008  if (!Clone) {
5009  Clone = llvm::Function::Create(Fn->getFunctionType(),
5010  llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
5011  Fn->getAddressSpace(), FDInlineName, M);
5012  Clone->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
5013  }
5014  return CGCallee::forDirect(Clone, GD);
5015  }
5016 
5017  // Replaceable builtins provide their own implementation of a builtin. If we
5018  // are in an inline builtin implementation, avoid trivial infinite
5019  // recursion.
5020  else
5021  return CGCallee::forBuiltin(builtinID, FD);
5022  }
5023 
5024  llvm::Constant *CalleePtr = EmitFunctionDeclPointer(CGF.CGM, GD);
5025  if (CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA && !CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
5026  FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>())
5027  CalleePtr = CGF.CGM.getCUDARuntime().getKernelStub(
5028  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CalleePtr->stripPointerCasts()));
5029 
5030  return CGCallee::forDirect(CalleePtr, GD);
5031 }
5032 
5033 CGCallee CodeGenFunction::EmitCallee(const Expr *E) {
5034  E = E->IgnoreParens();
5035 
5036  // Look through function-to-pointer decay.
5037  if (auto ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
5038  if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_FunctionToPointerDecay ||
5039  ICE->getCastKind() == CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr) {
5040  return EmitCallee(ICE->getSubExpr());
5041  }
5042 
5043  // Resolve direct calls.
5044  } else if (auto DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
5045  if (auto FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
5046  return EmitDirectCallee(*this, FD);
5047  }
5048  } else if (auto ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
5049  if (auto FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl())) {
5050  EmitIgnoredExpr(ME->getBase());
5051  return EmitDirectCallee(*this, FD);
5052  }
5053 
5054  // Look through template substitutions.
5055  } else if (auto NTTP = dyn_cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)) {
5056  return EmitCallee(NTTP->getReplacement());
5057 
5058  // Treat pseudo-destructor calls differently.
5059  } else if (auto PDE = dyn_cast<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(E)) {
5060  return CGCallee::forPseudoDestructor(PDE);
5061  }
5062 
5063  // Otherwise, we have an indirect reference.
5064  llvm::Value *calleePtr;
5065  QualType functionType;
5066  if (auto ptrType = E->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
5067  calleePtr = EmitScalarExpr(E);
5068  functionType = ptrType->getPointeeType();
5069  } else {
5070  functionType = E->getType();
5071  calleePtr = EmitLValue(E).getPointer(*this);
5072  }
5073  assert(functionType->isFunctionType());
5074 
5075  GlobalDecl GD;
5076  if (const auto *VD =
5077  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(E->getReferencedDeclOfCallee()))
5078  GD = GlobalDecl(VD);
5079 
5080  CGCalleeInfo calleeInfo(functionType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>(), GD);
5081  CGCallee callee(calleeInfo, calleePtr);
5082  return callee;
5083 }
5084 
5085 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitBinaryOperatorLValue(const BinaryOperator *E) {
5086  // Comma expressions just emit their LHS then their RHS as an l-value.
5087  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
5088  EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getLHS());
5089  EnsureInsertPoint();
5090  return EmitLValue(E->getRHS());
5091  }
5092 
5093  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemD ||
5094  E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI)
5095  return EmitPointerToDataMemberBinaryExpr(E);
5096 
5097  assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_Assign && "unexpected binary l-value");
5098 
5099  // Note that in all of these cases, __block variables need the RHS
5100  // evaluated first just in case the variable gets moved by the RHS.
5101 
5102  switch (getEvaluationKind(E->getType())) {
5103  case TEK_Scalar: {
5104  switch (E->getLHS()->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
5105  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
5106  return EmitARCStoreStrong(E, /*ignored*/ false).first;
5107 
5108  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
5109  return EmitARCStoreAutoreleasing(E).first;
5110 
5111  // No reason to do any of these differently.
5112  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
5113  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
5114  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
5115  break;
5116  }
5117 
5118  RValue RV = EmitAnyExpr(E->getRHS());
5119  LValue LV = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), TCK_Store);
5120  if (RV.isScalar())
5121  EmitNullabilityCheck(LV, RV.getScalarVal(), E->getExprLoc());
5122  EmitStoreThroughLValue(RV, LV);
5123  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP)
5124  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(*this,
5125  E->getLHS());
5126  return LV;
5127  }
5128 
5129  case TEK_Complex:
5130  return EmitComplexAssignmentLValue(E);
5131 
5132  case TEK_Aggregate:
5133  return EmitAggExprToLValue(E);
5134  }
5135  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5136 }
5137 
5138 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCallExprLValue(const CallExpr *E) {

5140 
5141  if (!RV.isScalar())

5143  AlignmentSource::Decl);
5144 
5145  assert(E->getCallReturnType(getContext())->isReferenceType() &&
5146  "Can't have a scalar return unless the return type is a "
5147  "reference type!");
5148 
5149  return MakeNaturalAlignPointeeAddrLValue(RV.getScalarVal(), E->getType());
5150 }

5222 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCIvarRefLValue(const ObjCIvarRefExpr *E) {
5223  // FIXME: A lot of the code below could be shared with EmitMemberExpr.
5224  llvm::Value *BaseValue = nullptr;
5225  const Expr *BaseExpr = E->getBase();
5226  Qualifiers BaseQuals;
5227  QualType ObjectTy;

5236  BaseQuals = ObjectTy.getQualifiers();

5240  EmitLValueForIvar(ObjectTy, BaseValue, E->getDecl(),
5241  BaseQuals.getCVRQualifiers());

5252 
5253 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCall(QualType CalleeType, const CGCallee &OrigCallee,
5254  const CallExpr *E, ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue,
5255  llvm::Value *Chain) {
5256  // Get the actual function type. The callee type will always be a pointer to
5257  // function type or a block pointer type.
5258  assert(CalleeType->isFunctionPointerType() &&
5259  "Call must have function pointer type!");
5260 
5261  const Decl *TargetDecl =
5262  OrigCallee.getAbstractInfo().getCalleeDecl().getDecl();
5263 
5264  CalleeType = getContext().getCanonicalType(CalleeType);
5265 
5266  auto PointeeType = cast<PointerType>(CalleeType)->getPointeeType();
5267 
5268  CGCallee Callee = OrigCallee;
5269 
5270  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Function) &&
5271  (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))) {
5272  if (llvm::Constant *PrefixSig =
5273  CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getUBSanFunctionSignature(CGM)) {
5274  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5275  // Remove any (C++17) exception specifications, to allow calling e.g. a
5276  // noexcept function through a non-noexcept pointer.
5277  auto ProtoTy =
5278  getContext().getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(PointeeType, EST_None);
5279  llvm::Constant *FTRTTIConst =
5280  CGM.GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(ProtoTy, /*ForEH=*/true);
5281  llvm::Type *PrefixSigType = PrefixSig->getType();
5282  llvm::StructType *PrefixStructTy = llvm::StructType::get(
5283  CGM.getLLVMContext(), {PrefixSigType, Int32Ty}, /*isPacked=*/true);
5284 
5285  llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5286 
5287  llvm::Value *CalleePrefixStruct = Builder.CreateBitCast(
5288  CalleePtr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(PrefixStructTy));
5289  llvm::Value *CalleeSigPtr =
5290  Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(PrefixStructTy, CalleePrefixStruct, 0, 0);
5291  llvm::Value *CalleeSig =
5292  Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(PrefixSigType, CalleeSigPtr, getIntAlign());
5293  llvm::Value *CalleeSigMatch = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CalleeSig, PrefixSig);
5294 
5295  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = createBasicBlock("cont");
5296  llvm::BasicBlock *TypeCheck = createBasicBlock("typecheck");
5297  Builder.CreateCondBr(CalleeSigMatch, TypeCheck, Cont);
5298 
5299  EmitBlock(TypeCheck);
5300  llvm::Value *CalleeRTTIPtr =
5301  Builder.CreateConstGEP2_32(PrefixStructTy, CalleePrefixStruct, 0, 1);
5302  llvm::Value *CalleeRTTIEncoded =
5303  Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Int32Ty, CalleeRTTIPtr, getPointerAlign());
5304  llvm::Value *CalleeRTTI =
5305  DecodeAddrUsedInPrologue(CalleePtr, CalleeRTTIEncoded);
5306  llvm::Value *CalleeRTTIMatch =
5307  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(CalleeRTTI, FTRTTIConst);
5308  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc()),
5309  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(CalleeType)};
5310  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(CalleeRTTIMatch, SanitizerKind::Function),
5311  SanitizerHandler::FunctionTypeMismatch, StaticData,
5312  {CalleePtr, CalleeRTTI, FTRTTIConst});
5313 
5314  Builder.CreateBr(Cont);
5315  EmitBlock(Cont);
5316  }
5317  }
5318 
5319  const auto *FnType = cast<FunctionType>(PointeeType);
5320 
5321  // If we are checking indirect calls and this call is indirect, check that the
5322  // function pointer is a member of the bit set for the function type.
5323  if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIICall) &&
5324  (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))) {
5325  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5326  EmitSanitizerStatReport(llvm::SanStat_CFI_ICall);
5327 
5328  llvm::Metadata *MD;
5329  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiICallGeneralizePointers)
5330  MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierGeneralized(QualType(FnType, 0));
5331  else
5332  MD = CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(FnType, 0));
5333 
5334  llvm::Value *TypeId = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(getLLVMContext(), MD);
5335 
5336  llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5337  llvm::Value *CastedCallee = Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, Int8PtrTy);
5338  llvm::Value *TypeTest = Builder.CreateCall(
5339  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {CastedCallee, TypeId});
5340 
5341  auto CrossDsoTypeId = CGM.CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD);
5342  llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
5343  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, CFITCK_ICall),
5344  EmitCheckSourceLocation(E->getBeginLoc()),
5345  EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType(FnType, 0)),
5346  };
5347  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiCrossDso && CrossDsoTypeId) {
5348  EmitCfiSlowPathCheck(SanitizerKind::CFIICall, TypeTest, CrossDsoTypeId,
5349  CastedCallee, StaticData);
5350  } else {
5351  EmitCheck(std::make_pair(TypeTest, SanitizerKind::CFIICall),
5352  SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, StaticData,
5353  {CastedCallee, llvm::UndefValue::get(IntPtrTy)});
5354  }
5355  }
5356 
5357  CallArgList Args;
5358  if (Chain)
5359  Args.add(RValue::get(Builder.CreateBitCast(Chain, CGM.VoidPtrTy)),
5360  CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
5361 
5362  // C++17 requires that we evaluate arguments to a call using assignment syntax
5363  // right-to-left, and that we evaluate arguments to certain other operators
5364  // left-to-right. Note that we allow this to override the order dictated by
5365  // the calling convention on the MS ABI, which means that parameter
5366  // destruction order is not necessarily reverse construction order.
5367  // FIXME: Revisit this based on C++ committee response to unimplementability.
5368  EvaluationOrder Order = EvaluationOrder::Default;
5369  if (auto *OCE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E)) {
5370  if (OCE->isAssignmentOp())
5371  Order = EvaluationOrder::ForceRightToLeft;
5372  else {
5373  switch (OCE->getOperator()) {
5374  case OO_LessLess:
5375  case OO_GreaterGreater:
5376  case OO_AmpAmp:
5377  case OO_PipePipe:
5378  case OO_Comma:
5379  case OO_ArrowStar:
5380  Order = EvaluationOrder::ForceLeftToRight;
5381  break;
5382  default:
5383  break;
5384  }
5385  }
5386  }
5387 
5388  EmitCallArgs(Args, dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType), E->arguments(),
5389  E->getDirectCallee(), /*ParamsToSkip*/ 0, Order);
5390 
5391  const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo = CGM.getTypes().arrangeFreeFunctionCall(
5392  Args, FnType, /*ChainCall=*/Chain);
5393 
5394  // C99 6.5.2.2p6:
5395  // If the expression that denotes the called function has a type
5396  // that does not include a prototype, [the default argument
5397  // promotions are performed]. If the number of arguments does not
5398  // equal the number of parameters, the behavior is undefined. If
5399  // the function is defined with a type that includes a prototype,
5400  // and either the prototype ends with an ellipsis (, ...) or the
5401  // types of the arguments after promotion are not compatible with
5402  // the types of the parameters, the behavior is undefined. If the
5403  // function is defined with a type that does not include a
5404  // prototype, and the types of the arguments after promotion are
5405  // not compatible with those of the parameters after promotion,
5406  // the behavior is undefined [except in some trivial cases].
5407  // That is, in the general case, we should assume that a call
5408  // through an unprototyped function type works like a *non-variadic*
5409  // call. The way we make this work is to cast to the exact type
5410  // of the promoted arguments.
5411  //
5412  // Chain calls use this same code path to add the invisible chain parameter
5413  // to the function type.
5414  if (isa<FunctionNoProtoType>(FnType) || Chain) {
5415  llvm::Type *CalleeTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
5416  int AS = Callee.getFunctionPointer()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
5417  CalleeTy = CalleeTy->getPointerTo(AS);
5418 
5419  llvm::Value *CalleePtr = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5420  CalleePtr = Builder.CreateBitCast(CalleePtr, CalleeTy, "callee.knr.cast");
5421  Callee.setFunctionPointer(CalleePtr);
5422  }
5423 
5424  // HIP function pointer contains kernel handle when it is used in triple
5425  // chevron. The kernel stub needs to be loaded from kernel handle and used
5426  // as callee.
5427  if (CGM.getLangOpts().HIP && !CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
5428  isa<CUDAKernelCallExpr>(E) &&
5429  (!TargetDecl || !isa<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl))) {
5430  llvm::Value *Handle = Callee.getFunctionPointer();
5431  auto *Cast =
5432  Builder.CreateBitCast(Handle, Handle->getType()->getPointerTo());
5433  auto *Stub = Builder.CreateLoad(
5434  Address(Cast, Handle->getType(), CGM.getPointerAlign()));
5435  Callee.setFunctionPointer(Stub);
5436  }
5437  llvm::CallBase *CallOrInvoke = nullptr;
5438  RValue Call = EmitCall(FnInfo, Callee, ReturnValue, Args, &CallOrInvoke,
5439  E == MustTailCall, E->getExprLoc());
5440 
5441  // Generate function declaration DISuprogram in order to be used
5442  // in debug info about call sites.
5443  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getDebugInfo()) {
5444  if (auto *CalleeDecl = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(TargetDecl)) {
5445  FunctionArgList Args;
5446  QualType ResTy = BuildFunctionArgList(CalleeDecl, Args);
5447  DI->EmitFuncDeclForCallSite(CallOrInvoke,
5448  DI->getFunctionType(CalleeDecl, ResTy, Args),
5449  CalleeDecl);
5450  }
5451  }
5452 
5453  return Call;
5454 }
5455 
5456 LValue CodeGenFunction::
5457 EmitPointerToDataMemberBinaryExpr(const BinaryOperator *E) {
5458  Address BaseAddr = Address::invalid();
5459  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI) {
5460  BaseAddr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getLHS());
5461  } else {
5462  BaseAddr = EmitLValue(E->getLHS()).getAddress(*this);
5463  }
5464 
5465  llvm::Value *OffsetV = EmitScalarExpr(E->getRHS());
5466  const auto *MPT = E->getRHS()->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
5467 
5468  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
5469  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
5470  Address MemberAddr =
5471  EmitCXXMemberDataPointerAddress(E, BaseAddr, OffsetV, MPT, &BaseInfo,
5472  &TBAAInfo);
5473 
5474  return MakeAddrLValue(MemberAddr, MPT->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
5475 }
5476 
5477 /// Given the address of a temporary variable, produce an r-value of
5478 /// its type.
5479 RValue CodeGenFunction::convertTempToRValue(Address addr,
5480  QualType type,
5481  SourceLocation loc) {
5482  LValue lvalue = MakeAddrLValue(addr, type, AlignmentSource::Decl);
5483  switch (getEvaluationKind(type)) {
5484  case TEK_Complex:
5485  return RValue::getComplex(EmitLoadOfComplex(lvalue, loc));
5486  case TEK_Aggregate:
5487  return lvalue.asAggregateRValue(*this);
5488  case TEK_Scalar:
5489  return RValue::get(EmitLoadOfScalar(lvalue, loc));
5490  }
5491  llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
5492 }
5493 
5494 void CodeGenFunction::SetFPAccuracy(llvm::Value *Val, float Accuracy) {
5495  assert(Val->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy());
5496  if (Accuracy == 0.0 || !isa<llvm::Instruction>(Val))
5497  return;
5498 
5499  llvm::MDBuilder MDHelper(getLLVMContext());
5500  llvm::MDNode *Node = MDHelper.createFPMath(Accuracy);
5501 
5502  cast<llvm::Instruction>(Val)->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_fpmath, Node);
5503 }
5504 
5505 namespace {
5506  struct LValueOrRValue {
5507  LValue LV;
5508  RValue RV;
5509  };
5510 }
5511 
5512 static LValueOrRValue emitPseudoObjectExpr(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5513  const PseudoObjectExpr *E,
5514  bool forLValue,
5515  AggValueSlot slot) {
5516  SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData, 4> opaques;
5517 
5518  // Find the result expression, if any.
5519  const Expr *resultExpr = E->getResultExpr();
5520  LValueOrRValue result;
5521 
5522  for (PseudoObjectExpr::const_semantics_iterator
5523  i = E->semantics_begin(), e = E->semantics_end(); i != e; ++i) {
5524  const Expr *semantic = *i;
5525 
5526  // If this semantic expression is an opaque value, bind it
5527  // to the result of its source expression.
5528  if (const auto *ov = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(semantic)) {
5529  // Skip unique OVEs.
5530  if (ov->isUnique()) {
5531  assert(ov != resultExpr &&
5532  "A unique OVE cannot be used as the result expression");
5533  continue;
5534  }
5535 
5536  // If this is the result expression, we may need to evaluate
5537  // directly into the slot.
5538  typedef CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMappingData OVMA;
5539  OVMA opaqueData;
5540  if (ov == resultExpr && ov->isPRValue() && !forLValue &&
5541  CodeGenFunction::hasAggregateEvaluationKind(ov->getType())) {
5542  CGF.EmitAggExpr(ov->getSourceExpr(), slot);
5543  LValue LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(slot.getAddress(), ov->getType(),
5544  AlignmentSource::Decl);
5545  opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov, LV);
5546  result.RV = slot.asRValue();
5547 
5548  // Otherwise, emit as normal.
5549  } else {
5550  opaqueData = OVMA::bind(CGF, ov, ov->getSourceExpr());
5551 
5552  // If this is the result, also evaluate the result now.
5553  if (ov == resultExpr) {
5554  if (forLValue)
5555  result.LV = CGF.EmitLValue(ov);
5556  else
5557  result.RV = CGF.EmitAnyExpr(ov, slot);
5558  }
5559  }
5560 
5561  opaques.push_back(opaqueData);
5562 
5563  // Otherwise, if the expression is the result, evaluate it
5564  // and remember the result.
5565  } else if (semantic == resultExpr) {
5566  if (forLValue)
5567  result.LV = CGF.EmitLValue(semantic);
5568  else
5569  result.RV = CGF.EmitAnyExpr(semantic, slot);
5570 
5571  // Otherwise, evaluate the expression in an ignored context.
5572  } else {
5573  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(semantic);
5574  }
5575  }
5576 
5577  // Unbind all the opaques now.
5578  for (unsigned i = 0, e = opaques.size(); i != e; ++i)
5579  opaques[i].unbind(CGF);
5580 
5581  return result;
5582 }
5583 
5584 RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPseudoObjectRValue(const PseudoObjectExpr *E,
5585  AggValueSlot slot) {
5586  return emitPseudoObjectExpr(*this, E, false, slot).RV;
5587 }
5588 
5589 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitPseudoObjectLValue(const PseudoObjectExpr *E) {
5590  return emitPseudoObjectExpr(*this, E, true, AggValueSlot::ignored()).LV;
5591 }
